title: janet's chili
directions: Cook 4 hours on low heat.

title: elephant stew(for large groups only)
directions: Cut elephant into small bite-size pieces.
This will take about 2 months.
Marinate in apple cider.
Add enough brown gravy to cover.
Cook over kerosene fire for about 4 weeks at 450°.
This will serve 3,800 people.
If more people are expected, the 2 rabbits may be added.
But do this only if necessary, as most people do not like to find hare in their stew.

title: chicken breast casserole
directions: Boil chicken; skin and remove from bone.
Cut into bite size pieces.
Place in a baking dish.
Mix together English peas that have been drained with soup and water.
Pour over chicken. Combine crushed crackers with melted margarine.
Sprinkle over chicken.
Bake 40 minutes at 350°.

title: chicken baked pork chops
directions: Brown pork chops on both sides and place in casserole dish. Pour Minute rice over top. Mix milk and soup together and pour over this, making sure all rice is moistened. Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: turkey chili
directions: Brown turkey in a large pot; drain well.
Add garlic and onion salt.
Add chopped veggies and beans.
Cook on medium heat and add tomatoes (reserving 1/4 cup of liquid).
Dissolve cornstarch and sugar into reserved liquid.
Add into mixture.
Add chili powder and simmer for 5 minutes.

title: orange sherbet salad
directions: Dissolve jello in hot water; add sherbet and mix well.
When partially set, add orange slices and fold in whipped cream.
Pour into 1 1/2 quart bowl or ring mold.
Chill to set.
Serves 8.

title: stove top baked beans
directions: Fry bacon; set aside.
Slowly fry pork chops until brown.
Cut in small pieces from bone.
Combine beans, ketchup, brown sugar, tomato sauce and mustard in a large pan.
Add the bacon and pork chops and mix well.
Simmer on top of stove for 1 hour or until as thick as you like.
Can make day before and just warm when ready to serve.

title: white party mix
directions: Combine cereal, pretzels and nuts.
Mix well.
Add chopped candy bars.
Toss.
Pour melted morsels over mixture.
Toss until well coated.
Spread mixture onto well sprayed sheet pan to cool. Break into pieces.
Store in airtight container.
Yield 5.25 lbs. Servings:
42 - 2 oz. servings.

title: almond celery bake
directions: Place the celery in a greased 2-quart baking dish. Sprinkle with cheese, pepper and paprika. Top with the soup. Sprinkle with bread crumbs. Cover and bake at 375° for 45 minutes. Uncover; sprinkle with the almonds. Bake 10 to 15 minutes longer or until golden brown. Yield: 10 to 12 servings.

title: shrimp quiches
directions: Grease 2 dozen 1 3/4 cup muffin tins.
Set aside.
Separate rolls into 12 even pieces and cut each in half.
Press dough into bottom and sides of each muffin cup.
Divide shrimp evenly among the muffin cups.

title: pierogi
directions: Mix the flour, salt, egg, butter and water to make medium-soft dough.
Knead well, then roll out until thin.
Cut into circles about 3 3/4 inches in diameter.
Place 1 tablespoon of filling in center of circle and fold over dough.
Pinch the edges well to keep the dumplings from falling apart.
(If you rub water around the edges before folding dough in half, pierogi will hold together better.)
Add some salt and butter to boiling water and drop dumplings in.
When they float to top, cook 2 to 4 minutes.
Do not cook more than 6 pierogi at a time.

title: lemony basil mushroom soup
directions: In a 6-quart Dutch oven, melt margarine.
Saute onion, mushrooms, celery, carrots and garlic in margarine about 5 minutes. Stir in water, chicken broth, chicken soup, basil, pepper, lemon juice, wild and regular rice.
Cover.
Simmer over low heat until wild rice is tender, about 40 minutes.
Serve garnished with lemon slices and Parmesan cheese.
Yields 16 (1 cup) servings.

title: sloppy joes
directions: Cook 2 hours on slow heat or longer.
Makes a lot.

title: mini emmental and gruyere tartlets(makes 24 mini-tarts)
directions: Make these very small if you have little tart tins. If not, make a larger tart and cut into small squares. The cheeses melt well to make a rich tasty tart. Do not use salt as Swiss cheese has a saltiness of its own when cooked. Use the shortcrust pastry to line the tart tins. Mix the cheeses and divide between the lined tart tins. Beat the eggs, cream and pepper together. Pour a little egg mixture over the cheese so that the tart is 3/4 full. Put the tray on the floor of the roasting oven and bake for 15 to 20 minutes until the pastry is crisp and the filling is risen and golden.

title: sour cream blueberry pancakes
directions: Beat eggs, milk and sour cream with wire whip.
Add Bisquick, stirring with wire whip.
Fold in blueberries.
Fry like regular pancakes.

title: cheese souffle
directions: Heat but do not scald milk.
Melt butter in saucepan; stir in flour, milk and seasonings.
Cook, stirring, until smooth and thickened.
Blend in cheese.
Beat egg yolks until thick and lemon colored.
Blend with a little cheese sauce; slowly stir into remaining cheese sauce.
Cool slightly.

title: cream of coconut cake
directions: Bake cake by directions on package.
Long square pan is best to use.
When cake is done, poke holes in it.
Pour cream of coconut over cake, then pour Eagle Brand milk over cake; let soak.
After cake cools, spread Cool Whip on top.
Sprinkle coconut on top. Garnish with cherries or nuts if you wish.

title: chocolate peanut butter marshmallow fudge or freed's fudge
directions: Mix the first 5 ingredients in medium saucepan.
Bring to a boil and cook for 5 minutes.
Remove from heat and add peanut butter and Marshmallow Creme.
Beat quickly until blended and pour into a buttered 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cool completely before cutting.

title: banana split cake
directions: Melt butter and mix with graham crackers.
Press in bottom of pan.
Slice bananas over crumbs.
Mix pudding and pour over bananas.
Put well drained pineapple on top of pudding.
Top with Cool Whip.
Sprinkle nuts and cherries on top of Cool Whip.

title: special garlic bread
directions: Cut 4 slices of Italian bread; warm up in microwave 20 to 30 seconds each.
Spread as much butter desired on each slice of bread.
Place 1/2 slice of cheese on each piece of bread.
Shake garlic powder (as much desired) over piece of bread.
Shake a dash of Mrs. Dash seasoning on cheese and a bit of parsley flakes.

title: chunky applesauce
directions: Cut each apple into half crosswise.
In large saucepan, combine quartered apples, sugar, Sweet One, water, cinnamon and cloves.
Over low heat, cook, covered, stirring frequently, for 10 to 15 minutes or until apples are soft, but still chunky.
Serve warm or cold.
Makes 8 (1/2 cup) servings.
Calories:
115 per 1/2 cup.

title: martha's pecan pie
directions: Mix the ingredients well.
Pour into an unbaked 9-inch pastry pie shell and bake in 350° oven for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: date pie
directions: Crush cookies and press into well-buttered pie plate.
Boil dates in 3/4 cup water with salt added.
Boil 3 minutes.
Add nuts.
Stir in marshmallows.
Pour into crust and place in refrigerator overnight.
Cover with whipped cream and 1/4 cup reserved cookie crumbs.

title: bill edwardsen's famous corn chowder
directions: In a large pan, saute bacon until crisp.
Set aside.
Drain all but 3 tablespoons of drippings.
Lightly saute onions and garlic. Add stock, potatoes and carrots. Cover and bring to a boil over high heat.
Reduce heat. Simmer until vegetables are al dente, about 15 minutes.
Remove cover.

title: russian punch
directions: Let cloves steep in 1/2 gallon of boiling water for 30 minutes.
Let tea steep in 3 cups of boiling water for 5 minutes. Combine tea and clove water.
Add pineapple juice and lemon juice. Sweeten to taste.
Let steep for 10 minutes.
Serve piping hot. Yields 1 gallon.

title: old fashioned cocoa cake
directions: Cream
butter,	sugar,	vanilla
and eggs until fluffy. Beat on	high
speed
3 minutes; reduce speed to low. Combine flour, cocoa, baking soda, baking powder and salt; add alternately
with milk to creamed mixture. Pour into greased cocoa-dusted pans. Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Let cool 10 minutes before removing from pans.

title: quiche diego
directions: Pour into greased pan, 8 x 2-inch.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes.
Lower to 350° for 45 minutes or until knife comes out clean.

title: english pea asparagus casserole
directions: Drain vegetables and save juice.
Place vegetables in casserole.
Make cheese sauce by melting butter in saucepan.
Add flour and thicken.
Add juice and cheese and seasonings.
Cook and stir constantly until smooth.
Pour over vegetables and top with sliced, boiled eggs.
Bake 40 minutes at 350°.

title: microwave chocolate cakelettes
directions: In mixing bowl, stir together flour, sugar, cocoa, baking powder and salt.
Stir in water, egg, oil and vanilla.
Mix thoroughly.
Stir in chocolate chips.
Spoon batter into 6 greased 6 ounce custard cups.
Microwave 3 cakes at a time, uncovered, until wooden pick comes out clean, about 2 minutes.
Loosen edges of cakes; remove from dishes.
Serve warm.

title: date pudding
directions: Put together as listed into a glass baking dish and bake at 350° for 45 minutes to an hour.
Top with whipped cream.

title: chicken chile
directions: Dice and brown chicken in skillet.
Place in crock-pot.
Chop onion and green pepper and place in crock-pot.
Add balance of ingredients and cook in crock-pot until beans are tender.
You can also cook on stove for about 1 hour.

title: finger salad(vegetable pizza)
directions: Press dough into jelly roll pan.
Bake as directed on package. Cool.
Beat cream cheese, mayonnaise and dressing mix until smooth.
Spread on cool crust.
Chop vegetables very fine and put on top.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Keep refrigerated.

title: hot milk cake
directions: Combine eggs, flour, sugar and baking powder.
Combine milk and oleo and let boil.
Pour over egg mixture.
Add vanilla.
Bake at 350° about 1 hour (sheet cake).

title: lemon lush
directions: Mix together nuts, margarine and flour; pat into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake for 20 minutes at 350° and then let cool.

title: chicken wings
directions: Pour liquid ingredients over chicken wing sections.
Marinate overnight.

title: holiday punch
directions: Heat sugar and water until boiling, then cool. Add pineapple juice and freeze just until slushy. When slushy, stir in beaten egg whites. Return to freezer until completely frozen.
Right before serving, add ginger ale and allow time for mixture to thaw. Serve and enjoy.

title: wedding mints
directions: Melt oleo, hot water and oil.
Add sugar and cream.
Sprinkle molds with fine sugar so it will be easy to remove.

title: bread pudding
directions: Put into large pan or bowl.
Bake until brown.

title: peanut butter lo-cal snackies
directions: Butter 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan.
In a medium saucepan, combine corn syrup and both sugars.
Cook over medium heat, stirring frequently, until mixture just comes to a boil.
Remove from heat. Stir in peanut butter until completely blended.
Add corn flake crumbs.
Mix with rubber scraper until evenly coated.
Press into pan with back of buttered spoon.
Cool.
Cut into squares and enjoy!

title: morning special
directions: Place bacon in 1-quart casserole.
Cover and cook 5 to 6 minutes or until crisp.
Remove bacon and crumble.
Reserve 1 tablespoon of bacon drippings.
Add green pepper to bacon drippings and cook 1 minute or until pepper is tender.
Combine eggs and soup.
Pour into casserole with green pepper.
Cook, covered, on 70% power for 5 1/2 to 6 1/2 minutes.
Stir twice during cooking time.
Sprinkle crumbled bacon and cheese over top. Season with salt and pepper as desired.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Mix sugar, flour, soda, cinnamon and salt and set aside. Mix remaining ingredients and add to dry ingredients. Pour into a loaf pan. Bake at 350° for approximately 1 hour.

title: toll house pie
directions: Beat eggs until foamy; beat in flour, sugar and brown sugar. Blend in butter.
Stir in chips and nuts.
Pour into pie crust and bake at 325° for 1 hour.
Serve with Cool Whip or ice cream.

title: mexican rice
directions: Add oil, rice, celery, onion, green bell pepper, garlic and cumin to skillet.
Saute over medium heat, stirring constantly, until rice is brown.
Remove from heat.
Combine water and bouillon cubes in medium saucepan; bring to a boil.
Add to rice mixture.
Stir in tomato sauce.
Heat just until mixture simmers. Cover; continue to simmer 20 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Let stand covered 10 minutes before serving.

title: zippy potatoes(microwave)
directions: Melt margarine in bottom of microwave dish.
Cut potatoes longway in half; then slice them, but keep halves together.
Place flat side down in buttered dish to butter them, then turn to other side.
Sprinkle seasonings on top.
Cook 11 to 12 minutes on Full power.
Serves 2 to 3.

title: hush puppies
directions: Add enough buttermilk to all other ingredients until well mixed.
About 15 minutes before cooking, spread a small amount of hot cooking oil over mixture and allow to rise, then spoon out into hot oil into pan.
Cook until brown.
Place on paper towel to drain.
Makes 1 to 2 dozen hush puppies.

title: featherweight chocolate chip cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cover a large baking sheet with foil; set aside.
In a medium size bowl, beat egg whites until foamy. Gradually add super fine sugar; beat until stiff peaks form.
Mix in vanilla and salt, then fold in chocolate pieces and walnuts. Drop by teaspoonfuls, 2 inches apart, on baking sheet.
Put in oven, then turn off heat and leave cookies at least 5 hours without opening door.
They can be left overnight for convenience. Cookies will be a very light brown in color.
Store airtight until ready to serve.
Makes about 45 cookies.

title: cherry pie
directions: Mix graham crust according to directions on package.
Using mixer, mix softened cream cheese, sugar and milk.
Add Cool Whip. In a large glass dish, layer graham crust (packed), then can of cherry pie filling, then Cool Whip mixture.
Repeat layering with Cool Whip mixture being on top.
Chop pecans fine and sprinkle on top.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Brown beef or sirloin in margarine or butter.
Add mushrooms and onions until browned.
Then add all rest of ingredients, except sour cream.
Simmer 30 minutes.
Slowly add sour cream, stirring constantly.
Do not boil.

title: bisquick chicken
directions: Line a 9 x 13-inch pan with foil.
Spread oil over bottom of pan.
Place dry ingredients in a plastic bag.
Shake chicken parts and place skin side down in pan.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes. Reduce heat to 350° and bake 40 minutes.
Turn chicken halfway through baking.

title: soft molasses cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients together until thoroughly mixed. Roll dough out on floured board and cut or drop by spoonfuls onto cookie sheet.

title: bread and butter pickles
directions: Slice cucumbers thin.
Add sliced onions, peppers, garlic and salt.
Cover with ice and mix thoroughly.
Let stand 3 hours, then drain.
Combine remaining ingredients with 1 cup water.
Pour over cucumber mixture.
Heat to boiling.
Seal in hot, sterilized jars to top (don't leave space).
Put into water bath 10 minutes and remove.

title: hot clam dip
directions: Mix cream cheese, sour cream, mayo, salt and clams and put in baking dish.
Sprinkle heavily with paprika and parsley.
Cover with Parmesan.
Bake 30 minutes at 250°.

title: salt-free salsa
directions: *Red Pack tomato puree is low sodium; use 1 to 2 cups.

title: dill shrimp
directions: Mix well; cover and refrigerate overnight.
Stir once.
Serve with crackers.

title: cousin kathy's quickie quiche
directions: Partially cook bacon and chop. Heat oven to 400 degrees and grease pie plate. Steam broccoli and chop. Mix broccoli, 2 cups of the cheese, ham onion and bacon and place in pie plate. Beat milk, eggs, baking mix, salt and pepper until smooth. Pour over ingredients in pie plate. Bake until knife inserted in center comes out clean (30-40 minutes). Top with remaining cheese. Bake until cheese is melted (1-2 minutes).

title: chocolate dump cake
directions: Bake chocolate cake as per directions on the box.
After cake is baked, crumble it up into a large bowl.
Prepare chocolate pudding and mix it in bowl with crumbled up cake.
Top the mixture with Cool Whip, and place in refrigerator to cool and set. For finishing touch, top with chocolate candy bar shavings and jimmies.
Hope you enjoy it; my family does.

title: shrimp pilaf
directions: In a large heavy pot over medium heat, cook bacon until crisp; remove from pan and set aside (reserving 1 tablespoon of fat).
In the same skillet, cook onion in reserved fat until tender.

Stir in rice, broth, tomatoes, lemon juice and pepper; heat to a boil. Cover; reduce heat and simmer 25 minutes or until rice is done. Stir in shrimp and bacon; cook until shrimp is done, about 5 minutes.
Makes 8 servings.

title: curry dip-fresh vegetables
directions: Mix and refrigerate.
Serve with raw vegetables.

title: southern hamburger pie
directions: Combine meat and onion in large skillet; cook until meat is browned.
Drain meat mixture in colander and pat dry with paper towel; wipe drippings from skillet with a paper towel.
Return meat mixture to skillet; add mushrooms, green chilies and lite cream cheese.
Cook over low heat, stirring constantly, until cheese melts.
Stir in flour, salt, pepper and cumin, blending well.
Split each biscuit in half; pat evenly into a 9-inch pie plate, coated with nonstick spray.
Spoon meat mixture over dough. Combine cottage cheese and egg, mixing well; spread evenly over meat mixture.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Serves 6.
Calories:
Exchanges:
1/2 meat, 1/2 bread and 1/2 fat.

title: quick "crock-pot" gumbo
directions: In a skillet, brown chicken breasts and onions until brown. Prepare brown gravy mix by package directions.
Transfer to crock-pot; then add celery and mushrooms.
Cook in crock-pot on low (6 to 7 hours) or high (4 to 5 hours) or until chicken shreds easily with a fork.
Serve with rice.

title: cabbage rolls
directions: Strip large outer leaves from cabbage head.
Parboil leaves for 5 to 7 minutes in salted water.
Mix all other ingredients together.
On each cabbage leaf, place meat mixture the size of a walnut.
Roll and tuck ends.
Place toothpick to secure.
Place in Dutch oven in tomato juice and cook about 45 minutes on medium heat.

title: date balls
directions: To melted oleo, add sugar, egg and dates.
Bring to boil; boil 3 minutes.
Remove from heat and add Rice Krispies and nuts.
Make into balls and roll in coconut.
This real, so be careful.
Makes about 50 balls.

title: constance's plain vanilla squares
directions: Cream butter and sugar together.
Add a little milk if too stiff.
Add egg, vanilla and nuts.
Bake at 350° in small, well-greased pan for about 30 minutes.
Let cool for about 10 minutes before removing from pan.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Grease and flour two 9 x
x 3-inch bread pans or any pan you want to use.
Sift dry ingredients together.
In other bowl, beat eggs, oil and	sugar.	Add
zucchini,	then the dry ingredients and vanilla.
Mix well.
Pour
in pans and bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Serve warm.

title: cobbler
directions: Melt oleo in a baking dish.
Make a batter of flour, sugar and milk.
Pour into melted oleo.
Mix 1/2 cup of sugar to fruit. Pour over batter.
Do not stir.
Bake at 350° until brown (30 minutes).

title: topping for ice cream
directions: Boil sugar and water for 2 minutes.
Combine ingredients.
Put in a fruit jar and refrigerate.
Will keep until eaten up.

title: mud pie
directions: Mix chocolate and Eagle Brand milk well. Pour into pie crust. Sprinkle with pecans. Pour milk into large bowl; add pudding mix. Beat for 2 minutes. Spoon 1 1/2 cups of pudding over nuts. Add 1/2 of Cool Whip to remaining pudding and mix well.
Spread over pudding in crust. Top with remaining Cool Whip. Refrigerate for 3 hours.

title: french dressing
directions: You might want to reduce sugar a little.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Grease shallow 2 quart baking dish. Spread chicken and vegetables in prepared dish.
Stir soup broth and pepper in a small mixing bowl.
Pour evenly over chicken mixture.
Combine Recip-Ease baking mix or self-rising flour, milk and butter in a separate bowl.
Stir until smooth.
Pour flour mixture over ingredients in the baking dish.
Bake for 45 to 50 minutes or until golden brown.
Cool for 15 minutes before serving.
Makes about 6 servings.

title: chicken stew
directions: Boil chicken and debone and dice.
Dice onions, bell pepper, cabbage and potatoes (you may use other vegetables).
Add diced vegetables, corn and peas to broth.
When vegetables are tender, add noodles and diced chicken.
To thicken, add 6 teaspoons margarine, flour, both types of milk to stew.
Stir until thick; serve hot.
This is good with cornbread.

title: pecan pie
directions: Beat eggs slightly; add sugar, syrup, nuts, salt and vanilla. Pour in unbaked pie shell.
Bake 50 minutes at 350°.
Pecans will come to top forming a crust.

title: santa fe soup
directions: Brown ground chuck and onions. Do not drain. Stir in Ranch dressing and taco seasoning. In large pot, add remaining ingredients; stir and then add meat mixture. Simmer 2 hours. Serve with corn chips and cheese.

title: almond cookies
directions: Stir together flour, sugar, soda and 1/2 teaspoon salt.
Cut in butter until mixture forms fine crumbs.
Combine egg, milk and almond extract.
Add to flour mixture; mix well.
Shape into 1-inch balls.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Place almond half on top of each.
Press to flatten slightly.
Bake in 325° oven for 16 to 18 minutes.
Makes 4 dozen.

title: firehouse creole
directions: Brown meat with onion, salt and bell pepper; drain.
Add tomatoes, tomatoes with green chilies, soup, cabbage and 1 soup can of water.
Cook slowly for 1 hour.

title: raisin easter egg nests
directions: In large bowl, combine 2 cups of the flour, the sugar, salt and yeast.
In small saucepan over low heat, combine milk, water, butter, orange peel and nutmeg.
Heat to very hot (120° to 130°). Butter need not melt completely.
Stir milk mixture into yeast mixture and beat with electric mixer at medium speed 2 minutes, scraping bowl as needed.
Add 3 of the eggs and 1 more cup of flour.
Beat at high speed 3 minutes.
Stir in raisins and enough of the remaining flour to make a soft dough.
Turn onto floured board and knead 8 to 10 minutes, until dough is smooth and elastic. Form into a ball and place in greased bowl.
Cover and let rise in warm place until almost doubled, about 1 hour.

title: pumpkin bars
directions: Beat eggs, sugar, oil and pumpkin until light and fluffy. Stir together dry ingredients and add to pumpkin mix.
Blend thoroughly.
Bake in bar pan at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: hamburger pie
directions: Brown meat in 9-inch Corning dish in microwave oven.
Peel potatoes and boil converting into mashed potatoes.
Then top meat with mashed potatoes, add corn as next layer, then top with peas. Place in conventional oven at 375° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: cream cheese frosting
directions: Blend butter, cream cheese and sugar with electric mixer until well blended.
Add vanilla and mix again.

title: 10 minute spaghetti sauce
directions: Saute ground beef in skillet, drain fat.
Add remaining ingredients; heat to boil.
Simmer 10 minutes.
Stir occasionally. Serve over hot cooked spaghetti.
Serves 4.

title: delicious chicken
directions: In a frying pan, put olive oil.
Heat it, adding minced garlic and finely chopped onion.
Stir it up, then remove it from the fire.

In a roasting pan, place the seasoned pieces of chicken. Add the garlic and onion mixture and the raw, quartered potatoes. Sprinkle parsley and put it in a hot oven at medium temperature (350° probably) for 1 1/2 hours, being careful not to burn it, only golden brown it.
Don't cover it!

title: cocoa peanut butter mounds
directions: Mix cocoa and sugar in a saucepan.
Add butter and milk.
Bring to a boil for 2 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Remove from heat. Stir in rolled oats, peanut butter and vanilla.
Mix well.
Drop on waxed paper a spoonful at a time.
Let cool thoroughly before serving or storing.

title: syrup tea cakes
directions: Mix all ingredients together; dissolve soda in hot water. Add flour.
Mix well.
Bake at 375 degrees for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: minnie's candy
directions: Sift sugar, melt margarine and milk, being careful not to scorch.
Pour into sugar.
Mix well.
Add nuts and coconut.
Mix well and pour onto large cookie sheet spread to about 1/4 to 1/2-inch thick.
Pat to smooth.
Place in freezer 45 minutes or refrigerate 3 hours.
Cut into squares and dip in chocolate mixture.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Cook sugar, water, cornstarch and Jell-O until syrupy.
Bake pie crust.
Let cool.
Put strawberries in crust.
Pour filling over strawberries.
Place in refrigerator and allow to congeal. Serve with Cool Whip.

title: frosted pretzels
directions: Measure 1 cup frosting (refrigerate remaining frosting for another time).
Heat the 1 cup frosting in top of double boiler over hot water until frosting is liquid, stirring occasionally. Remove from heat.
(Keep the top of the double boiler over the hot water.)
Dip the pretzels into the frosting with your fingers, then place them on waxed paper.
Let dry 8 hours.

title: strawberry-banana salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water; stir in fruit.
Pour half of gelatin mixture into an 8-inch dish and refrigerate until firm; store remaining gelatin mixture at room temperature.
Spread congealed gelatin with 1 cup sour cream.
Spoon remaining gelatin over sour cream and refrigerate until firm.
Top with remaining 1 cup sour cream, spreading evenly.
Sprinkle with nuts.
Yields 8 to 10 servings.

title: hanky panky
directions: Brown hamburger and sausage; drain and add cheese. Heat until melted. Serve with tortilla chips.

title: orange slice cake icing
directions: Mix this and let stand while cake is baking; remove cake from oven.
Let cool for 5 minutes.
Run a knife around edges; then pour over cake.
Let cool in pan.
Wrap and then freeze for best results.

title: taco salad
directions: Brown ground beef with taco seasoning.
Drain good.
Mix lettuce, tomato, onion, black olives and 3/4 grated cheese in a large bowl.
Drain.
Drain kidney beans; add beans and meat.
Mix well, then mix in 1/2 bag tortilla chips.
Serve in salad bowls. Top with cheese and sour cream.

title: spanish omelet
directions: Put oil in pan.
Beat eggs in bowl.
Add eggs to pan when oil is hot.
When bottom is done, flip and cook top.
When top is done, flip again and add cheese and onion.
Fold in half and let cheese melt completely.
Flip once more when folded.

title: bokhari rice
directions: Mix the tomato juice with the spices and set aside.
Heat the oil, then drop the meat pieces all at once and cover for 2 minutes.
Uncover and stir well.
Saute the onions with the meat until almost golden brown.
Add the tomato juice mixture and water; cook for 40 minutes or until the meat is tender.
Remove the meat from the tomato sauce and set aside.
Wash the carrots and boil in 2 cups water.
Add 1/2 teaspoon salt and 1 tablespoon oil.
Cook for 20 minutes or until tender.
Strain the cooking water of the carrots over the tomato mixture and set the carrots aside.
Add the rice to the tomato mixture.
Place a soup spoon in the middle of the rice pot; if it remains standing, then the quantity of the broth is just right, if not, there is too much broth.
When the rice reaches the boiling stage, reduce the heat and cook for 40 minutes.

title: freezer pickles
directions: Sprinkle 2 tablespoons salt on the cucumbers and onion.
Let set 2 hours. Warm only to dissolve sugar and vinegar.
Now put cucumbers in small containers and pour liquids over them and freeze.

title: apple dumplings
directions: Peel apple and cut into 8 wedges. Place an apple wedge in each roll, sprinkle with cinnamon. Roll as you would a crescent roll. Place 8 rolls in a pie plate. Melt oleo, add sugar and orange juice, stir, pour over rolls. Bake approximately 40 minutes at 350 degrees. Serve with ice cream or plain. Good for breakfast. Enjoy!!!

title: tamale pie
directions: Mix well.
Then add enough water to make mixture thin.
After putting topping on meat mixture, bake at 450° until cornbread is brown.

title: brownie goody bars
directions: Stir brownie mix, water, oil and eggs until well blended. Spread in 9x13 pan and bake at 350°F oven for 28-30 minutes.
Cool about one hour.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Cook zucchini, carrots, onions (saute 5 minutes).
Drain, combine soup and sour cream and add vegetables.
Combine stuffing mix and margarine.
Spread 1/2 mix on bottom of pan.
Add vegetable mix and then spread remaining stuffing mix on top.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes at 350°.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Prepare crust.
Fit bottom crust into pie pan.
Prepare bouillon broth by dissolving granules in 2 cups boiling water.
Melt butter; blend in flour and salt.
Allow to bubble slowly about 30 seconds.
Add broth and milk gradually. Cook and stir until thick and bubbly.
Add remaining ingredients. Heat until bubbly.
Pour into pastry crust.
Put on the top crust. Seal and flute the edge.
Cover edge with aluminum foil, dull side down.
Bake uncovered in 425° oven until golden brown, 30 to 35 minutes.

title: salsa
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Bring to a boil and let boil for 1 hour. Put in hot pint jars and seal.
Makes about 8 pints.

title: coconut pie
directions: Mix all ingredients except coconut and vanilla; cook in double boiler until
thickened.
Add coconut and vanilla; pour into baked pie shell and
top
with
meringue and brown or use Cool Whip for topping.

title: my grandma's chocolate cake
directions: Mix together in listed order.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes in a 9-inch square pan.
Double the recipe for a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cake is so rich and moist, Grandma usually just sprinkled powdered sugar on top when cool.
Vanilla icing or ice cream is great, too.

title: mixed vegetable casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients except butter and crackers.
Place in baking dish.
Combine butter and crackers.
Sprinkle over top. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: lemon bread
directions: Cream butter; gradually add sugar, creaming well.
Add egg yolks and beat well.
Blend together the dry ingredients; add to egg-yolk mixture alternately with milk.
Blend just to mix.
Fold in stiffly beaten egg whites, chopped nuts and lemon peel. Turn into 3 greased and lightly floured loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 55 to 60 minutes or until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.
Combine lemon juice and remaining 1/2 cup sugar.
Prick all over top of loaves with toothpick.
Immediately spoon lemon juice mixture over hot loaves.
Cool 1 hour before removing from pans.
Do not cut for 24 hours (it will slice easily).
Makes 3 loaves.

title: three bean chili
directions: Drain and rinse 3 cans of beans.
Chop onion and garlic.
In a large saucepan, heat oil.
Add garlic and onion; cook until soft. Add tomatoes, beans and seasonings.
Simmer 1 hour.

title: down south pecan pie
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Cream butter well.
Add sugar slowly, creaming until light.
Slowly stir in syrup, eggs, vanilla and 1 cup nuts.
Pour into shell.
Top with rest of nuts.
Bake for 55 minutes.
I cool pie crust for several hours before adding filling.
Serve small wedges with whipped cream flavored with sherry.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Cream eggs and sugar until creamy.
Add oil and blend well. Sift all dry ingredients together and add to sugar mixture.
This batter will be thick.
Fold in chopped apples and then add vanilla.
Sprinkle butterscotch chips on top.
Bake in greased and floured 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 55 minutes or until done.
No frosting is necessary.
If you prefer, serve cake warm with whipped cream.

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: Mix together everything but the salsa.
Stuff mixture into tortilla shells evenly and wrap.
Place enchiladas seam side down in baking dish (9 x 13-inch).
Cover with aluminum foil and bake for 20 minutes at 375°.
Remove from oven and immediately pour salsa over top.
(Low-fat sour cream and cheese can be used in this recipe.)

title: mike's favorite casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients in a large bowl.
Place in a 9 x 13-inch pan and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: hearty bean and pasta stew
directions: Mix all ingredients in a 2-quart saucepan.
Heat to boiling, stirring occasionally; reduce heat.
Cover and simmer about 15 minutes, stirring occasionally, until macaroni is tender.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Combine 1/2 package cream cheese and margarine.
Mix until blended.
Add flour and salt; mix well.
Form into a ball and chill 1/2 hour.
On a slightly floured surface, roll to a 14-inch circle.
Place in a 12-inch pizza pan and prick bottom and sides with a fork.
Bake at 425° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Combine remaining cream cheese, sugar and juice; mix until blended.
Fold in whipped cream and spoon into crust.
Place fruit on crust and serve.

title: peach mess
directions: Use a 13 x 9-inch cake pan.
Drain the peaches.
Put peaches in cake pan.
Take box of yellow cake mix (dry) and put on top of peaches.
Take the margarine and slice on top of the cake mix all over.
Bake at 350° until lightly brown.

title: green chile rice casserole
directions: Mix rice, sour cream, salt and pepper to taste (add onions, if you like).
Add half to Pam sprayed casserole.
Top with grated Monterey Jack cheese.
Cover with diced green chiles, then add layer of grated cheese, Cheddar, then add rice, sour cream, Monterey Jack cheese and chiles.
Bake uncovered 45 minutes at 350°.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Cook, drain and crumble ground beef.
Mix together ground beef, onion, celery, soups, dry milk, drained green beans and grated cheese.
Put into a casserole dish; cover with Tater Tots. Bake in a 400° oven until the casserole is hot and bubbly.

title: roast beef supreme
directions: Roll roast lightly in pepper and flour.
Put cooking oil in pan.
Brown roast in pan.
Sprinkle onion soup mix over roast. Pour mushroom soup over roast.
Add water and cover.
Bake at 350° until tender (25 to 30 minutes per pound).
Serve over rice if desired.

title: sour cream cake
directions: Grease and flour a tube pan; set aside.
Sift flour.
Add baking soda and sift twice more; set aside.
Cream butter.
Add sugar gradually and cream together well until fluffy.
Add egg yolks one by one (saving egg whites in a separate bowl), mixing well.
Add sour cream and flour mixture alternately, mixing well between each addition.
Beat egg whites until fluffy and fold into batter.
Pour into greased and floured tube pan.
Bake 1 1/2 hours at 300°.

title: pepperoni roll(appetizer)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Remove the outer layer of skin from 1 to 6 heads of garlic.
Cut 1/2-inch off from each head straight across top and arrange in shallow baking pan.
Drizzle 2 teaspoons olive oil over each head, letting it run between the cloves.
Cover with foil and bake 30 minutes.
Remove foil and bake 30 to 45 minutes more, until garlic is tender when pierced with a toothpick.
Cool slightly.

title: 24 hour salad
directions: Mix grapes and pineapple with dry pudding mix.
Add marshmallows and Cool Whip.
Blend well.
Best if refrigerated 24 hours before serving.

title: mexican fruit cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together with a spoon. Grease and flour a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Pour in batter and bake at 350° for 35 minutes or until golden brown.
Make the icing while the cake is in the oven.

title: browned butter glaze
directions: Heat margarine over low heat until golden brown. Remove from heat.
Stir in powdered sugar and vanilla. Beat in 2 to 4 tablespoons hot water until smooth and of desired consistency.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Bake at 350° in a casserole dish until firm.
You make top with marshmallows and return to oven until light brown.

title: diabetic applesauce cake
directions: Cook raisins in water until about dry.
Add apaplesauce, sugar, eggs & oil.
Mix well. Add flour, soda, vanilla & spices. It will be thick.
Spread in 9x13 pan and bake at 325° for 25-30 minutes.

title: cherry sandwiches
directions: Beat cream cheese until smooth.
Cut up cherries.
Add drained pineapple, drained well.
Mix all together.
Add mayonnaise to ingredients.
Make sandwiches using three slices of bread.
Chill and slice in desired size.

title: deluxe strawberry pizza dessert(in honor of "dan patch")
directions: For the crust, take the first 3 ingredients listed; mix and spread on pizza pan.
Bake at 350° for about 10 minutes.
Cool.

title: cheese biscuits
directions: Cream margarine; add flour, grated cheese and red pepper. Mixture will be very stiff; chill.
Roll out on lightly floured surface and cut into 2 or 3-inch circles.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: cheese grits
directions: In a saucepan, bring water, milk and salt to a boil.
Add grits, reduce heat and cook until done, stirring occasionally. Add butter, cheeses, Worcestershire, garlic powder and cayenne. Stir until the butter and cheeses have melted.
Put in greased 3-quart casserole and sprinkle with paprika.
Bake in 350° oven for 15 to 20 minutes or until heated thoroughly.
Makes 12 side dish servings or 6 main dish servings.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Combine flour, sugar and soda in large bowl.
Cut in shortening; stir in yeast and buttermilk.
Mix very well.
Keep covered in refrigerator at least one hour or two before using. Roll out and cut as desired.
Place on greased pan.
Allow them to rise for 2 hours.
Bake at 450° approximately 10 minutes or until golden brown (450° oven).

title: deviled carrots
directions: Cook carrots in water until just tender.
Drain.
Then saute in butter for 5 minutes.
Add brown sugar, mustard, 2 drops Tabasco sauce, salt and pepper.
Cook, covered, about 10 minutes.

title: homemade chicken noodle soup
directions: Add all ingredients to water, except egg noodles.
Bring to boil, then simmer about 45 minutes or until carrots are tender and water has reduced about 1/3.
Add egg noodles about last 10 minutes of cooking time and boil until tender.

title: cauliflower
directions: Place cauliflower in 1 1/2-quart glass dish.
Add water. Cover and microwave for 8 to 10 minutes.
Combine mayonnaise, mustard and onion.
Spoon sauce on top of cauliflower and sprinkle with cheese.
Roast for 2 minutes.
Let stand 2 minutes; serve.

title: hamburger salami
directions: Do not substitute salts or use lean ground chuck.

title: frosted cinnamon rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Stir in cooled milk, sugar, oil, baking powder, salt, egg and 1 to 1 1/2 cups flour.
Beat until smooth.
Mix in remaining flour to make dough easy to handle.
Turn dough onto well floured board; knead 5 minutes or until smooth.
Let dough rest 15 to 20 minutes.
Roll to a 12 x 10-inch rectangle.
Spread with 4 tablespoons softened butter. Sprinkle evenly with a mixture of 1/2 cup sugar and 1 1/2 teaspoons cinnamon.
Roll up, beginning at wide end.
Cut into 12 slices.
Place in a 9 x 13-inch greased pan, slightly apart (4 rows of 3 each).
Refrigerate at least 12 hours.
Heat oven to 350° and bake for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: orange slice cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add eggs one at a time.
Mix well. Dissolve soda in buttermilk; add to creamed mixture.
Place flour in bowl.
Add dates, candy and nuts.
Stir to coat each piece.
Add mixture and coconut to creamed mixture and mix.
Bake in tube pan at 250° for 2 1/2 to 3 hours.

title: peanut butter frosting
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Use electric beater for best results.

title: peach cobbler bake
directions: Pour peaches and juice into baking dish (approximately 9 x 9-inch).
Mix sugar and Bisquick together and sprinkle on top. Cut oleo into slices and layer top.
Bake at 325° for 25 to 30 minutes, or until top is golden brown.
Heavenly! An original recipe.

title: krumkake(this very old recipe is from norway, as is my father.)
directions: A very old cookie recipe I got from Myrtle Boyer when she played Mrs. Santa Claus at O.H. Garden Club display.

title: hot fudge pudding cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
In medium bowl, combine 3/4 cup sugar, flour, 3 tablespoons cocoa, baking powder and salt.
Blend in milk, butter and vanilla.
Beat until smooth.
Pour batter into pan.
In small bowl, combine remaining 1/2 cup sugar, brown sugar and remaining 4 tablespoons cocoa.
Sprinkle mixture evenly over batter.
Pour hot water over top.
Bake 35 to 40 minutes or until center is almost set.
Let stand 15 minutes.
Spoon into dessert dishes.
Serve with ice cream or whipped cream.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: german apple cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together with a spoon.
Do not use mixer. Batter will be stiff.
Spread into greased and floured 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake in 350°
oven for 45 to 60 minutes.
Serve with whipped topping or ice cream.

title: irish potato soup
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bring to a boil.
Simmer.
Salt and pepper to taste.

title: diabetic ice cream
directions: *Lesser amount of evaporated milk may be used with whipped cream of equal portion.

title: chili dip
directions: Heat chili in saucepan on low heat.
Stir in cream cheese and Cheddar cheese.
When melted, serve warm with nacho chops.

title: amish sugar cookies
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients; beat well. Add eggs; beat again. Add remaining ingredients and mix well. Drop small balls of dough on cookie sheet and flatten slightly with a fork. Bake in 375° oven 10 to 12 minutes.

title: toffee bars
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Cream butter and margarine well with sugar.
Add vanilla; mix.
Add flour, nuts and chocolate chips. Bake for 20 to 25 minutes in a 13 x 9-inch jelly roll pan.
Cool and cut in squares.

title: make ahead party chicken
directions: Wrap each piece of chicken with a strip of partially cooked bacon.
Cover bottom of flat, greased dish (12 x 8-inch) with dried beef.
Arrange chicken on beef.
Mix soup and sour cream, then pour over chicken.
Cover and refrigerate (even overnight).
Bake uncovered at 275° for 3 hours.
Serve over wild or white rice. Serves 8.

title: pumpkin cake
directions: Sift all dry ingredients.
Add others into bowl; mix well. Bake 1 hour or until cake leaves no imprint.
Ice.

title: roast beef roll-ups
directions: Mix mayonnaise and garlic together. Spread mixture on the tortillas. Layer spinach, roast beef, cheese on top of mixture. Roll up tortilla tightly. Wrap in foil and refrigerate until ready to serve. Slice in pinwheels when ready to serve.

title: potato soup
directions: Cook diced potatoes, onions, salt and pepper in water until soft.
Set aside with water.
In small saucepan, simmer margarine, flour, milk and a dash of salt.
Cook this until thickened.
Cook separately the bacon strips.
Use oil from bacon to mix all ingredients together and simmer to preferred thickness.
Serve with bacon bits on top.

title: chocolate pretzels(microwave)
directions: Melt entire package almond bark in microwave, stirring well until smooth.
Drop handful of pretzels at a time.
Stir well; remove one pretzel at a time.
Place on waxed paper until hardened.

title: cocktail meatballs
directions: Meatballs:
Mix hamburger, soy sauce, cornflakes, parsley flakes, garlic powder, eggs, onion, ketchup and pepper.
Roll into 1-inch balls and place in a shallow baking pan.

title: chocolate chip bundt cake
directions: Mix cake mix, eggs, pudding, oil and water for 4 minutes. Pour 3/4 batter into well-greased and floured Bundt pan.
To the 1/4 left, add chocolate syrup and chocolate chips.
Pour over batter in pan and swirl lightly.
Bake in 350° oven for 55 to 60 minutes.
Cool.
Remove from pan.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: chicken with chipped beef
directions: Wrap each breast with strip of bacon.
Cover bottom of pan with chipped beef (tear up). Lay chicken on beef.
Sprinkle dried or fresh onion on top.
Mix soup, sour cream and pour over chicken.
Cover and refrigerate 3 1/4 hours.
Bake, uncovered, at 275° for 3 hours.
I use chicken breast halves and shorten baking time.

title: fruit dip
directions: Mix 2 ingredients with electric mixer until fluffy.
Serve as dip with strawberries, melon or any fruit.
Makes 1 1/4 cups.

title: raisin cream pie
directions: Cook raisins in water for 15 minutes.
Add the rest of the ingredients; cook on low heat, stirring, until thickened.
Pour into baked crust.
May be topped with meringue or served plain.

title: butter fingers
directions: Cream sugar and butter.
Add flour and other ingredients. Pinch off tiny pieces.
Roll between the palms.
Bake about 30 minutes at 325° or 350°.
Take from oven.
Roll, while hot, in the powdered sugar.

title: mama's p-nut butter pie
directions: Mix sugar, peanut butter and cream cheese.
Blend in Cool Whip.
Pour into crust.
Chill at least 4 hours.

title: baked stew
directions: Arrange beef cubes in single layer; do not brown.
Place vegetables on top, then sauce, water and sugar.
Scatter tapioca over top and seal with foil.
May either bake 1 1/2 hours at 325° or 8 to 10 hours at 200°.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Mix ingredients well, into balls.
Then roll in coconut (optional) or pat flat in a pan as fudge.
Refrigerate.

title: crusty garlic bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cut loaf in half lengthwise.
Melt some butter in bowl and stir in olive oil.
Spread on bread and sprinkle with garlic, seasoning and Parmesan cheese.
Bake 15 minutes at 350°; cut into 1-inch strips.

title: o' henry bars
directions: Bring sugar and corn syrup to a boil; add peanut butter and mix
well.	Pour
over
Rice
Krispies
and peanuts.
Mix lightly and
add
chocolate
chips last (as they don't melt). Pour into 9 x 13-inch buttered pan.
Cool and cut into bars.

title: rachel's easy tomato chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Wash, dry and season chicken.
Saute onion in oil.
Add undiluted tomato soup.
Cook slowly for 5 minutes.
Add sour cream to sauce.
Pour over chicken which has been layered in ovenproof casserole.
Cook 1 hour.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Sift dry ingredients into large bowl.
Add shortening, eggs and about half the applesauce; beat until smooth, about 2 minutes.
Add remaining applesauce, water and vanilla and beat about 1 minute longer.
Bake in greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan in a moderate oven at 375° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Use a 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Melt butter, mix with peaches.
Sprinkle cake mix over top of peaches and pat gently to spread.
Make a few holes so juice can come up.
Melt another stick of butter, add to top of cake mix.
Sprinkle with nutmeg.
Bake for 45 minutes.

title: oven fried chicken
directions: Salt and pepper chicken about 15 minutes ahead of baking. Mix crumbs, cornmeal and seasonings. Dip chicken in melted shortening and then in crumb mixture and place into greased baking pan. Bake at 400° for 20 minutes. Turn and bake on 325° for 40 to 50 minutes. (Pour a little shortening on top of chicken.)

title: pork kabobs
directions: In resealable plastic bag or shallow glass container, combine the first 8 ingredients; add pork and toss to coat. Seal or cover and refrigerate overnight. Drain pork and discard marinade; thread pork on skewers, leaving a small space between pieces. Grill, uncovered, over medium coals for 8-10 minutes or until the meat is no longer pink, turning frequently. Serve in pita bread with sauce.

title: chili con queso dip
directions: Chop up tomatoes and place in a colander with the chilies to drain.
Add onion and mix thoroughly, set aside to drain.

title: irene's wheat bread
directions: Put 8 cups warm water in large bowl; stir in sugar until dissolved.
Sprinkle yeast over sugar water and set until yeast is bubbly.
Stir in salt, Postum, molasses and potato flakes.
Then add wheat flour; stir in well.
Stir in vinegar and allow to sit 20 to 30 minutes.
Beat batter with wooden spoon 2 to 3 minutes until mixture begins to get "glue-y" or "globby" --- that means the gluten is ready.
Then add the oil and stir in until it disappears. Beat in 5 cups white flour until mixed in, then beat in enough more to make a kneadable dough (dough will be sticky).
Knead 5 to 7 minutes, until dough is smooth and elastic.
Add flour as needed to keep dough from sticking to the surface.
On lightly floured surface, let raise until doubled in size; punch down and let raise again (you can skip the second raising if time is short).
Punch down; divide into 4 equal parts.
Knead each part into a smooth round ball; let rest 10 minutes.
Shape each ball into a loaf and place in a greased loaf pan.
Let loaves raise until about 2-inches above rim of pan.
Bake in preheated oven at 375° for 42 minutes, or until done.
Remove from oven; wait 2 minutes.
Remove from pans and cool on clean dish towel.
Enjoy.
Makes 4 large loaves.

title: beef pie
directions: Cook beef and onion together; drain.
Beat milk, eggs and Bisquick.
Place beef in a greased baking dish; pour over milk mixture.
Top with tomatoes and cheese.
Bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes, or until done.

title: best ever simple banana cake
directions: Combine the ingredients with electric mixer.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes, or until done.

title: jumbo raisin cookies
directions: Cream Crisco, sugar and eggs well.
Add vanilla and cooled raisin mixture.
Set aside.
Sift together flour, salt, cinnamon, nutmeg and allspice.
Add to raisin mixture and blend well.
Add 1 cup chopped nuts.
Drop on cookie sheet and bake 10 to 12 minutes in 350° oven.
Makes 6 dozen.

title: pineapple coconut pie
directions: Bake in unbaked pie shell 10 minutes at 450°, then 30 minutes at 350°.

title: clam fritters
directions: Mix and sift flour, salt and pepper.
Add clam liquid, milk and eggs.
Stir until well blended.
Add clams and butter.
Mix thoroughly.
Drop from spoon into deep hot fat.
Fry for 4 to 6 minutes.

title: spicy hot eggplant casserole
directions: Cook eggplant in small amount of boiling water 5 minutes; drain well.

Layer half the eggplant, tomatoes, bread crumbs, oregano, tomato sauce, Parmesan cheese and Cheddar cheese in a 1 1/2-quart casserole dish coated with cooking spray. Repeat layers, omitting top layer of Cheddar cheese.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 15 minutes. Sprinkle with remaining Cheddar cheese and bake 5 minutes more.
Makes 3 servings.

title: blonde brownies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Over low heat, slowly melt the shortening or margarine, taking care not to scorch.
Remove from heat and blend in brown sugar.
Cool.
Stir in egg.
Sift together and stir in flour, baking powder and salt.
Stir in vanilla or nuts. Spread in a well-greased and floured OR wax paper lined 8 x 8 x 2-inch (square) pan.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes until a light touch with finger leaves a slight imprint.
Brownies should look a light golden color.
Do NOT overcook.
Cut into bars while warm.

title: sunshine raisin casserole
directions: In a large skillet, melt margarine and saute onions, carrots, string beans and caraway seed for 5 minutes.
Add peppers and cook 3 more minutes.
Add zucchini and cook for 3 more minutes, stirring constantly.
Add mushrooms and cook an additional 5 minutes, covered.
(Drain off any liquid.)
Add cooked rice, raisins, chopped walnuts, dillweed and tamari, salt and pepper.
Place mixture in a buttered casserole and top with grated Cheddar cheese. Bake at 375° for 15 minutes or until casserole is heated through and cheese is melted.
Makes 6 servings.

title: squash casserole
directions: Put squash, onion, salt and water together; cook until tender. Drain.
Put in a 1 1/2-quart baking dish.
Add cracker crumbs, egg, cheese soup and 1/2 stick butter.
Melt the other 1/2 stick of butter; stir in Shredded Wheat.
Stir until well coated; sprinkle over squash mixture.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 30 minutes, or until bubbly and top is golden brown.

title: busy-day burgers
directions: Brown ground beef in a heavy skillet, stirring to separate meat particles.
Sprinkle flour over meat; stir in until well mixed with meat.
Add soup; cook until thoroughly heated and slightly thickened.

title: fruitcake cookies(good!!!)
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
Cream the first 7 ingredients.
Add the nuts and fruit, which has been chopped.
Drop by 1/2 teaspoonful (bite-size) on a greased cookie sheet.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes until lightly golden brown.

title: lemon squares
directions: Mix first three ingredients and press into 9 x 13-inch glass pan.
Bake 15 minutes in 350° oven.
Beat eggs slightly, add remaining ingredients and mix.
Pour over top of hot crust.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes in 350° oven.
Remove from oven and sprinkle with powdered sugar.
Cool overnight or 4 hours in refrigerator.
Cut into squares.
Makes 32 small squares.

title: summer peach tea punch
directions: Boil water to steep tea and mint. Steep about 15 minutes and remove tea bags. Leave mint in solution until cool. Strain into 2-gallon container. Add lemonade, peach nectar and syrup concentrate. Add the ginger ale and soda. Taste before adding Simple Syrup.

title: hot cocoa mix
directions: Combine the first 3 ingredients thoroughly in a gallon ice cream bucket.
Fill almost to top of container with dry milk. Store in airtight container.
To serve, spoon 3 to 4 teaspoons of mix in cup.
Add 1 cup boiling water; stir well.

title: fresh strawberry pie
directions: Mix sugar and Jell-O.
Add water.
Mix cornstarch with a little water.
Let dissolve.
Add to mixture.
Bring to a boil and let thicken.
Cool and add berries.

title: pecan frosties
directions: Cream butter and 1 cup brown sugar in bowl.
Bet in egg and vanilla.
Add mixture of flour, soda and salt gradually, mixing well after each addition.
Shape into 1-inch balls.
Place 2 inches apart on cookie sheets.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Cook together the tomatoes, onions and red pepper, then add tomato paste, sugar, salt, oregano, Wesson oil and basil.
Cook until thick and can.

title: swiss cream of potato soup
directions: Cook potatoes in small amount of water in saucepan until tender; drain and mash.
Saute bacon and onion over low heat, stirring, until golden brown.
Add bacon mixture, butter, parsley, salt, nutmeg, pepper, mustard and Worcestershire sauce to potatoes.
Stir in milk; simmer, stirring constantly, until heated through.
Sprinkle with cheese; serve at once.

title: taco seasoning mix
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Add to 1 pound hamburger that has been browned and drained.
Stir in 1/2 cup of water and simmer 10 minutes.
Mix equals 1 package of commercial taco mix.

title: earthquake cake
directions: Spread coconut on bottom of 13 x 9 x 2-inch cake pan.
Spread pecans over coconut.
Mix German chocolate cake mix per directions on box; pour over coconut and pecans.
Mix together margarine, cream cheese and powdered sugar.
Drop this mixture from spoon in dollops onto cake mix; do not stir.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: boston baked beans
directions: Soak beans overnight in a large pot with 6 cups water.
Add the baking soda and bring to a boil.
Allow to simmer 10 minutes; drain and reserve liquid.
Place the beans, salt pork and onions in a bean pot or casserole.
Add molasses, sugar, dry mustard, salt, pepper and a cup of the bean liquid.
Stir thoroughly and add enough liquid to cover the beans.
Cover with lid.
Bake 2 hours at 300°.
Add the remaining liquid and stir.
Bake an additional 1 1/2 hours or until the beans are tender.
Uncover for last 1/2 hour of cooking.
Total cooking time is 3 1/2 hours at 300°.
Serves 8.

title: swedish rice pudding
directions: Beat eggs.
Add cooled milk.
Mix well.
Add rest of ingredients. Pour into buttered 9 x 9-inch baking dish.
Set dish in pan of hot water in oven.
Bake in slow oven for 1 hour at 325°.
Take out and sprinkle with nutmeg.

title: tuna salad
directions: Drain tuna and place in mixing bowl.
Chop celery and sweet pickles; add to tuna.
Chop boiled egg and add with other ingredients.
Add mustard, mayonnaise and salt and pepper to taste. Mix well.
Refrigerate leftovers.

title: taco chicken
directions: Marinate 6 to 8 chicken breasts overnight.
Grill to cook.

title: impossible quiche
directions: Mix together in a blender all ingredients except cheese and meat.
Pour into a greased pie pan.
Put grated cheese and meat in mixture in pie pan and gently push below surface with a spoon. Bake in 350°
oven for 45 minutes.
Let stand 10 minutes before serving.

title: cocktail wieners
directions: Stir together jelly and mustard over warm heat. Add wieners (each cut into 4 or 5 pieces) and let simmer about 20 minutes. Serve warm in chafing dish.

title: french bean casserole
directions: Mix the first seven ingredients.
Melt margarine and crush Ritz crackers.
Mix with toasted almonds.
Sprinkle over top of mixture.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: apple pockets
directions: Put the apples, walnuts, brown sugar, raisins, flour, lemon peel and cinnamon into a bowl.
Mix these together.
Then roll with a rolling pin; roll pastry to 1/8-inch thickness.
Cut into 5-inch circles.
Spoon 1/4 cup of apple mixture into center of circle.
Moisten edges of pastry with few drops of water.
Fold pastry and trim the edges with a fork.
Place on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 450° for 10 minutes, then turn down heat to 400° and bake 10 more minutes.
Brush each with milk and the sugar. Take out of oven.
Then put back into the oven for 5 minutes.
It makes 10 to 12 servings.
Yum!
Yum!

title: beef goulash with vegetables
directions: Heat oil in large heavy kettle.
Add onion and green pepper and cook, stirring often, until onion is golden.
Add paprika, beef and salt and cook, stirring until meat loses its red color. Add tomatoes and 3/4 cup water.
Bring to a boil, cover and simmer 1 1/2 hours.
Add potatoes and carrots and cook until all is tender.
Makes 6 servings.

title: anchovy veal rolls
directions: Top each piece of veal with some cheese and one anchovy. Sprinkle with salt and pepper; roll and tie with string.
In melted butter, cook rolls uncovered on top of stove, turning occasionally.
Add wine and cook 10 minutes.
Remove string and arrange on platter.
Pour on sauce and garnish with fresh parsley.

title: christmas crown cake
directions: Cream together margarine, brown sugar and egg.
Add dry mix and Cola.
Stir in raisins, nuts and fruit.
Put in greased tube pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: kahlua
directions: Mix 3 cups water and sugar in saucepan.
Bring to boil; reduce heat.
Simmer 20 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Add vanilla bean halves.
Let stand until cool.

title: hot fudge pudding cake
directions: In medium mixing bowl, stir together the 1/2 cup sugar, flour, the 2 tablespoons cocoa powder and baking powder.
Stir in milk, butter and vanilla.
Pour into 3-quart microwave-safe dish.
In small mixing bowl, combine 3/4 cup sugar and 1/4 cup cocoa powder. Stir
in
hot
water.
Pour evenly over batter. Do not stir. Microwave
uncovered
on High for 5 to 8 minutes or until
cake springs
back when lightly touched.
Let cool, uncovered,
at least
minutes
before
serving.
Makes
4 servings.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Melt the butter in a 9 x 13 glass baking dish.
Mix in the flour with the butter slowly, then add the sugar then milk.
Once this mixture is blended thoroughly, add the can of peaches.
You can use light if you want to.
Do not drain the syrup.
Cook at 350° for approximately 45 minutes.
Please check it often from 30 minutes on for appropriate doneness as oven temperature may vary.

title: strawberries 'n cream
directions: In a bowl, combine cracker crumbs, 1/4 cup of sugar and the melted butter.
Reserve 1/4 cup of crumb mixture.
Press the remaining crumbs in bottom of 10 x 6 x 2-inch dish.

title: chocolate frosting
directions: Melt butter and cocoa.
Add sugar and bring to a rolling boil. Add milk and whipping cream.
Turn heat to medium-low and cook until thickened.
Stir frequently.
Takes 20 to 30 minutes.

title: low calorie french dressing
directions: Salt and pepper to one's taste.
Combine ingredients; shake well.

title: grandma pat's peach cobbler
directions: Melt butter in baking dish.
Mix together flour, sugar, milk, vanilla and baking powder.
Pour over melted butter.
Spoon peaches over mixture and then pour peach syrup over the top. Sprinkle lightly with cinnamon and additional sugar.
Bake 40 to 50 minutes at 350°.

title: ritz crackers meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients together and form a loaf. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour. Cover last 15 minutes and remove lid and cover with ketchup.

title: beet salad(salata z buraczkow)
directions: Place beets in a large bowl; combine remaining ingredients and toss lightly.
Garnish with walnuts.
Serves 75.

title: chinese chop soy
directions: Place celery in crock-pot; add mushrooms, bean sprouts, water chestnuts and onions.
Brown beef or chicken in skillet.
Add that to the crock-pot with vegetables.
Serve with white rice, noodles or plain.

title: teriyaki
directions: Slice roast into thin strips.
In skillet, brown meat in small amounts of cooking oil.
Put meat in slow cooker with bouillon in 2 cups water and marinade.
Cook on low, 2 hours, or until meat is tender.

title: pickled okra
directions: Wash okra (be sure pods are small), leaving short stems on pods.
Pack in hot, clean jars.
Place one pepper pod and one clove of garlic in each jar.

title: crab meat dip
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serve warm with crackers.

title: dessert supreme
directions: Crumble Oreo cookies; add 1/4 cup melted margarine.
Spread vanilla ice cream on cookies and put in freezer while preparing remaining ingredients.
Beat egg yolks; add melted margarine, powdered sugar, cocoa, vanilla and peanuts.
Beat egg whites until stiff; fold in mixture.
Pour over ice cream and freeze.
Cover with Cool Whip.
Cut in squares to serve.

title: chocolate delight(3 layers)
directions: Mix and pat in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 15 minutes at 350°. Cool.

title: ham 'n broccoli soup
directions: In large saucepan cook onion in diet margarine until tender. Stir in flour, chicken bouillon, mustard, thyme and pepper.
Add milk and water all at once.
Cook and stir over medium heat until thickened.
Stir broccoli and ham into soup.
Bring to boil, then reduce heat and simmer for 6 to 8 minutes, until broccoli is tender.
Serves 2 (313 calories, 25 g protein, 9.8 g fat, 5 mg cholesterol and 591 mg sodium).

title: pink lemonade dessert
directions: Mix together like pie crust.
Pat into bottom of 13 x 9 x 2-inch or pie pan.
Bring amount up on edge by working with fingers to form a crust.
Save small amount to sprinkle on top of filling.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Mix; bring to a boil.
Remove from heat and chill.
Slice 1 pint fresh strawberries into bottom of one baked pie shell.
Pour cooled mixture over them and top with Dream Whip or Cool Whip. Let stand for 2 hours to jell.

title: hot and saucy enchilada casserole
directions: Brown onion in 2 tablespoons oil.
Add beef and brown.
Drain off fat.
(If using chicken, boil until tender, bone and chop in small pieces.
Add browned onion.)

title: choc-oat chip cookies
directions: Beat margarine and sugars until creamy. Add eggs, milk and vanilla. Beat well. Add flour, baking soda and salt. Mix well. Stir in oats, chocolate chips and nuts. Mix well. Drop by rounded tablespoonful onto ungreased cookie sheet. Bake 9 to 10 minutes for chewy, 12 to 13 for crispy cookies. Cool 1 minute on cookie sheet; remove to wire rack. Cool completely.

title: stuffed bread
directions: Chop onion and green pepper; saute in butter.
Add ground beef.
As beef is browning slice the top of the bread off to make a "lid."
Hollow out inside of bread; save in a bowl.
After the ground beef is brown, add 1 can of soup.
Cook until mixed well. Pour mixture into bowl with the bread.
Stir well.
Stuff mixture back into bread.
Wrap in foil.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour.
Cook remaining can of soup as directed.
Pour over sliced Stuffed Bread.

title: chicken gourmet style
directions: Pound chicken flat.
cut into 4 inch pieces.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Saute in small amount of olive oil.
Remove.
In same pan saute onion, add garlic and sauteed chicken.
Add white wine and boil 2 minutes.
Add broth, bouillon cube, artichokes, olives, tomatoes, and spices.
Simmer all for 30 to 45 minutes uncovered.
Sauce will be pink in color.
Serve with broccoli or asparagus.

title: fruit dip
directions: Blend all ingredients together well.

title: potato filling
directions: Cook the potatoes.
Saute the onion and celery in the butter, then combine everything.

title: stay-on batter for fresh vegetables
directions: Beat all ingredients by hand.
Dip floured vegetables in batter.
Fry at 375° in hot oil.

title: hellmann's seven layer salad
directions: In a large bowl, layer lettuce, celery, onion, pepper and peas.
Sprinkle cheese over peas.
Sprinkle bacon over cheese. Spread mayonnaise on salad, completely sealing salad.
Chill.
Can be tossed before serving.
Yields 8 to 10 servings.

title: fruit cake
directions: Chop pecans, candied cherries, pineapple and dates. Add coconut and Eagle Brand milk. Use angel food cake pan or make 1 large cake or can make small cakes or cupcakes. Bake at 300° for 1 hour.

title: quiche
directions: Use 1 deep-dish pie crust, baked but not brown. Put into crust the meat, cheese and onion. Mix eggs, milk, garlic salt, salt and pepper and pour into crust. Bake at 400° for 15 minutes. Reduce to 350° for 15 more minutes or until set.

title: creamed sweet potatoes with marshmallows
directions: Place in a casserole dish and cook until it sets.
Cover with marshmallows and brown lightly.
Add crystallized red cherries between marshmallows.

title: pizza rice casserole
directions: Simmer browned ground beef, tomato sauce, sugar, salt, oregano and parsley flakes.
Mix cooked rice with the cottage cheese.
Put this layer of rice/cheese mixture in greased pan. Cover with thin layer of meat sauce and another thin layer of rice/cheese.
Alternate layers, ending with meat sauce layer.
Top with 1/2 cup grated cheese.
Bake at 325° for about 30 minutes or in microwave on High for 6 minutes.

title: chip and cherry cake
directions: Cream the margarine and sugar together.
Add eggs and beat well.
Add flour, baking powder and salt and beat again.
Then, add dates, cherries, nuts and chocolate bits and mix well.
Put into a tube pan and bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: dilly crackers
directions: Stir everything except crackers.
Put crackers in square dish. Pour the mixture over them.
Shake the container up to make sure every cracker has some mixture on it.

title: dinner in one
directions: Mix together ground beef, eggs, crumbs, salt, pepper and onion. Pack on the bottom of a well greased casserole dish. Pour corn over the meat. Top with a layer of macaroni. Bake in a covered casserole or small roaster in oven at 350 degrees for 45 minutes.

title: ashleigh's delight
directions: Prepare cake as directed on the box.
Let cool.
Cut in half. On both sides, pinch out the very center, about an inch.
Mix the strawberries with the whipped cream and the cake that was pinched out.
Pour the mix into the center, on both sides.
Turn the top over very carefully onto the bottom half.
Pour the remaining mix on top.
Chill.

title: honey orange carrots
directions: In a medium saucepan, combine carrots, honey, orange juice, margarine and nutmeg. Cook over medium-high heat until mixture begins to boil. Reduce heat. Cover and simmer 5 minutes. Uncover and continue cooking until carrots are tender and mixture has thickened. (Takes about 5 to 10 minutes.) Stir in parsley.

title: quick pudding
directions: Sift together the first 4 ingredients.
Add raisins and milk. Mix and place in greased 11 x 7-inch baking dish.
Mix brown sugar and boiling water.
Pour over the mixture.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes in moderate oven. Serve with whipped cream or plain.

title: swedish pancakes
directions: Beat eggs and milk well. Add flour gradually and mix well. Add butter, salt and sugar. Mix well and fry on hot, greased skillet. Pancakes will be thin.

title: strawberry-banana fruit shake
directions: Turn on blender and drop frozen strawberries, one at a time. Next, drop in banana pieces.
Stop blender and scrape with spatula.
Add milk, preserves and sweetener and blend.
Makes 2 (16 oz.) shakes.
Approximately 150 calories.

title: microwave peanut brittle
directions: Use a microwavable glass bowl.
Stir together peanuts, sugar, syrup and salt. Cook in microwave on High 7 to 8 minutes, stirring well after 4 minutes.
Add butter and vanilla to syrup, blending well.
Return to microwave and cook 1 minute more. The peanuts will be lightly brown and the syrup very hot.

Add baking soda and stir gently until light and foamy. Pour and spread mixture quickly onto a lightly greased flexible cooking sheet. Let cool for 1/2 hour. When cool, break into small pieces and store in an airtight container. You can use 1 cup pecans or 1 cup sesame seeds instead of the peanuts.

title: electric skillet beef stew
directions: Combine flour, pepper and 1 teaspoon salt.
Toss meat cubes in mixture until well coated.
Reserve leftover flour mixture. Preheat skillet to 340°; add fat and heat.
Brown meat on all sides.
Reduce temperature to 250°.
Stir in chopped onion, 1 teaspoon salt and reserved flour.
Slowly stir in hot water.
When boiling, reduce temperature to simmer.
Cover with vent closed until meat is almost tender, about 30 minutes.
Add vegetables and more hot water if needed.
Increase temperature to bring to boiling, then reduce again to simmer.
Cook vegetables until tender about 30 minutes.
Makes 4 to 5 servings.

title: shortcut caramels
directions: Line a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan with foil; lightly butter foil.
In a heavy 3-quart pan, melt butter over low heat.
Add sugar, milk and corn syrup; mix well.
Cook over medium heat, stirring often to 248° (firm ball stage).
Mixture should boil at a moderate steady rate over the entire surface, about 15 to 20 minutes.
Remove from heat; immediately add vanilla and walnuts.
Quickly pour into pan. Use a buttered knife to cut into 1-inch squares.
Wrap in waxed paper.

title: lemon chess pie
directions: Thoroughly mix sugar and melted butter.
Add eggs and mix well.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix well.
Pour into 8-inch unbaked pie shell and bake at 300° for 1 hour.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Melt butter, use 1/2 in bottom of 8 x 14-inch casserole pan. Break crackers, layer 1/2 of the crackers in bottom of pan; top with shredded chicken.
Top with mixed cream soups, water chestnuts, peas and sour cream.
Top with remaining crackers (use more if needed).
Top with remaining butter.
Bake at 350° until crackers brown, about 20 to 30 minutes.

title: homemade bread
directions: Mix the first 2 ingredients together.
Add yeast.
Let stand 15 to 20 minutes.
Dissolve sugar in water and add yeast.
Let stand until bubbly (15 to 20 minutes).
Beat eggs; add sugar, salt, oil and water.
Mixture should be slightly warm.
Add yeast and mix thoroughly.
Add flour, 2 to 3 cups at a time, until dough is soft and manageable.
Oil the bottom and sides of a very large bowl or Dutch oven.
Place dough in bowl and turn to coat with oil.
Let stand 2 to 4 hours until doubled in bulk.
Take out, knead and shape into loaves.
Grease loaf pans.
Add dough and cover and let rise again for 40 to 50 minutes.
Bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: no-crust cheese cake
directions: Beat the cream cheese, eggs, 2/3 cup sugar and almond extract together until smooth.
Pour into 9-inch greased pie plate.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: butter crescents
directions: In large bowl, sprinkle yeast and 1 tsp. sugar over warm water; stir until dissolved.
Add milk, salt, egg, 1/2 c. melted butter, 1/4 c. sugar and 2 c. flour.
Using mixer at low speed, beat until well blended.
Increase speed to medium;
beat 2 minutes.
Stir in enough additional flour to make a soft dough. Turn out dough onto lightly floured surface.
Knead until smooth and elastic.
About 5 minutes.
Place in large greased
bowl, turning over dough so that top is greased.
Cover with towel and let rise in warm place until doubled, about 1 hour.
Punch down dough.
Divide dough in half.
Cover and let rest 10 minutes.
On lightly floured surface with floured rolling pin, roll out each half into a 12 inch circle.
Brush both circles with 3 Tbsp. melted butter.
Cut each circle into 12 wedges.
Roll up each wedge, starting at the wide end.
Place rolled wedges, points down, 2 inches apart, on greased large baking sheets.
Curve the ends gently to form crescents.
Brush tops of crescents with extra melted butter.
Cover and let rise until doubled, about 30 minutes.
Bake in 350 degree oven 15 minutes or until crescents are golden brown and sound hollow when tapped.
Immediately remove from baking sheets.
Serve warm.
Makes 24 crescents.

title: onion roasted potatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Place all ingredients in a large bag and shake until potatoes are coated.
Empty into a baking dish. Bake 40 minutes.

title: asparagus roll-ups
directions: Mix softened cheeses and egg together until smooth.
Roll bread thin with rolling pin.
Spread cheese mixture on bread.
Roll up asparagus spears in bread and coat with butter (melted). Refrigerate or freeze.
To serve:
Slice in 1/3-inch rounds.
Bake 15 minutes at 400°.

title: italian pot roast
directions: Place meat in a hot skillet and sear for 1 minute on each side.
Then place meat in a crock-pot.
Put all other ingredients on top of meat.
Cover and cook on high setting for 2 hours, then on low for 6 hours.
If you are in a hurry, cook on high for 4 1/2 hours.
The longer it cooks in the crock-pot the better it is. Serve with mashed potatoes, rice, spaghetti or noodles.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Cook cranberries in water and sugar until all berries are well popped.
Add Jell-O and cut up marshmallows.
When cool, add remaining ingredients.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Cream shortening and sugar, adding sugar slowly and beating until light.
Add unbeaten eggs, one at a time, then mashed bananas.
Next, sift the salt and flour together.
Stir soda in milk.
Add flour and buttermilk mixture.
Bake in tube pan or in 2 (9 x 5 x 3-inch) loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour for tube pan and for 50 minutes for loaf pans.

title: apple nut cake
directions: Beat eggs.
Add oil
and
sugar.
Add
rest of ingredients. Mix well.
Bake in a tube pan at 300° for 1 hour.

title: grandma's raisin pie
directions: Bring water to boiling.
Add raisins and cover; cook 5 minutes.
Mix sugar and flour and stir into raisins.
Lower to medium heat.
Cook, stirring all the time, until mixture boils. Boil 1 minute and remove from heat.
Stir in lemon juice.
Pour into unbaked pie crust and dot with butter.
Add the top crust; crimp the sides and put a slit in top for the steam to be released.
Bake for 30 minutes at 450°.

title: mexican lasagne
directions: Brown hamburger and drain.
Stir in 1/2 cup salsa.
Spread 1/4 cup salsa in bottom of an 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan.
Top with taco shells.
Top with half each of the beans, sour cream, meat and cheese.
Repeat layers.
Cover with foil and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Top with lettuce, olives, remaining salsa and sour cream.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: oasis angel biscuits
directions: Add yeast to 1/2 cup warm milk to dissolve.
Mix all ingredients and roll out as ordinary biscuits.
Dip in butter and bake in a 350° oven until brown (approximately 8 minutes).

title: gloria's horseradish sauce
directions: Whip cream.
Add all other ingredients.
Chill in refrigerator, then serve.
Serves 4.
Great with prime rib or steak!!

title: sweet potatoe pie
directions: Mix well and pour in pie shell. Bake at 350° for 1 hour. Makes 2 pies.

title: sausage macaroni bake
directions: Cook macaroni in boiling salted water until tender, 6 to 8 minutes.

title: cheese biscuits
directions: Mix 2 cups Bisquick with 2/3 cup of milk and 1/2 cup shredded Cheddar cheese.
Mix well.
Drop by spoon on ungreased cookie sheet.
When done (8 to 10 minutes), top with oleo and garlic salt mixture.
Brush on top of biscuits!
And enjoy!

title: baked pork chops
directions: Brown pork chops.
Mix sauce and pour over.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.
Good!

title: coconut cream cheese pound cake
directions: Cream butter, shortening and cream cheese; gradually add sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Combine flour, soda and salt; add to creamed mixture, stirring just until blended.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Pour into greased and floured 10-inch tube pan. Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: split pea soup
directions: Wash and drain split peas.
Combine all ingredients in a kettle with tight fitting lid.
Bring to boil.
Reduce heat and simmer, covered, 2 hours.
Stir occasionally.
Remove bone; cool slightly.
Cut ham off bone and dice.
Add to soup and heat thoroughly.
Remove bay leaf before serving.

title: maple walnut chiffon cake
directions: Pan size:
tube pan.
Mix flour, baking powder and salt.
Stir in with fork the brown sugar.
Make a well and add oil, egg yolks, cold water, maple flavoring and vanilla.
Beat until smooth.
Beat egg whites and cream of tartar until it holds very stiff peaks. Pour first mixture over egg whites in thin stream.
Fold gently; this is very important.
One cup of finely chopped nuts may be added last.
Bake at 325° for 65 to 70 minutes.

title: quiche
directions: Combine all ingredients and pour in pie shell.
Bake 45 minutes at 375°.

title: divinity candy
directions: Cook sugar, water and syrup.
Spin thread.
Pour over egg white.
Beat until it shapes when dropped.
Add 1 1/2 teaspoons vanilla flavoring.

title: deviled almonds
directions: Melt butter in a heavy skillet. Add almonds and saute gently until very light brown.
Place nuts in cake pan and sprinkle with cayenne and salt.
Shake well. Serve hot.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Combine all ingredients
and serve.
Better if made the day before you serve it.

title: mexican chicken
directions: Bake chicken for 1 hour and cut into bite-sized pieces.
Layer in a baking dish, starting with tortillas, then chilies, sauce (made from first 5 ingredients), chicken and ending with cheese. Refrigerate at least 12 hours, 3 days is better.
Can also be made ahead and frozen.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Serves 4.

title: baked beans
directions: Drain all beans.
Mix brown sugar with barbecue sauce.
Chop green pepper and green onions.
Fry bacon; remove and crumble. Brown green pepper and onions in bacon drippings.
Mix soy sauce, liquid smoke and mustard.
Add all ingredients to beans in casserole.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or more.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Saute margarine and onion.
Then mix all ingredients in a casserole.
Bake 30 minutes at 350° or until cheese melts.

title: vanilla ice cream(heritage recipe)
directions: Dissolve junkets in water and set aside.

title: chicken and wild rice
directions: Place chicken in deep kettle.
Add water, sherry, salt and curry powder and onion.
Bring to a boil, cover tightly and reduce heat.
Simmer 1 hour.
Remove from heat.
Strain broth. Refrigerate chicken and broth.
When chicken is cool, remove meat from bone.
Cut into bite-size pieces.
Clean and saute mushrooms until golden brown.
Measure chicken broth.
Use broth as liquid for cooking rice.

title: five bean salad
directions: Drain all beans thoroughly, then add the bell pepper and onion.
Mix together the remaining ingredients; add to beans. Serves 10 to 12.

title: pinto bean pie(tastes like pecan pie)
