directions: Combine and mix all ingredients and pour into an unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix shortening, sugar and eggs.
Mix in soda, salt and flour. Add oats and raisins.
Put on greased cookie sheet and bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: green enchiladas
directions: Mix beef, Cheddar cheese, salt and onion in large bowl and set aside.
In saucepan, mix cream cheese, Velveeta cheese, evaporated milk, green onion dip mix (optional) and chilies (mild).
Heat until melted.

title: fruit squares
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Grease 10 x 15-inch jelly roll pan. In a large bowl, cream together sugar and margarine until well blended. Break eggs into large glass measuring cup. Beat with fork. Add vanilla to eggs. Add egg mixture to margarine and sugar. Beat until well blended. Gradually add flour. Mix thoroughly. Pour batter into greased jelly roll pan. Spread evenly. Cut through batter to make 24 squares. Place 1 heaping teaspoonful of pie filling onto center of each square. Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes until lightly browned.

title: lemon-pineapple jello salad
directions: Beat eggs and sugar.
Add dry Jell-O and pineapple; cook until thickened, stirring constantly.
Cool.
Fold in whipped Pet milk. Pour in pan or baking dish lined with graham crackers or vanilla wafer crumbs.
Sprinkle a few crumbs over the top.
Chill and serve.

title: raspberry fruit jello
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water. Add strawberries. Stir until thawed.
Add bananas and pineapple. Chill until firm.

title: zucchini squares
directions: Mix all together.
Grease 13 x 9-inch pan.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake in 350° oven 25 or 30 minutes.

title: potato (hash brown) casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into baking dish or dishes.
Top with crushed corn flakes and dribble melted butter on top or bake without topping at 350° for 1 hour.
Can be separated and frozen until ready to bake.
Cut to 45 minutes if separated.

title: jello dessert
directions: Cream sugar, egg yolks and butter.
Melt jello in hot water and add to above mixture.
Add pineapple and pecans.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch Pyrex.
Crush vanilla wafers and spread over the top.
Refrigerate.
Serve after it sets up.

title: eggs portugal
directions: Cut crusts from bread and line bottom and sides of Pam sprayed 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Put cheese and sausage on top of bread. Beat eggs, milk and mustard, then add soup and vermouth.
Pour over bread.
Cover with foil and refrigerate overnight.
Bake in 300° to 325° oven about 1 hour until bubbly and brown.

title: french onion soup
directions: Saute onions in butter and oil in a large pot.
Cook over medium heat until onions are soft.
Sprinkle onions with sugar and toss together.
Add stocks and wine, water and beef base.
Stir well and bring to boil.
Add brandy, parsley flakes, garlic powder and pepper to taste.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix cheese, pineapple, pepper, onion, salt and half of the nuts.
Shape into a ball.
Roll into remaining nuts.
Wrap in tinfoil and refrigerate for 24 hours.

title: stuffing
directions: In large skillet, melt butter on medium heat.
Add onions and celery; saute 5 minutes.
Place in large bowl.
Cook sausage until done (10 minutes).
Add to vegetables in bowl.
Stir in stuffing and remaining ingredients, including eggs.
Bake at 350° about 1/2 hour or until all ingredients are thoroughly hot in a baking dish.

title: boiled white potatoes and butter
directions: Peel, wash and cut the potatoes in small quarters.
Add 1 tablespoon of salt.
Cover with water and boil until tender. Add 1/2 stick butter and serve hot.
Serves 6 to 8 people.

title: date nut ice cream pie
directions: To make the crust, combine wafers, nutmeg and margarine.
Press mixture in 9-inch pie pan; chill.

title: swedish nuts
directions: Whip egg whites until stiff.
Gradually add sugar and salt. Add nuts; coat evenly.
Melt butter in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Add mixture and coat well with butter.
Bake at 325°, stirring every 15 minutes, until brown.
Takes approximately 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: better than sex cake
directions: Bake
cake
mix
as directed and cool.	Poke holes with wooden spoon handle.
Combine condensed milk and butterscotch caramel topping;
pour over cake.
Frost with large container Cool	Whip. Crumble
Heath bars over top.
Also could substitute Mrs. Richardson's hot fudge topping.

title: fried bows(easter cookies)
directions: Beat yolks, whole egg and salt together until very stiff, about 10 minutes.
Blend in sugar and flavorings.
Add flour all at once. Mix well.
Knead until blistered about 7 minutes.
Divide in half. Roll out very thin.
Cut dough into 4 x 2-inch diamonds.
Make 1-inch slit in diamond.
Draw point of diamond through slit.
Fry in hot fat until brown.
Turn and fry other side.
Drain on paper. Before serving, sprinkle with confectioners sugar or drizzle with honey.

title: chinese wedding cake
directions: Mix cake as directed at 350° for 15 minutes.
Mix pudding with 2 cups milk.
Add cream cheese; spread on cake.
Drain crushed pineapple and spread over cake.
Put Cool Whip on top.
Chill for 4 hours.

title: caramel frosting
directions: In a saucepan, melt butter.
Add brown sugar; cook over low heat for 2 minutes, stirring constantly.
Add milk and continue cooking until mixture comes to a boil.
Remove from heat. Gradually add powdered sugar and vanilla.
Mix well.
If necessary, thin with a few drops of cream (milk).

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli 3 to 5 minutes in boiling water.
Drain.
Mix with every ingredient except crackers.
Place in small casserole dish.
Top with crackers.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes until set.

title: rice with raisins
directions: Bring water to a boil.
Add all other ingredients. Cover and bring to a boil.
Reduce heat to just boiling and keep covered. Cook slowly for 30 minutes.
Stir.
If not done, cover and cook a few more minutes.
Serves 6 generously.

title: hash brown potatoes
directions: Mix first five ingredients together and pour into a buttered casserole dish.
Sprinkle on top: corn flakes crumbs and melted butter.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: kidney bean casserole
directions: Combine milk, bread crumbs, salt, pepper and chili powder. Add ground beef and mix well.
Make small balls, 1 tablespoon mixture.
Brown meat balls lightly on all sides in oil over medium heat.
Remove and cook onions with 1/2 teaspoon salt until soft. Add tomato sauce and peppers.
Let simmer 8 to 10 minutes.
Stir occasionally.
Drain kidney beans and put in shallow 4-quart casserole.
Cut cheese into 1/2-inch cubes and add to tomato mixture.
Stir well.
Spoon over beans.
Add border of meat balls. Bake in oven at 350° for 40 minutes.
If made ahead and refrigerated, allow one hour.

title: delicious corn bread
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Pour into 8 or 10-inch skillet or 9-inch glass pie pan.
Bake at 450° for 35 minutes or until done. If glass dish is used, may need to bake longer.

title: fruit crisp
directions: Mix the flour and sugar together.
Work in the butter with a pastry blender, fork or fingers until crumbly.
Use one or all of the different kinds of fruit or mix and match.
Spread fruit evenly in a buttered shallow baking pan.
Spread the crumb mixture on top of fruit.
Sprinkle rhubarb and cherries with 1/3 to 1/2 cup sugar.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until fruit is hot. Serve warm.

title: cheesy chicken crescent supper
directions: Preheat oven to 375°. In small bowl combine chicken and 2 Tbsp. cheese. Separate dough into 8 triangles and place about 2 Tbsp. chicken mixture on each and roll up. In medium saucepan, combine soup, milk and 1/4 c. cheese. Heat until cheese melts. Pour soup mixture into 8 or 9 inch baking dish. Arrange rolls over soup. Bake 20 to 25 minutes. Sprinkle remaining cheese on top and return to oven until it melts.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Dissolve the first 4 ingredients.
Add peanuts.
Cook at high heat; stir often.
Cook until peanuts take up all syrup and pop like popcorn.
Take off heat; add soda.
Pour in greased cookie sheet.
Cool and break up.

title: low-fat lasagna
directions: Cook lasagna noodles according to package, but do not add salt.
While noodles cook, preheat oven to 350°.
Spray a 13 x 9-inch baking dish with vegetable spray.
Set aside.
In a small bowl, combine tomato sauce, garlic and oregano.
Mix well.
In medium bowl, combine broccoli, carrot, Ricotta and Parmesan.
Mix well. Drain noodles in colander.
Spread 1/2 cup tomato sauce in bottom of prepared dish.
Place 3 noodles on top of sauce.
Spread half the broccoli mix over the noodles. Spoon 1/2 cup sauce over broccoli.
Place 3 noodles on top. Spread remaining broccoli mix. Top with 1/2 cup tomato sauce.
Top with remaining noodles and sauce.
Sprinkle Mozzarella cheese over top. Bake 45 minutes until bubbly. Cool 15 minutes.

title: cattle clatter hash
directions: Brown meat.
Push to one side and cook onions until limp.
Add chili powder, salt and tomato sauce.
Cover skillet and steam for 20 minutes.
Add cooked and drained macaroni; mix well.
Pour into casserole dish.
Top with cheese and mushroom soup.
Bake at 375° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: spinach pie
directions: Combine spinach, cheese, onion soup, sour cream and egg.
Melt butter; stir in flour, bouillon, milk and cream.
Cook until golden brown.

title: mexican cabbage
directions: Cut cabbage in pieces and cook covered in water until tender (20 to 25 minutes).
Mix chili sauce, onion, garlic and salt.
Fry these in butter until well browned, then add the cabbage with comino seeds and let cook 5 to 6 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: broccoli bake
directions: Cook broccoli.
Melt cheese.
Add soup, milk and garlic.
Put in buttered casserole.
Add bread crumbs and margarine.
Bake at 350° for about a half hour.

title: finnish rieska(flat bread)
directions: Add soda to milk.
Mix dry ingredients first, then work in shortening.
Stir in milk and soda until a soft dough.
Divide in half.
Pat to 1/2-inch thick and bake on cookie sheet in a 400° oven for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: judson's refrigerator rolls
directions: Set oven to 400°.
Mash potatoes, add fat, sugar, salt and eggs; cream.
Dissolve yeast in lukewarm water.
Add to milk.
Add to potato mixture.
Add flour, knead, let rise 5 hours in lightly greased bowl.
Punch down and keep in refrigerator until 1 hour before baking.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes.

title: little smokies
directions: Combine in crock-pot and heat until warm.

title: russian tea
directions: Mix all dry ingredients well.
Use 2 heaping teaspoonfuls of mix per cup of hot water for each serving.

title: bug wash for house plants
directions: Combine.
Store in spray bottle.
Spray plants before bringing into house in the fall.

title: chess pies (2)
directions: Combine
all
ingredients except pie crusts.
Pour this into your half
baked pie crusts and bake at 325° for about 40 to 50 minutes or until golden brown.

title: chicken tortilla casserole
directions: Wrap chicken
breasts
in
foil and bake in a 400° oven for 1 hour
or
until
tender.
Open
foil
and cool.
Remove chicken bones
and
cut
chicken
into
large pieces.
Cut the tortilla into
inch
strips.
Butter
a
13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Put 2 to 3 tablespoons of the juice from the chicken in the bottom of the dish.
Mix soups, milk and onion and add the salsa.
Place
a layer of tortillas on bottom of dish, a layer of chicken
and spoon
salsa
soup
mixture over the chicken. Repeat.
Top
with cheese.
Refrigerate
24 hours.
Next day, bake in a 300° oven for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.
Yields 8 servings.

title: 5-can casserole
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients.
Heat thoroughly.
Serve hot over dry noodles.
Yields 4 servings.

title: apple dip
directions: Mix together all ingredients with a mixer until smooth. Chill and serve with sliced apples or other fruit.

title: saddle venison
directions: Have venison at room temperature.
Rub with garlic.
Amply cover with butter and sprinkle with thyme.
Roast at 450°, uncovered, for 15 minutes.
Rub with more butter.
Roast for an additional 15 minutes at 400°.

title: yokan(sweet bean dessert)
directions: Wash the kanten and tear into small pieces; soak overnight. Add sugar and boil until the kanten is melted.
Turn the heat to medium and add the koshi an and mix well.
Cook over low heat for 45 minutes, stirring constantly.
Pour into a 7 x 11-inch pan or larger and cool.
Do not move the pan while cooling because the yokan will be wrinkled.

title: orange slice candy cake
directions: Cream the butter and sugar together; add eggs, soda and buttermilk mixture.
Mix remaining ingredients with flour and add to creamed mixture.
Stir well.
Pour mixture into a tube pan. Bake at 275° for 2 1/2 to 3 hours.

title: cheesy-chicken soup
directions: Cut up chicken and boil until tender.
Remove skin and bones and chop in bite size pieces.

Replace chicken pieces in the broth. Add the vegetables (canned vegetables, cabbage, onion and mushrooms which have been cooked until tender in a separate pan and drained). Stir in Cheez Whiz and simmer about 15 minutes. Makes about 3 quarts.

title: caramel bars
directions: Line buttered jelly roll pan with whole graham crackers.
Boil brown sugar and butter for 2 minutes.
Take off heat and add nuts. Spread over crackers.
Bake for 10 minutes at 350°.
Spread with chocolate chips and spread.
Cut while warm.

title: gumdrop cake
directions: Cut up the gumdrops; adding half of the flour makes the cutting easier.
Then add the raisins and nuts to same mixture. Cream the shortening, eggs and sugar.
Add a teaspoon of soda, dissolved first in a tablespoon of warm water.
Last, add the applesauce and the remainder of flour to other dry ingredients. Bake about an hour or more, depending
on the size of the pan.

title: sauerkraut salad
directions: Boil vinegar, sugar, salt and sauerkraut juice for 2 minutes. Combine remaining.
Pour hot dressing over mixture; cool. Refrigerate.
Yields 8 servings.

title: turkey ratatouille
directions: Sprinkle turkey with pepper. Heat oil in 12 inch nonstick skillet over medium high heat. Cook turkey in oil 3 to 5 minutes, stirring occasionally, until brown. Stir in stir fry vegetables. Cook 2 minutes, stirring occasionally. Stir in eggplant and zucchini. Cook 2 to 4 minutes, stirring occasionally, until vegetables are tender. Stir in tomatoes; reduce heat to low. Cover and simmer 3 to 5 minutes, stirring occasionally, until sauce is desired consistency. Sprinkle each serving with cheese.

title: spiced tea mix
directions: Mix all ingredients together.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Pat hamburger in bottom of 9 x 12-inch pan.
Sprinkle with salt and half of chopped onion, garlic and grated cheese.
Lay 6 tortillas over meat mixture.
Pour beans over tortillas.
Lay 6 more tortillas over beans.

title: pork chop casserole
directions: Brown chops; set aside.
Combine soup and milk in bowl. Butter casserole dish. Layer potatoes, onion and cheese.
Pour soup over all.
Lay pork chops on top.
Cover and bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Remove cover and bake 15 minutes more.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Brown steak strips, onion and garlic powder together.
Add soup and let simmer.
Cook noodles separately, drain and add to beef mixture.
Before serving, add the sour cream.

title: nutty flavored fruit salad
directions: Drain pineapple, but save one tablespoon.
In large mixing bowl, combine pineapple, carrot, celery, pears and raisins.
In another bowl mix yogurt, peanut butter, ginger and one tablespoon pineapple juice.
Stir yogurt mixture into fruit, making sure to coat all fruit.
Cover and chill.
Makes 6 servings.

title: hush puppies
directions: Sift all dry ingredients together in a bowl.
Add egg and milk.
Stir until well mixed.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Add more milk, if needed.
Drop by small spoonfuls into hot oil.
Fry until golden brown.
Drain on paper towels.

title: easy potato soup
directions: Combine potatoes, onion, chicken broth, and water in Dutch oven.
Bring to a boil.
Cover, reduce heat, and simmer for 30 minutes.
Stir in celery soup, chicken soup, and milk.
Heat thoroughly.
Garnish if desired with shredded cheddar cheese, diced cooked ham, or bacon.
Makes 2 1/2 quarts.

title: frito salad
directions: Mix lettuce, tomatoes, beans, Fritos, cheese and dressing. Toss and serve.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Blend together and pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake about 1 hour at 350°.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Put eggs, oil, zucchini and vanilla in blender; blend until mixed.
Add sugar, flour, cinnamon, salt, soda and baking powder. Mix thoroughly.
Put in 2 greased and floured loaf pans; sprinkle with chopped nuts, sugar and cinnamon.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Grease loaf pans.
Grate the zucchini; set aside.
Stir together the dry ingredients.
Make a well inside and pour in the liquid.
Stir to blend well, then stir in the zucchini and nuts.
Pile into greased loaf pan or mini loaf pans. Bake 1 1/4 hours for loaf, 40 to 50 minutes for smaller loaves depending on size.
Makes 1 large or 2 small loaves.

title: veg-all casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together, except Ritz crackers and oleo. Put in 2-quart casserole dish.
Top with crackers and pour oleo over crackers.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Mix 1st six ingredients.
Stir in potatoes.
Spoon into lightly greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes. Sprinkle with cheese.
Cook 5 minutes.

title: dirt(a delicious, fun dessert!)
directions: You will need 8-inch flowerpot or sand pail (lined with plastic bag), a garden shovel or scoop and silk or plastic flower.

title: fresh strawberry pie
directions: Place strawberries in cool baked pie shell.
In a saucepan stir the remaining ingredients.
Cook until it boils and becomes transparent.
Pour over strawberries.
Cool in refrigerator. Serve topped with whipped cream or Cool Whip.

title: white yeast bread
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients; let cool to lukewarm.
Combine next 3 ingredients and let rise.
Combine the 2 mixtures and add 2 eggs, then add flour, 4 cups with a mixer and 4 cups with hands.
Cover and let stand in refrigerator at least 3 hours.
Remove, punch down and make into 4 equal loaves.
Place in greased pans.
Cover and let rise 2 hours.
Bake 30 minutes at 375°.
Brush with melted butter when done.

title: cake mix cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix 1/2 cake mix, margarine, vanilla and eggs until smooth.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Drop by teaspoonfuls on ungreased cookie sheets.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: bingo salad
directions: Mix together and serve cooled.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients in large bowl.
Sift dry ingredients into another bowl.
Mix the two mixtures together. Add 1 cup walnuts.
Pour into greased tube pan.
Add Topping (recipe follows).
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: peanut butter chews
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Press 1/2-inch thick in pan. Cut into pieces. Chill before serving.
Yields 24 pieces.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Cream the sugar and butter.
Add remaining ingredients.
Pour batter into greased and floured loaf pan. Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes or until done.

title: peach cake
directions: Drain the peaches well.
Arrange peaches on bottom of a well greased 9 x 13 pan.
Set aside.
Prepare cake mix according to package directions.
Spread evenly over peaches.
Sprinkle with cinnamon.

title: yeast bread
directions: Use 1 c warm water and dissolve yeast.
Put rest of water in lg. bowl and add sugar, salt and shortening and then add yeast mixture.
Add flour until you can't mix no more.
Put on floured board or table and knead until not sticky.

title: sausage and cheese balls
directions: Let sausage and cheese soften at room temperature.
Mix Bisquick, cheese and sausage.
Roll into small balls and bake at 325° for about 8 to 10 minutes or until golden brown.

title: stuffed shells or manicotti
directions: Cook pasta as directed.
Mix all ingredients except sauce and reserved cheese.
Stuff shells with mixture and place in baking dish.
Pour sauce over all and top with remaining cheese.
Bake at 375° for 30 - 45 minutes.

title: lou's white texas sheet cake
directions: Bring butter and water to a boil.
Remove from heat and stir in flour, sugar, sour cream, eggs almond extract, salt and baking soda; mix until smooth.
Pour into a greased jelly roll pan.
Bake at 375 degrees for 20 to 22 minutes.
Cool for 20 minutes. Spread frosting on warm cake.

title: corn casserole
directions: Chop onion and saute in 1 stick margarine.
Then mix all ingredients together and put in 2-quart casserole dish.
Top with grated cheese. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until lightly browned.

title: oyster potato cakes
directions: Mix potatoes with egg, green onions, dill, salt and pepper. With lightly floured hands, form into patties.
Place an oyster in middle of each patty and enclose it completely with potato.

title: microwave chocolate pie
directions: Microwave first four ingredients 8 minutes, stirring twice Mixture should thicken. Pour half of thickened mixture into beaten yolks and blend back into other half. Microwave 2-3 more minutes, stirring once. Stir in 2 Tbsp. butter, vanilla, and Choco Bake. Pour into a cooled shell.

title: apple crumb pie
directions: Pare apples and cut in eighths.
Arrange in unbaked shell. Combine 1/2 cup sugar with the cinnamon.
Sprinkle over apples. Combine 1/2 cup sugar with the flour; cut in butter until crumbly. Sprinkle over apples.
Bake at 400° for 40 minutes.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Refrigerate for 1 hour before serving.

title: macy's chocolate chip cookies
directions: Cream oleo, sugars, eggs and vanilla until fluffy.
Use a blender to powder the oatmeal.
Freeze, then grate Hershey bar. Add all other ingredients; mix well.
Roll into "ping-pong" ball size.
Bake at 375° on ungreased cookie sheets for 8 to 10 minutes.
Makes 13 dozen cookies.

title: noodle casserole
directions: Drop noodles into boiling water with 1/2 teaspoon salt and cook for 15 minutes, drain.
Break chili into small pieces, place in a deep pan or skillet and add 2/3 cup water.
Heat and stir until smooth and add 1 can undiluted cream of mushroom soup and 1 small can of mushrooms; heat and stir until well blended.
In a buttered casserole dish, place a layer of noodles, then a layer of chili, topping with the green onions and Parmesan cheese, alternate until dish is filled.
Bake 20 to 30 minutes at 350°.
Serve hot with a green salad.

title: cool cabbage salad
directions: Chop all vegetables.
Combine with vinegar, oil, sugar, salt and pepper.
Toss to coat.
Refrigerate; cover and serve several hours later.

title: peanut butter pizza
directions: Combine sugar, brown sugar, peanut butter, butter, egg and vanilla.
Add flour and beat with electric mixer to form soft dough.
Spread on 12-inch pizza pan.
Sprinkle with chips and marshmallows.
Bake 15 to 18 minutes or until marshmallows are light brown. Bake at 350°.

title: pork chop casserole
directions: Brown pork chops.
While pork chops are browning, microwave hash browns 10 to 13 minutes.
Combine soup, milk, sour cream, dash of salt and pepper.
Stir in hash browns, 1/2 Cheddar cheese and 1/2 French fried onions.
Pour in baking dish.
Put pork chops on top.
Cover.
Bake 40 minutes at 350°.
Take top off.
Put remaining cheese and French fried onions on top.
Bake 5 minutes, uncovered.

title: hungarian layered cabbage
directions: Cook the rice in the salt water.
When it becomes soft, filter and put away.
(In the water you can put a little filed down onion.)

title: eye of round roast
directions: Salt and pepper round.
Chop peppers and onions and add enough ketchup to make a paste.
Cover the roast with the paste.
Place roast in oven at 9:00 A.M. and cook all day, uncovered.
Cook at 250° for the first hour and reduce temperature to 150° to cook for the rest of the day.
Remove from oven at 5 or 6 P.M.
Slice thin to serve.

title: onion rings
directions: Peel onions and slice 1/4 inch thick.
Separate rings and soak in milk for one hour.
Dip into egg, then roll in flour.
Fry in hot oil until light brown (about 2 to 3 minutes), turning once. Drain on absorbent paper.
Sprinkle with salt.
Serve hot.

title: first prize pickles
directions: Pour off all liquid from pickles.
Slice pickles round or long.
Put in a pan.
Add all the other ingredients, mixing well. Let set 2 to 3 days.
Stir occasionally.
Let sugar get all over the pickles.
Pack into hot jars and seal.
Chill in refrigerator before eating.

title: million dollar relish
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients, add salt and let soak overnight. Drain, do not squeeze.
Add vinegar, sugar and spices.
Boil 15 to 20 minutes.
Seal in sterilized jars.

title: old fashion tea cakes
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Knead good; roll out and cut out cookies.
Bake on a cookie sheet.

title: sour cream cheese potatoes
directions: Mix together and put cheese on top.
Bake in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish for 1 1/2 hours at 350°.
tags: cream of mushroom and chicken soup

title: fresh coconut pie
directions: Mix sugar, eggs and butter.
Add milk, flavoring and coconut. Bake in uncooked pie crust at 325°.

title: tom's hot stuff
directions: Mix onions and peppers together in a large mixing bowl, then spoon into jars and add salt.
In a small saucepan mix the vinegar and water and heat. Don't boil.
When the liquid is hot, pour into the jars, making sure the onions and peppers are covered.
Seal and let sit for about a week before using.
It's hot!

title: cabbage dinner
directions: Fry bacon; drain and crumble.
Combine bacon, cabbage, green pepper, onion, celery and salt in a saucepan and heat for 2 to 3 minutes, stirring constantly.
Add tomatoes and mushrooms if desired and continue cooking until mixture is slightly thickened and tender.
Makes 4 servings, 50 calories per serving.

title: turkey chili
directions: In a large skillet, cook turkey and onions about 5 minutes, breaking up clumps; stir in tomatoes, lima beans, corn and water. Simmer 15 to 20 minutes.

title: tostada bake
directions: Combine Bisquick, corn meal, 1/4 c. milk, oil and egg.
Set aside.
Brown meat, onions, taco seasoning, add tomato sauce and stir.
Put Bisquick in pie pan and press to sides.
Cover with meat mixture, beans, and chilies.
Top with cheese and thin salsa.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: sausage casserole
directions: Brown sausage and drain.
Cook rice partly; mix cream of mushroom, cream of chicken and 1 cup water.
Mix everything together; pour in casserole dish and bake at 300° for about 20 minutes.

title: pork chops, applesauce and sauerkraut
directions: Spray a 13 x 9-inch baking pan with a nonstick vegetable coating.
Combine sauerkraut, applesauce and onion; spread evenly over bottom of baking pan.
Dip each chop in milk, then coat with seasoned mix.
Layer on top of sauerkraut mixture.
Bake, uncovered, at 425° until chops are browned and cooked through, about 1 hour.
Makes 8 servings.

title: super spinach casserole
directions: Cook spinach using package directions; drain well.
Combine spinach, margarine, onion dip, salt and pepper in bowl; mix well. Spoon into 1-quart baking dish.
Top with stuffing mix.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until hot and bubbly.
Yield:
6 servings.

title: grilled ranch bread
directions: Combine butter with salad dressing mix.
Slice the bread lengthwise and spread tops with butter mixture.
Place bread under broiler (or cut surface down on grill) until crispy and golden brown.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients. Put in casserole pan. Bake 45 to 60 minutes at 350° until hot.

title: hot mexican bean dip
directions: Combine all ingredients except bacon.
Heat through.
Top with bacon.
Serve with corn chips or potato chips.
Makes 3 cups.

title: witches brew
directions: For each serving, add 1 package instant breakfast to 1 cup of milk.
Stir until there are no bubbles on top.
Add ground cinnamon so it floats on surface.
Add 3 pieces of crushed Pop Tart crunch cereal.
Mix.

title: german potato salad
directions: A.M. or day before:
Boil eggs and cool. Chop onions.
Boil potatoes with jackets in salted water until tender.
Drain and cool.

title: easy potato sausage casserole
directions: In skillet, crumble and brown sausage and onion.
Drain.

title: always pink leg of lamb
directions: Mash garlic with salt, pepper and herb seasonings.
Add oil and vinegar; rub mixture all over lamb.
Place lamb on rack in a roasting pan.
Roast at 350° for 30 minutes.
Lower oven to 200° for 8 hours.
No need to baste.

title: cheese mushroom bread
directions: Slice bread in half lengthwise.
Combine remaining ingredients.
Spread mixture evenly over bread halves.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes or until brown and cheese is melted.

title: easy lasagna
directions: Boil noodles; drain and rinse.
Place in large flat buttered dish.
Mix softened cream cheese, cottage cheese and sour cream. Spread over noodles.
Cook onion and green pepper until tender. Add ground beef, salt and pepper.
Brown lightly, then add tomato sauce and mushrooms.
Spread over cheese.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: frozen strawberry salad
directions: Each member of class brings in 2 pieces of fruit.
Wash fruit and cut into bite-size pieces.
Combine in large bowl and mix gently.
Put in bowls and eat it.

title: spinach balls
directions: Mix all the ingredients.
Refrigerate several hours.
Roll into approximately 1-inch balls.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes on greased cookie sheet.
Good warm or cold!

title: three hole cake
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients and make three holes.
In first hole put vinegar.
In second put vanilla flavoring.
In third put butter.
Add water; mix.
Put in ungreased pan and cook at 325° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: layered salad
directions: In a bowl, layer first 8 ingredients in order given.
Chill for 24 hours.
When ready to serve, salt to taste; toss with parmesan cheese.
Serves 8 to 10.
Must be made a day ahead.

title: prime rib
directions: Select a well-marbled standing rib roast.
Let stand at room temperature for one hour.
Rub roast with salt; sprinkle with pepper.
Place on rack, fat side up, in shallow roasting pan.

title: baked onion rings
directions: Mix egg whites, salt and pepper.
Dip onion rings into mixture, then coat with bread crumbs.
Place in single layer on greased sheet.
Bake for 10 minutes at 450°.
Makes 4 servings.

title: cheesy-ham-potatoes
directions: Cook potatoes; drain.
Mash.
Add cheese, butter, milk, salt, pepper and sour cream.
Mix well.
If too thick, add more milk. Add ham.

title: cornmeal sticks(surullitos de maiz - spanish recipe)
directions: Combine water and salt in a saucepan; heat to boiling.
Remove from heat.
Add cornmeal; mix thoroughly.
Return to cook over moderate heat until mixture separates from bottom and sides of pan.
Remove from heat.
Take mixture by teaspoonfuls and shape into balls.
In the palms of the hands, roll balls to 1/2-inch thickness, in the shape of small cigars.
Deep fry in fat, heated to 375°, until golden brown.
Remove and drain on absorbent paper. Makes 50.

title: pineapple cheese mold
directions: Dissolve gelatin in water.
Stir in remaining ingredients and pour into quart mold.
Chill until firm.

title: ravioli soup
directions: Brown beef and onion in large pot.
Combine remaining ingredients, except pasta and cheese.
Bring soup to a boil. Reduce heat; cover and simmer for 30 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Cook pasta in boiling water for 8 to 10 minutes; drain pasta.
Add to soup; also add Parmesan cheese.
Serve with additional Parmesan.

title: chicken and broccoli casserole
directions: Boil
chicken
breasts until tender.
Let cool.
Remove from bone.
Chop
up
in
a Pyrex dish.
Cool broccoli; drain. Pour on top
of chicken.
Mix cream of chicken soup and mushroom soup with
mayonnaise.
Pour
mixture on top of broccoli (evenly). Spread
cheese on top of mixture.
Put bread pieces on top.
Bake in 375° oven for 20 minutes.

title: hawaiian wedding cake
directions: Prepare and bake cake mix in a 9 x 13-inch pan according to package directions.
Cool slightly.
Poke holes in top of cake with a fork.
Spread with the can of pineapple, juice and all.
In mixer, put cream cheese and pudding together and slowly add milk. Blend slowly until mixture is of smooth consistency.
Spread on top of pineapple.
Spread Cool Whip on top of pudding mixture. Sprinkle on coconut and chill.

title: drop doughnuts
directions: Beat
the
eggs.
Add
the
sugar and shortening.
Sift together the
flour,
salt, nutmeg and baking powder.
Add the milk and
vanilla.	Mix all together.
Drop by small teaspoons into hot
fat
(Use 2 teaspoons, dropping them in hot fat first,
to	allow
the
dough to slide off spoons easier.) Turn to brown
evenly.
Lift out of fat with a slotted spoon. Dust with 10x sugar or glaze.

title: cinnamon biscuits
directions: Mix cinnamon and sugar. Melt oleo. Shape biscuits into balls. Dip in melted oleo and roll into sugar mixture. Put in greased loaf pan. Bake in a 350° oven about 30 minutes. May be glazed with icing.

title: rumaki(do ahead)
directions: Dip liver halves in brown sugar.
Slice water chestnuts in halves.
Hold each piece of liver and chestnut; wrap around with bacon slice.
Secure both ends with toothpick.
If you are not ready to use them, refrigerate up to 1 day.
When ready to cook, place on broiler pan and broil each side until bacon is crisp (15 minutes).
Can prepare 1 day in advance, but cook at last minute. Serves 8.

title: stuffed garden green peppers
directions: Cut tops from peppers.
Remove seed and membrane.
Combine salt, pepper, Worcestershire sauce, rice, egg, 3/4 cup soup, onion and ground beef in bowl; stir lightly.
Pack each pepper with approximately 1/2 cup mixture.
Place filled peppers in round microwave casserole; peppers should fit tightly in casserole. Pour remaining soup over filled peppers.
Cover with plastic wrap.
Microwave on High for 15 to 18 minutes.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Cook macaroni until tender.
Mix egg and milk.
Add a layer of macaroni, then cheese.
Repeat.
Pour egg, milk, salt and pepper over macaroni and cheese.
Slice butter and lay on top.
Bake 45 minutes or until brown.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Press sugar cookie dough into pizza pan or medium-size cookie sheet.
Bake according to package directions until golden brown. Remove from oven and cool.
While cookie is baking, mix softened cream cheese with sugar and vanilla and blend well.
Spread over cooled cookie, leaving 1/2-inch border.
Top with fresh strawberries, kiwi, grapes, blueberries, bananas (dip in lemon juice first), pineapple chunks or any kind of fruit that you like.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Thaw hash brown potatoes and mix all ingredients except the bread crumbs. Put in a 9 x 13 buttered baking dish. Top with bread crumbs. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: In a punch bowl, layer half of pineapple and fruit cocktail, half of pudding, half of cherry pie filling placed around outer edge of bowl and 1 container Cool Whip.
Repeat steps.
Top with remaining Cool Whip, chopped nuts and maraschino cherries. Refrigerate.
Should be made the day you are going to use it. Will not keep.

title: reuben quiche
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Sprinkle caraway seed over pie crust. Prick crust.
Bake for 7 minutes.
Fill pie shell with corned beef. Spread mustard over meat.
Top with sauerkraut and cheese.
Mix together eggs, cream, onion and dry mustard.
Pour into pie shell and bake for 40 minutes.
Let stand 5 minutes before cutting.
Put together in 1 hour.
Makes 8 servings.

title: pork pie
directions: Chop onion fine and saute with butter. In another pan cook pork and hamburger until done. Add spices and onions.

title: mystery pie
directions: Roll crackers with rolling pin until crushed fine. Beat egg whites until stiff. Fold in sugar, salt and baking powder. Add crackers. Blend and add vanilla and nuts. Pour in greased pie pan. Cook about 30 minutes at 350°. Top with Cool Whip and chill.

title: caramel popcorn(microwave)
directions: Mix sugar, syrup, butter and salt.
Boil together 2 minutes. Add 1 teaspoon baking soda and stir (caution: this will cause mixture to double in size and become frothy).
Pour over popped corn in brown grocery sack.
Shake well and microwave 1 1/2 minutes on High.
Shake well again!
Microwave 1 1/2 minutes on High again, watching carefully as it scorches easily.

title: lemon dessert
directions: Mix flour, butter and nuts together.
Spread into a 9 x 13-inch pan by pressing it in pan with fingers.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes or until
lightly brown.

title: refrigerated dessert
directions: In mixing bowl, cut butter into flour until crumbly.
Stir in 3/4 cup peanuts.
Press mixture over bottom of a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Bake in 350° oven for 20 minutes; cool.
In small mixer bowl, beat cream cheese on low speed until fluffy.
Beat in powdered sugar and half of whipped topping.
Spread over crust and chill.
In larger mixing bowl, combine pudding mix and milk.
Beat 2 minutes.
Spoon on top of cream cheese layer.
Chill or freeze until firm, overnight.
Top with remainder of whipped cream (Cool Whip).
Sprinkle with grated chocolate and remainder of peanuts.

title: walnut brittle
directions: Cook without stirring over high heat the sugar and cream of tartar.
Shake pan occasionally until it becomes a syrup-molasses color.
Stir in walnuts and pour onto a well-buttered cookie sheet.
Cool.

title: peanut butter crisscrosses
directions: In a bowl, beat peanut butter, shortening and margarine or butter with an electric mixer on medium to high speed about 30 seconds or until softened.

title: black bean dip
directions: Blend all ingredients together in a food processor or blender. Serve with Tostitos or other chips. Easy and good!

title: cherry delight
directions: Mix all together.
Put in dish and refrigerate.

title: hot sausage balls
directions: Mix all ingredients thoroughly.
Make balls using a teaspoon for measuring and bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: sparklin strawberry pie
directions: Dissolve jello in water.
Add frozen berries and allow to set a few minutes to thicken.
When partially set, spoon into cooked crust.
Top with Cool Whip.
Refrigerate.

title: hot pineapple side dish
directions: Drain the pineapple, reserving 1/4 cup of the liquid.
Set aside.
In a medium bowl, combine sugar and flour.
Add the margarine.
Add 1 cup of cheese.
Mix well.
Gently stir in pineapple.

title: medallions for a king
directions: Trim fat from meat and cut into 1-inch pieces.
In a 1-quart glass saucepan simmer together pepper and vinegar until the solution is reduced by one half.
Combine soup mix, cornstarch and water and blend then add to vinegar mixture.
Bring to a boil, lower heat and cook, stirring, until this thickens.
Remove from heat but keep warm.
Season meat with apple pie spice and celery salt.
Melt butter with onion liquid.
Add meat and cook until golden on both sides.
Stir in jelly and continue cooking.
Pour pepper sauce over meat and serve.

title: cheesy parmesan potatoes
directions: Mix cheese, flour, salt and pepper in large bowl.
Add potatoes and toss until well coated.
In 13 x 9-inch pan, coat bottom with a mixture of oil and margarine.
Add potatoes.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: cake mix rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in water or milk.
Add cake mix and flour. Knead 5 minutes until dough is no longer sticky.
Cover; let rise until double in size, about 45 minutes.
Punch down; shape into rolls.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes.
Can be made into cinnamon rolls and cut out.
Spread with butter, brown sugar, nuts and cinnamon.
Roll up as jelly roll and cut.

title: bobby's cheese cake
directions: Beat cream cheese and sugar together, then add 1 egg at a time and beat, then add vanilla.
Pour in a graham cracker pie crust. Bake at 300° for an hour.

title: small meat balls (swedish)(smakottbullar)
directions: Brown onion in 2 tablespoons butter or margarine until golden. Mix with remaining ingredients until blended.
Use heaping teaspoonful for each meat ball.
Dip hands in cold water and shape into smooth balls.
Saute in browned butter 2 dozen at a time, shaking skillet occasionally to brown evenly.
When all are browned, add small amount of hot water to skillet and loosen drippings.
Return meat balls to skillet and simmer 15 minutes or until done.
Serve as appetizer or main dish.
Makes about 5 dozen.

title: blueberry delight
directions: Split cake into 3 layers.
Place first layer in container**. Mix pudding as directed on box.
Add pudding to sour cream.
Put between layers.
Put pie filling on top of cake.
Refrigerate overnight, if time allows.

title: cherry topped cheesecake pie
directions: Combine crumbs, 3 tablespoons sugar and butter; mix well. Press into bottom and sides of 8-inch pie pan.
Chill for 1 hour. Beat cream cheese with 1/2 cup sugar until creamy.
Blend in whipped topping.
Pour into crust.
Spread pie filling around edge.
Chill at least 3 hours.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: stuffed macaroni
directions: In medium mixing bowl with hands, mix together sausage and ground chuck and stuff into manicotti shells.
Lay in 9 x 13-inch glass baking pan.

title: mayonnaise cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together and bake at 350 F for 30 minutes.

title: gluten free cornbread
directions: Mix ingredients together and bake in a greased muffin pan at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes until golden brown.
Makes 10 to 12 muffins.
These freeze well.

title: chicken stroganoff
directions: In large skillet, heat oil over medium heat; add chicken, garlic and onions.
Cook 2 to 3 minutes, stirring until chicken is white and onions are soft.
Stir in broccoli, soup and mustard. Cover and cook 4 to 5 minutes until heated through.
Remove from heat; stir in sour cream.
Serve over hot noodles.
tags: cream of chicken and broccoli soup

title: teriyaki steak
directions: Peel and chop ginger root.
Chop dried garlic.
Combine first 4 ingredients into baggie.
Add meat to baggie.
Force air out of bag and twist tie the top.
Marinate for up to 3 days, turning a couple of times a day.
Broil meat or cook on the grill.

title: chocolate drop cookies
directions: Mix and roll 1 teaspoon of mix in powdered sugar. Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: strawberry delight
directions: Dissolve jello in water.
Add fruit and nuts.
Pour 1/2 of mixture in dish.
Chill until slightly set.
Spread 1 cup of sour cream on first layer.
Pour on remaining jello and chill until firm.
May top with Cool Whip, if desired.

title: shortcake recipe
directions: Mix and stir 22 seconds.
Bake at 350° in greased 8-inch pan until golden brown.
Cool.
Add fresh strawberries.
Top with milk or whipped cream.

title: marinated london broil
directions: Mix all sauce ingredients.
Marinate meat overnight, covered, in refrigerator.
Turn in the morning.
Broil meat.
Spoon marinade over meat while broiling.
This marinade also excellent for small chicken parts to be barbecued.

title: spiced watermelon rind
directions: Let watermelon stand in salted water overnight.
Add 2 tablespoons of pickling salt to 1 quart of water.
Make sure to cover all melon cubes with this solution.
In the morning drain. Cover with fresh water in a large pot and cook until tender. Drain.

title: asparagus quiche
directions: Place pie shell in freezer for 15 minutes.
Reserve 8 spears of asparagus for garnish.
Chop remaining asparagus and add to egg mixture.
Mix all ingredients together well and pour into chilled pie shell.
Arrange asparagus spears "spoke-fashion" on top, tips in center, and bake in preheated 375°
oven for 35 minutes or until knife inserted in center comes out clean.
Let cool 10 minutes before cutting to serve.

title: nut milk
directions: Blend nuts and hot water until smooth.
Add remaining ingredients and blend again.

title: puff shells
directions: In medium saucepan, heat water and margarine until margarine melts and water boils.
Remove from heat.
Immediately add 1 cup flour and stir with a wooden spoon until the mixture leaves sides of the pan.
Cool for 5 minutes.
With wooden spoon, beat in eggs, one at a time, until each is thoroughly blended into the mixture.
Place mixture in a large bowl and repeat entire process for another batch.
Add all batches together.
Let cool at room temperature for about 30 minutes.
Preheat oven to 375°.
Grease a baking sheet.
Drop mixture into mounds of desired size onto sheet.
Bake until lightly browned and fluffy.
Adjust time to your own oven.
Fill with chicken salad or any filling you prefer.

title: taco pie
directions: Cook ground beef and onion; drain well.
Add taco seasoning mix and water; stir well.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat; cook 20 minutes.

title: angel refrigerator biscuits
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Sift dry ingredients 2 times. Cut in shortening until the size of crumbs.
Add buttermilk and yeast mixture to flour mixture and stir only until well moistened. Cover and put in refrigerator.
As needed, use part of dough, roll and cut out biscuits; let stand in pan about 15 minutes, then bake at 400° for 10 or 12 minutes or until done.
May be kept in refrigerator for one week and used as needed.

title: foolproof chocolate fudge
directions: In heavy pan over low heat, melt chocolate chips with milk. Remove from heat; stir in remaining ingredients.
Spread evenly into wax paper lined 8-inch square pan.
Chill 2 to 3 hours, until firm.
Turn fudge onto cutting board, peel off paper and cut into squares.

title: louisiana boiled shrimp
directions: In a large pot, add water, lemon, onion, crab boil and salt. Bring to a rolling boil.
Add shrimp.
Return to boil quickly. When rolling boil returns, time for 5 minutes.
Remove from heat, allowing to stand 10 to 15 minutes.
Drain shrimp and serve.

title: double chocolate brownies
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
In a small bowl, combine flour, baking soda and salt; set aside.
In a small saucepan, combine butter, sugar and water.
Bring just to a boil.
Remove from heat and add 6 ounces (1 cup) chocolate chips and vanilla.
Stir until chocolate chips melt and mixture is smooth.
Transfer to large bowl.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition. Blend in flour mixture.
Stir in remaining chocolate chips and nuts.
Spread into a baking dish and bake at 325° for 30 minutes. Cool.

title: breadsticks
directions: Heat oven to 450°. Melt butter in oven in a 9 x 13 pan. Remove as soon as melted. Sift dry ingredients into bowl. Add milk. Stir with a fork until dough clumps together. Turn on floured board and knead 10 times. Roll out 1/2 inch think into 12 x 8 inch rectangle. Cut in half lengthwise, then crosswise into 16 strips. Dip each strip in butter and coat on both sides. Lay close together in pan. Bake 15-20 minutes in 425° oven. Serve hot.

title: carrot custard pie
directions: Drain carrots.
Put through a sieve or food mill.
There should be one generous cup.
Combine with sugar, salt and spices. Add beaten eggs, milk and butter.
Pour into pie shell and bake at 400° for 45 minutes or until set.

title: lemon fluff
directions: Crust:
Mix oleo, flour and nuts until crumbly.
Press into 9 x 12-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Cool.

title: squash bread
directions: Sift first three ingredients together and stir in beaten egg. Add water or milk to make a soft dough.
Round up on lightly floured cloth or board.
Knead lightly.
Roll or pat out 1/2-inch thick.
Cut into strips about 2 x 3-inches.
Slit the center of dough.
Drop in deep fat; brown on one side, then turn over and brown the other.
Serve with pinto beans, stew or syrup.

title: chocolate fudge
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients in a heavy saucepan.
Stir while boiling to soft ball stage (235°), about 20 minutes.
Remove from heat and add remaining ingredients.
Stir until chips are melted. Pour into 9 x 3-inch greased pan.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Boil chicken until tender; debone and chop up.
Save broth to cook spaghetti in.
Before cooking spaghetti, skim off enough fat from broth to saute onions, celery and bell pepper; cook until clear.
Add tomatoes, olives and mushrooms.
Simmer approximately 1 hour.
Add seasoning to taste.
Cook spaghetti and drain.
Mix cooked spaghetti, chicken and sauce.
Place into casserole dishes and layer with shredded cheese, topping off with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes, until cheese is melted and it is hot in the middle.
If recipe is tripled, etc., baking time will increase and larger pans are needed.

title: tomato salad
directions: In saucepan over low heat, combine cream cheese and soup. Dissolve gelatin in cold water.
Add to soup mixture.
Mix well and let cool.
Add mayonnaise, vegetables, (optional pecans and shrimp) and pour into 2 quart mold and chill.

title: chocolate cake
directions: Put in a bowl as given. Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour.

title: grandma's chicken
directions: Melt butter and next 7 ingredients in saucepan.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Skin chicken and sprinkle with salt, pepper and paprika. Pour sauce over chicken and cover pan with foil.
Cook 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Last 20 minutes in oven, take off foil so chicken can brown.
Serve with rice.

title: mud cookies
directions: Mix together in a large bowl oatmeal, peanut butter and vanilla.
Bring sugar, butter, cocoa and milk to a full boil and boil 1 minute.
Pour liquid into oatmeal mixture and mix well. Immediately drop by teaspoonfuls on wax paper.

title: apricot nectarine cake
directions: Mix together first 5 ingredients and pour in Bundt cake pan. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: pat's blueberry muffins
directions: In a large bowl, combine flour, sugar, baking powder and salt.
Add blueberries.
In another bowl, beat egg and milk; stir in margarine.
Stir into dry ingredients just until moistened. Fill greased muffin cups two-thirds full.
Bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes or until muffins test done.
Yield: 1 dozen.

title: mother's custard
directions: Warm milk to scalding.
Beat eggs.
Add sugar, cornstarch and salt. Stir in half of the warmed milk.
Pour the egg and milk mixture into remaining milk and cook, stirring constantly, until thickened.
Remove from heat and stir in vanilla.

title: tomato dumplings
directions: Boil tomatoes in medium saucepan for 10 minutes.
Use no water. Stir in sugar, salt, butter and nutmeg.
Break biscuits apart and drop in tomato mixture.
Simmer on low heat for about 5 minutes.

Serve while hot. This is and old country recipe.	We always had tomato dumplings when tomatoes were ripe and in abundance.	Brown-'n'- Serve rolls can be used instead of biscuits. Tomato dumplings should pass the taste test.
Sweeten and season to suit your own taste.	My mother would explain that this is one of those "pinch of this and dash of that" recipes.

title: tomato casserole
directions: Combine tomatoes, onion, butter, bacon drippings, sugar, seasoned salt and garlic salt in bowl; mix well.
Layer half the stuffing mix, tomato mixture, cheese, oregano and remaining stuffing mix in greased baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. May substitute oil for bacon drippings.
Yield:
6 servings.

title: japanese fruit pie
directions: Melt oleo and let cool.
Add other ingredients and mix together.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 325° for about 40 minutes, until jellied together.

title: homemade applesauce
directions: Cut apples into quarters.
Peel apple pieces.
Put apples and water into a pot.
Set on stove over low heat.
Cover and cook gently for about 15 minutes or until they are soft.
Add the honey or sugar while they are hot.
Mash apples with a wooden spoon until desired consistency.
You can add cinnamon (optional). Serve hot or cold.

title: chops baked-in-soup
directions: Rub chops with salt and pepper.
Melt butter in skillet; add onions and chops; brown lightly on both sides.
Put sliced potatoes in buttered 2-quart baking dish.
Arrange chops over potatoes.
Add soup and milk to onions in skillet.
Blend until smooth.
Poor over chops.
Cover.
Bake in 350° oven for 30 minutes.
Uncover; continue baking for 30-40 minutes, until potatoes are done.
Makes 6 servings.

title: sausage spaghetti
directions: Slice links. In skillet, lightly saute links with pepper, mushrooms and onions.
Stir in spaghetti sauce.
Simmer, uncovered, for 10 minutes, stirring occasionally. Serve over hot cooked spaghetti.

title: layered casserole
directions: Saute beef and onion until well done.
Drain.
Place meat mixture in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
This is your first layer. Pour can of peas over top of meat.
Over top of peas, pour can of mushroom soup.
On top of soup, put entire box of Tater Tots.
Bake at 425° for 30 minutes.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix together corn, whipping cream, milk and salt.
Then add cayenne pepper and sugar.
Bring all to boil.
Then, add flour and butter.
Put in baking dish and bake at 350° until top is brown (don't let it dry).

title: wild plum tea
directions: In a 1-gallon pitcher, steep tea bags and 1 quart of hot water. Mix the remaining quart of water and sugar; heat over high heat until sugar is dissolved. Pour over tea and water in pitcher. Steep 15 minutes. Strain out tea bags; add orange juice and lemon juice and enough water to make 1 gallon.

title: heavenly delight
directions: Melt oleo.
Add the cocoa.
Beat eggs.
Add sugar and mix with cocoa mixture.
Stir in flour, nuts and vanilla.
Bake in a 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan at 350° for 30 minutes.
Do not overcook.
When done, cover top of cake with a large package of tiny marshmallows.
Put back in oven for 1 minute to soften marshmallows.
Cover with icing.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Mix flour and Crisco; add remaining ingredients and mix well. Cover and put in refrigerator to chill.
Take out amount needed for meal.
Roll, cut and bake in a 450° oven until brown.
Will keep indefinitely in refrigerator if covered well.

title: snowball cookies(pecan balls)
directions: In large bowl, combine all ingredients (except confectioners sugar).
Mix by hand.
Refrigerate 30 minutes.
Preheat oven to 375°.
Form into 1 1/4-inch balls.
Place 1 inch apart on ungreased cookie sheets.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes or until set, but not brown.
Let stand 1 minute.
Remove to wire rack to partially cool.
Roll in confectioners sugar while warm.
Cool completely. Before serving, re-roll in powdered sugar.
Yield:

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Melt butter; add onion and simmer over medium heat for 3 minutes.
Stir in remaining ingredients and simmer until sauce thickens, about 30 minutes.
Yields 2 cups sauce.

title: sauerkraut salad
directions: Mix sugar, oil and vinegar.
Pour over remaining ingredients. Mix well and let stand for several hours before serving.

title: fudge ribbon cake
directions: In small bowl cream 2 tablespoons butter with cream cheese, 1/4 cup sugar and cornstarch.
Add 1 egg, 2 tablespoons milk and 1/2 teaspoon vanilla. Beat at high speed until smooth and creamy; set aside.

title: hot punch
directions: Put in a party perk and serve hot.

title: pumpkin cake
directions: Mix well first 4 ingredients.
Beat eggs, sugar and oil well. Add dry ingredients, then add pumpkin.
Beat again.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour in 11 x 13-inch pan.

title: meatballs
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Bake for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: fresh cucumber slices
directions: Place the cucumbers and onions in large bowl and sprinkle with salt and celery seed.
Mix well and let stand 10 minutes.
Do not drain.
Stir together 1 cup vinegar and 2 cups sugar.
Pour over pickles and stir frequently for most of the day. Refrigerate.
Eat right out of bowl.
Can also be frozen.
Makes about 1 1/2 quarts.

title: kid's cookies
directions: *Do not substitute, butter only.

title: pancakes
directions: Blend dry ingredients.
Mix in other items.
Fry over medium heat.

title: sachertorte cookies
directions: In a large bowl, cream the butter and pudding until light and fluffy.
Beat in the egg.
Gradually add the flour until dough forms.
Shape dough into 1-inch balls.
Roll the balls in the sugar and place 2 inches apart on ungreased cookie sheets.
Make an imprint in the center of each ball with your thumb. Bake at 325° for 15 to 18 minutes or until firm.
Immediately remove from the cookie sheet.
Cool.
Fill each imprint with a half teaspoon of preserves.
In a small saucepan, blend the chocolate chips with the melted butter.
Stir over low heat until chocolate melts. Drizzle a half a teaspoon over each cookie.
Makes 48 cookies.

title: breakfast pizza
directions: Cook sausage until browned; drain.
Set aside.
Separate crescent roll dough into 8 triangles.
Place triangles with elongated points toward center in a greased 12-inch pizza pan. Press bottom and sides to form a crust; seal perforations.
Spoon sausage over dough.
Sprinkle with hash browns and cheese.
Combine eggs, milk, salt and pepper.
Pour over sausage mixture.
Bake at 375° for 25 minutes.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Bake an additional 5 minutes.
Garnish with pimento and oregano, if desired.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: bran flake muffins
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Mix flour, brown sugar, baking soda, cinnamon and salt in large bowl.
Beat egg whites in a small bowl and stir in milk and oil.
Add to the flour mixture.
Stir until mixed (batter will be lumpy).
Stir in cereal and raisins.
Spoon batter into greased muffin pan, filling each cup 2/3 full.
Bake 20 minutes or until golden brown.
Serve warm.

title: pickled green tomatoes
directions: Bring to a boil sugar, vinegar and salt.
Boil 1 minute.
Put cut up green tomatoes, sliced onion and garlic in quart jar. Cover with boiling mixture of vinegar and let stand 3 days before eating.

title: 7 layer bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Melt butter in 9 x 13-inch pan. Sprinkle graham crackers over butter, sprinkle coconut, then chocolate chips, then butterscotch chips then walnuts.
Pour condensed milk over all.
Bake 20 to 30 minutes.

title: garlic-roasted veggies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Cut each eggplant lengthwise into 8 strips; place, skin side down, on roasting pan.
Cut zucchini and squash into 3 pieces.
Place on second baking sheet.
Cut peppers in half and seed them.
Place them, cut side down, on the baking sheet with the zucchini and squash.

title: camp stew
directions: Brown ground beef and drain off grease. Add pork and beans, ketchup and onions. Simmer for 30 minutes. Serve with toasted cheese sandwiches.

title: merican fruit cake
directions: Mix together
well and put in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Frost.

title: wacky cake
directions: Sift together the flour, sugar, cocoa, soda and salt in ungreased 8 x 8-inch pan.
Make 3 wells in dry mixture.
In one well add 1 tablespoon vinegar, in another add 1 teaspoon vanilla and in other 6 tablespoons vegetable oil.
Pour 1 cup cold water over all the ingredients and mix with fork until mixture is wet. Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: pink salad
directions: Whip Eagle Brand milk and Cool Whip well.
Add other ingredients and stir well.
Makes 10 to 12 servings and keeps well in refrigerator.

title: beef teriyaki and rice
directions: Mix soy sauce, sherry, brown sugar and seasonings.
Add beef; let stand 10 minutes to marinate.
Stir-fry beef in hot oil in skillet until browned.
Add vegetables and stir-fry until tender and crisp.
Mix broth and cornstarch; add to skillet.
Bring to boil
1 minute.
Prepare rice as directed.
Serve beef mixture over rice.
This recipe will serve 5 people.

title: cherry pound cake
directions: Cream shortening and sugar. Add eggs, one at a time. Mix well. Add flavoring and cherries. Add milk and flour alternately. Place cake in cold oven. Bake at 300° for 1 hour and 45 minutes. Cool in pan 15 minutes before removing from pan.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix
all ingredients together.
Bake in buttered baking dish at 375° for approximately 50 minutes to 1 hour.

title: butterfinger fudge
directions: Combine sugar, milk and butter and boil for about 3 minutes. Stir occasionally.
Remove from heat.
Add peanut butter and marshmallow cream and stir until blended.
Pour into a buttered 8 x 8-inch pan.
Cut into squares.
Makes 16 pieces.

title: cheery cherry cheese pie
directions: In a medium bowl, beat cheese until fluffy.
Add milk and blend thoroughly.
Stir in lemon juice and vanilla.
Pour cheese mixture into a prepared graham cracker crust.
Chill 3 hours or until set. Top with desired amount of pie filling before serving.
Refrigerate leftovers.

title: chicken noodle soup
directions: Heat all ingredients except noodles until boiling; reduce heat. Cover and simmer until chicken is done, about 45 minutes.
Skim fat if needed.

title: strawberry creme cake
directions: Mix cake according to directions and bake in two layers. Cool.
Put into freezer until very cold and split layers in half.

title: pig lickin' cake
directions: Mix and bake at 350° until done.
Let cool completely.

title: nectar cake
directions: Combine and mix according to instructions on cake mix.
Bake in greased and floured tube pan at 325° for 1 1/4 hours.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: In casserole dish, combine broccoli, soup, milk, onion and cheese.
Crush one tube Ritz crackers and sprinkle on top.
Place 3 to 4 pats of butter on top of crackers.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: aunt deenie's strawberry punch
directions: Boil 4 cups water and 4 cups sugar until dissolved.
In large container, put strawberry and mixed fruit jello.
Add 9 cups cold water; mix.
Pour into hot sugar water.
Add lemon juice and pineapple juice.
Pour into 16 ounce containers and freeze.
When ready to use, take out of freezer and let thaw until you can break it up with spoon.
Put in punch bowl.
Add 7-Up.
Serves 100.

title: pepper jelly
directions: Put all ingredients in blender, except Certo.
Blend.
Strain. Add sugar; mix well.
Bring to a hard boil.
Boil 2 to 3 minutes. Remove from heat.
Add Certo and red or green food coloring.
Skim and put into jars.
Makes six half-pints.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Beat the first 7 ingredients well with a mixer until blended and then with a large spoon. Add apples, raisins and nuts.
Pour into a well-greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan or tube pan. Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes in the 9 x 13-inch pan or 45 minutes to 1 hour in a tube pan.

title: peanut butter spread
directions: In a medium bowl, combine all ingredients.
Then spread on bread or toast.

title: spaghetti cake
directions: Cook spaghetti and drain.
Add eggs, Parmesan cheese and melted butter.
Pat into a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: chicken supreme
directions: Boil chicken breasts until tender (reserve the liquid). Remove chicken from bone and cut into 1-inch cubes.
Place chicken chunks in greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Mix mushroom soup and sour cream together and spread over chicken chunks.
Mix stuffing and melted margarine together and spread over sour cream and soup mixture.
Measure 2 cups of reserved chicken broth and drizzle over stuffing.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes, 20 minutes covered and uncovered the last 20 minutes.

title: cheesecake
directions: Melt margarine and pour into graham cracker crumbs.
Add 1/2 cup sugar.
Press into the bottom of a 10-inch spring-form pan firmly.
Bake 5 minutes at 350°.

title: red chocolate cake
directions: Cream together sugar and shortening; add eggs and mix well. In another bowl mix vinegar and soda.
Pour milk into vinegar mixture and add to sugar and shortening mixture.
Sift together flour, salt and cocoa and add to the mixture.
Beat well; add boiling water, stirring constantly.
When well mixed, add vanilla. Pour into a greased 9 x 13-inch pan or 2 (9-inch) round pans. Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: 50th anniversary punch
directions: Mix orange juice, Hi-C, lemonade and 2 lemonade cans of water. Chill thoroughly.
Add ginger ale when ready to serve.
Add sherbet. Stir lightly and serve.
Makes 20 servings.

title: lazy cobbler
directions: Pour melted oleo into a 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Mix sugar, flour, milk, salt and baking powder; pour over melted butter.
Add blueberries; do not drain.
Sprinkle 1/2 cup sugar over top.
Bake at 350°.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Cream sugar and Crisco well.
Add 2 eggs; beat well.
Add buttermilk and soda.
Add flour, one cup at a time, with baking powder, salt and vanilla.
Drop from spoon.
Dip bottom of glass (use glass with flat bottom) in sugar and cinnamon; flatten cookies.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes.

title: fresh fruit dip
directions: Mix together on low speed with electric mixer.
Great with all fresh fruits.

title: butter cookies
directions: Mix butter, sugar and eggs; then add flour vanilla and baking powder. Mix well. Divide dough in half. Chill for 3 hours. Roll out and cut; then bake at 350° for about 9 minutes.

title: skroodles vegetable salad
directions: Mix thoroughly all of the above.

title: butterscotch cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add eggs, vanilla and sour cream, then dry ingredients, nuts and bits last.
Bake 10 minutes at 400°, then frost with Caramel Icing.

title: mexican chicken
directions: Skin, debone and chop chicken.
Heat both soups, broth and Rotel over medium heat until hot.
Break enough chips to cover the bottom of a 9 x 13 inch Pyrex dish.
Add chicken then pour soup mixture over it.
Top with cheese and bake at 350° until melted.

title: chocolate chess pie 1
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients together.
Add remaining ingredients. Preheat oven to 400°.
Pour in unbaked crust and bake 45 minutes at 325°.

title: mexican manicotti
directions: Combine cooked and seasoned (with salt and pepper) hamburger, beans, oregano and cumin.
Mix well.
Fill uncooked shells with meat mixture.
Arrange in large 8 1/2 x 11-inch baking dish. Combine water and picante sauce.
Pour over shells.
Cover with vented plastic wrap.
Microwave for 10 minutes, giving dish a 1/2 turn once.
Using tongs, turn shells over.
Microwave, covered, 17 to 19 minutes, until shells are tender.
Top with cheese and melt. Spoon sour cream down middle.
Sprinkle green onions on top of sour cream.

title: zucchini chocolate cake
directions: Mix all but zucchini.
Add last.
Put in a 13 x 9-inch floured baking pan.
Sprinkle with 12 ounces chocolate chips.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: lemon-orange cake
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients in a large bowl; add 1 cup water. Blend, then beat 4 minutes at medium speed.
Pour into a greased Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Combine remaining ingredients for glaze.
Punch holes in cake with fork while hot; pour glaze over top.

title: all night chocolate chip cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Beat egg whites until they hold peaks. Add sugar gradually, then vanilla.
Beat until very stiff.
Fold in chocolate chips.
Drop by teaspoon on ungreased cookie sheet. Put in oven, close door and turn oven off.
Leave in oven overnight.

title: cream cheese chocolate chip cookies
directions: Cream sugar, butter and cream cheese until light and fluffy; blend in egg and vanilla.
Add combined dry ingredients;
mix well.
Stir in chocolate pieces and nuts.
Drop by rounded teaspoonsfuls onto greased baking sheet.
Bake at 375° for 12 minutes.
Makes approximately 5 dozen

title: garlic chicken with gravy
directions: Coat chicken with garlic powder.
Put chicken, gravy and any vegetables (carrots, celery, potatoes, etc.) into Reynolds cooking bag.
Cook at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: coffee cake
directions: Mix and sprinkle over top.
Bake in oven at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: beer bread
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients.
Pour into greased loaf pan.
Set aside 30 minutes.
Heat oven to 350°.
Pour melted margarine over top.
Bake 1 hour.
Allow to cool 10 to 15 minutes.
Remove from pan.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix all the ingredients together well. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: jalapeno potato casserole
directions: Slice potatoes and layer in casserole dish.
Put layer of potatoes, chopped bell pepper and pimentos.
In saucepan, melt butter.
Add flour, then gradually add milk.
Chop up cheese in hot sauce and pour the beaten sauce over potatoes.
Bake in oven for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: red rice
directions: Melt margarine in a 1 1/2-quart saucepan.
Cook onion and green pepper in margarine until tender.
Stir in rice; add remaining ingredients and blend lightly.
Cover and bring to a boil, reduce heat and cook over low heat until rice is tender and all liquid is absorbed.
Yields 4 servings.

title: sombrero dip
directions: Brown the ground round, onion and bell pepper.
Add salsa, chili powder, ketchup and salt.
Add kidney beans and cheese. Heat at 350° for 20 minutes, or until bubbly.
Makes 4 cups.

title: ham casserole
directions: Put a little bit of tomatoes on the bottom of your pan.
Then put ham, cheese, salt, pepper and butter.
Repeat process until you run out of stuff.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: smoked sausages and pineapple
directions: Saute sausages until brown and remove to chafing dish or warmer.
Drain pineapple, reserving 3/4 cup juice.
Add pineapple to sausages with the juice and heat through.
Serve with toothpicks.

title: fresh spinach and strawberry salad
directions: In bowl, combine spinach, strawberries and green onions. Cover; chill up to 2 hours.
For citrus dressing, combine salad oil and lemon juice; mix well.
Pour over spinach strawberry mixture.
Top with walnuts and, if desired, sprinkle with toasted sesame seed.
Use serving fork to toss lightly to coat.
Serve immediately.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: pizza pork hoagies
directions: Place pork strips and dressing into a self-sealing plastic bag.
Marinate in refrigerator 2 to 24 hours.
Drain marinade and discard.
Heat a large non-stick skillet over medium heat; add pork strips and stir until just done and lightly browned - six to eight minutes.
Open sandwich buns, place on cookie sheet.
Spread 1/2 Tbsp. pizza sauce over bottom halves of buns.
Divide pork strips into six equal parts and place atop the sauce.
Top each with 1 1/2 Tbsp. cheese.

title: sweet bars
directions: Melt in oblong cake pan the butter or margarine.
Add in layers the graham cracker crumbs, chocolate bits and coconut. Pour sweetened condensed milk over this.
Bake at 325° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: dinner rolls
directions: In a large bowl, mix 3 cups flour and yeast. Scald milk.
To milk, add the margarine, salt and sugar. Cool to about 130°.
Add liquid
to flour-yeast mixture.
Mix well.
Add eggs.
Mix in enough flour to make a soft dough.
Knead 8 minutes.
Place in greased bowl and cover with plastic wrap.
Let rise until double. Shape and let rise until double.
Bake at 375°.

title: crunchy salad
directions: Combine and mix sugar, oil, salad vinegar, soy sauce and seasoning packet until sugar is dissolved.
Set aside.

title: apple salad
directions: Combine flour, sugar, pineapple juice, egg and vinegar in saucepan.
Stir over medium heat until it thickens.
Takes awhile. Cool overnight.
Cube apples.
Add pineapple and mix together. Combine sauce mix and Cool Whip.
Fold into apple mixture.
Add nuts just before serving.

title: chicken salad vinaigrette with tarragon
directions: Marinate chicken and vegetables in dressing for 4 to 6 hours. Serve over shredded lettuce.

title: christmas wassail
directions: Combine all ingredients in a crock-pot or slow cooker.
If desired, tie whole spices in cheesecloth or place in a tea strainer.
Cover and set on high for 1 hour, then on low for 4 to 8 hours.
Serve warm.
To spike, add 1 cup rum.
Makes 12 cups.

title: baked beans with kielbasa
directions: Mix together all ingredients, except kielbasa.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour.
Arrange kielbasa over the top and bake for 10 more minutes.

title: cheese bread
directions: Stir cheese in milk until completely melted.
Cool.
Dissolve sugar, salt and yeast in water.
Combine.
Add 1/2 the flour and beat, add remainder of flour.
Brush with shortening and let rise until double.
Divide into 2 parts, knead lightly and place in pans.
Let rise until double.
This makes 2 loaves.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: squash casserole
directions: Boil squash and onion for 5 minutes and drain.
Combine soup and sour cream.
Stir in carrots.
Fold in squash and onion. Combine stuffing and margarine.
Put 1/2 stuffing in bottom; spoon in squash mixture and top with rest of stuffing.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: caramels
directions: Cook on medium heat to 245° on a candy thermometer stirring occasionally (takes about 45 minutes).
Take from heat and add 1 teaspoon vanilla.
Put in a square 8 x 8-inch Tupperware pan. When completely cooled, remove from pan.
Cut into small pieces and wrap in wax paper.

title: chicken and mushroom fettuccine
directions: Heat butter in a large skillet.
Add chicken and saute until edges are golden, about 5 minutes.
Add mushrooms and saute until tender, about 5 minutes.
Add scallions and garlic; saute 2 minutes.
Add heavy cream and tomatoes.
Heat to boiling over medium-high heat.
Reduce heat to low and simmer until sauce is thickened.
Add the peas, salt and pepper.
Heat, stirring, until peas are tender.
Meanwhile, cook fettuccine in plenty of boiling salted water until done and drain.
In a large serving bowl, toss with chicken and mushroom mixture.
Sprinkle with parsley and Parmesan cheese.

title: chocolate chess pie
directions: Mix first four ingredients well.
Add remaining ingredients. Pour into unbaked pie shell. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: mexican corn bread
directions: Mix all ingredients, beginning with eggs.
Pour into a well-greased, hot iron skillet.
Bake at 450° for approximately 40 minutes.
Can be doubled or made fat-free/low cholesterol.

title: turkey chili
directions: Using large frypan, saute the ground turkey using Pam in the pan.
Saute until meat is done.
Chop onion; put in with turkey, stirring.
Open and add large can kidney beans and tomato sauce. Stir frequently.
Shake on pepper, chili powder and onion flakes to taste.
Stir, serve and enjoy.

title: pineapple and coconut pies(makes 2 pies)
directions: Mix all ingredients together; put into unbaked pie shells. Bake at 325° for 45 to 55 minutes.

title: mint fudge
directions: Butter a 9 x 9-inch or 9 x 13-inch pan; set aside.

title: crab mold
directions: Dissolve gelatin in water.
Heat soup.
Add dissolved gelatin and add cream cheese until melted, then add rest of ingredients. Grease mold.
Pour in ingredients and refrigerate.
Unmold. Garnish with parsley and stuffed olives.

title: molded cranberry salad
directions: Cook cranberries in 1 cup water for twenty minutes.
Stir in sugar; cook 5 minutes longer.
Soften gelatin in 1/4 cup of cold water; dissolve and set aside.
Add cranberries and vegetables. Refrigerate to set.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Cook ground beef just long enough for it to separate.
Put in bottom of a baking dish, about 9 x 13-inch.
Sprinkle with dry onion soup; over that pour the creamed celery soup.
Then over that the Cheddar cheese soup.
Cover top with Tater Tots.
Bake in a 350° oven for one hour or until brown.

title: hearty stuffed shells
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In a large skillet, thoroughly brown beef, onion and garlic; drain fat.
In a large bowl, combine meat, breadcrumbs, egg, 1 cup spaghetti sauce, Parmesan cheese and oregano.
Season with salt and pepper.
Evenly spread 1 cup of sauce in baking dish.
Fill each shell with 1 heaping tablespoon meat mixture.
Arrange over sauce and top with remaining sauce. Bake, covered, 30 minutes.
Uncover; sprinkle with Mozzarella cheese and bake 5 minutes or until cheese melts.

title: coal garden
directions: Arrange coal in a bowl or flat dish.
Mix water, salt, bluing and ammonia; stir until salt dissolves.
Pour over coal.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Using a large skillet, saute onion, broccoli and mushrooms in butter 15 to 20 minutes.
Pour in soups and stir until well blended.
Pour in rice and stir.
Add Cheez Whiz and stir until well blended.
Place in large rectangular casserole and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: irish potato salad
directions: Mix and stir well.
It should be made several hours before putting on table.
Throw in bits of pickles and hard-boiled eggs.

title: venison meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients and place in baking dish.
Top with a mixture of brown sugar, mustard and catsup.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
You may divide into 2 pans.
Freeze one and bake the other.

title: nellie's bread
directions: Pour all ingredients in a bowl or mixer.
Mix until it is no longer sticky.
Shape into a ball and put the mixture in plastic bag for 1 hour.
Then take the bread out of the bag.
Knead and make any shape you desire.
Let it rise for 1 hour, when it's doubles put in the over for 25 minutes at 400°.

title: catalina salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together except corn chips.
Add them in before serving.

title: rhubarb cake
directions: Bake in an oblong cake pan at 350° for 1 hour.

title: rhubarb betty
directions: Arrange rhubarb in 12 x 8-inch glass baking dish.
Drizzle orange juice over fruit.
Mix next 5 ingredients and cut into margarine.
Sprinkle over rhubarb.
Bake at 350° for about 35 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: mamma's chicken dressing
directions: Mix rice, crumbled biscuits, crumbled muffin bread, light bread, torn in pieces, celery, onions and eggs.
Add broth from stewed hen to this mixture and allow for some evaporation during baking.
Cook in a big greased baking pan at about 400° for 15 minutes.
Reduce heat to 350° and bake for 30 more minutes. Pieces of hen can be arranged on top of dressing before baking. Serve with giblet gravy.

title: brown sugar blueberry pancakes
directions: Stir flour, brown sugar and baking powder through a strainer with the back of a spoon into medium size bowl.
Measure buttermilk into 4 cup glass measuring cup.
Add egg and melted butter.
Beat until blended.
Add to flour mixture and stir gently until well blended.
Stir in blueberries and orange peel.
Heat nonstick griddle on medium heat.
Lightly grease with 1/2 teaspoon butter.
Cook 1/4 cup batter 3 to 4 minutes, until bubbles appear on surface.
Turn; remove.
Sprinkle with brown sugar.

title: supper on a bread slice
directions: Cut bread in half lengthwise.
Mix all other ingredients except sliced cheese strips.
Spread meat mixture evenly over top surface of bread.
Wrap aluminum foil around crust side of each half, leaving top uncovered.
Place on a cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Remove from oven and garnish with strips of cheese.
Bake 5 minutes longer or until bubbly and browned nicely. (This can be done under a broiler.)

title: cookies in a jiffy
directions: Mix cake mix, oatmeal, oleo and eggs together well. Add M&M's or chocolate chips. Roll and bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: homemade crunchy peanut butter
directions: Measure 1/2 cup peanuts (you'll use them later).
Empty remaining peanuts (2 cups) into blender container.
Cover and blend on low speed 10 seconds or until the peanuts are chopped. Add 2 tablespoons butter to the chopped peanuts.
Cover and blend on low speed 10 seconds.
Turn off the blender.
Uncover and scrape down the sides with rubber scrapper.
Cover and blend on low speed 5 seconds.
Turn off the blender, uncover and scrape down the sides again.
Repeat this step 3 or 4 times or until the peanut butter starts to get smooth.
Cover and blend on highest speed 1 minute.
Uncover and add the 1/2 cup peanuts.
Cover and blend on medium speed 3 seconds.
Empty the peanut butter into bowl.
Refrigerate about 30 minutes.

title: pear cobbler
directions: Melt butter in baking dish.
Mix sugar, Bisquick, milk, nuts and raisins together.
