Spread in pan with butter.
Evenly spread pears over butter.
Sprinkle with cinnamon.
Bake at 400° for 40 minutes.

title: saucy baked chicken
directions: Mix chili sauce, soy sauce and mustard.
Dip each chicken piece in sauce, coating all sides.
Place chicken in baking pan that has been sprayed with Pam.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes. Serves 4.

title: effortless five hour oven stew
directions: Layer all ingredients in casserole.
Cover and bake in preheated oven at 250° for 5 hours.
Thicken gravy to serve if you desire.

title: un-stuffed cabbage
directions: Spray or grease a 13 x 9-inch pan or baking dish.
Mix together meat, rice, onion, egg whites and raisins.
In another bowl, beat together ginger ale, catsup, tomato sauce and honey.
Place 5 or 6 cups chopped cabbage in baking dish.
Spread meat mixture evenly over cabbage.
Sprinkle remaining cabbage over this.
Pour sauce mixture over all.
Bake, covered, in 350° oven for 1 1/2 hours until all ingredients are tender.
Serves 8.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together, except cheese and potato chips. Bake 20 minutes in 400° oven.
Add cheese and chips and bake 10 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: string bean and tater soup
directions: Brown meat in kettle 3/4 full of water.
Add onions.
Add potatoes and string beans.
Amount is flexible, determined by how far you want the soup to stretch.
Add spices if you like.
Bring to boil.
Cook until potatoes are tender.

title: artichoke chicken and rice salad
directions: Drain artichoke hearts, reserve marinade. Coarsely chop artichoke hearts. Cook rice according to package directions; Stir in reserved marinade. Cool. Combine artichoke hearts, rice, chicken, water chestnuts, olives and green onions. Mix mayonnaise, curry powder and pepper. Stir into chicken mixture. Cover and chill 1 to 2 hours. 8 servings.

title: savory macaroni
directions: Cook macaroni as directed on package.
Simmer onion and green peppers in skillet with margarine.
Cook until soft.
(Save out some of the onion, pepper, tomatoes and cheese.)
Now combine all the rest of the ingredients.
Mix well.
Pour into greased 2-quart casserole.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Fifteen minutes before finished, pour reserved ingredients on top and return to oven. Serves 8.

title: hamburger pie
directions: Mix all ingredients except potatoes, and bake in a 9-inch pie pan at 350° for 1 hour or until done.
Remove from oven after you have cooked and mashed the potatoes.
Place mashed potatoes on the top of hamburger like a topping, twirling it; bake until potatoes are slightly brown.

title: oatmeal pancakes
directions: Mix dry ingredients, then add eggs and buttermilk. Mix and bake on a lightly greased griddle. Very good with maple syrup or a fruit syrup!

title: candied yams
directions: Wash and peel yams.
Cut lengthwise in 1/4-inch slices.
Place in heavy skillet in which butter has been melted.
Sprinkle with water, sugar, salt and nutmeg.
Cover and cook very slowly until potatoes are tender.
Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: chop suey
directions: Brown meat.
Add onion, celery and water.
Simmer 30 to 40 minutes.
Add bean sprouts, soy sauce and water chestnuts.
Heat well and thicken with cornstarch.
Add salt and pepper to taste. Serve with chow mein noodles and rice.

title: creamy corn pudding
directions: Mix sugar, flour and salt together.
Add to beaten eggs.
Stir in corn, milk and melted butter. Pour into buttered 2-quart casserole. Bake at 350° for 1 hour, uncovered.
Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: chilled mexican appetizer
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients; spread mixture in 12-inch round platter with sides.
Combine chopped avocados, tomatoes and lemon juice; toss and arrange over bean mixture.
Set aside.

title: turkey-meatballs paprika
directions: In large bowl, combine all ingredients, except noodles, cream sauce mix and paprika.
Shape turkey mixture into 1 1/2-inch meatballs.
Place on jelly roll pan and bake 20 to 25 minutes at 400°.

title: butter bars
directions: Mix cake mix, 1 egg and melted butter.
Oil a 9 x 13-inch pan and press this mix into it.
Mix remaining ingredients together and pour over the first mixture.
Bake in a 350° oven for 40 minutes.

title: muggsy's favorite zucchini bread
directions: Combine eggs, oil, sugar & vanilla.
Beat together until thickens.
Add remaining ingredients.
Put into a greased and floured bread tin.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Makes 2 loaves.

title: chicken-broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli; drain.
Arrange broccoli in greased 7x11 inch baking dish.
Keep broccoli florets turned toward the outer edge of the dish.
Arrange chicken on top of broccoli.
Combine soup, milk, lemon juice, mayonnaise and curry powder; pour over chicken and broccoli.
Cover with cheese, making sure everything is covered with sauce and cheese.
Combine bread crumbs with melted butter and sprinkle over top.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° about 40 minutes.
Serves 8-10

title: nut brittle
directions: Spread peanuts in 15 x 10 x 1-inch pan.
Place in oven at 350° for 15 minutes. Remove.
Pour into a bowl; keep warm.
Meanwhile, blend baking soda and salt; set aside.
In 3-quart pan, stir together sugar, corn syrup and water.
Bring to boiling.
Boil rapidly until syrup begins to turn a golden color (275° on candy thermometer).
Add nuts and continue stirring often until syrup is a clear golden color (295°).
Remove from heat.
Quickly stir in butter or margarine and soda mixture.
Immediately pour hot mixture into 2 (15 x 10 x 1-inch) pans (buttered).
If desired, cool slightly and pull with forks to make thin.
Cool.
Break into pieces.
Makes 2 1/4 pounds.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: *You can also add chicken bouillon, and cream of chicken soup if desired.

title: blackberry cobbler
directions: Melt butter in casserole dish as oven preheats.
Mix together flour, sugar and milk until smooth.
Pour over butter; do not mix. Place berries on top and add sweetened juice.
Do not stir.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes, until crust rises to top and is golden brown.

title: chicken chantilly
directions: Blend sour cream and apricot jam together; spread over chicken in casserole.
Sprinkle lightly with paprika and bake at 325° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: no-fry doughnuts
directions: In large mixer bowl, dissolve yeast in warm water.
Add milk, sugar, salt, nutmeg, cinnamon, eggs, shortening and 2 cups of the flour.
Blend 1/2 minute on low speed, scraping bowl constantly. Beat 2 minutes medium speed, scraping bowl occasionally.
Stir in remaining flour until smooth, scraping side of bowl.
Cover; let rise in warm place until double, 50 to 60 minutes.

title: dessert chicken salad
directions: Serve with crackers as lunch salad.

title: fruit cocktail cake
directions: Sift together the sugar, flour, soda and salt. Mix eggs, fruit cocktail (undrained) and oil.
Blend dry and wet ingredients thoroughly.
Pour batter into a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: salmon patties
directions: In a medium bowl, beat eggs enough to blend.
Stir in salmon, 1/3 cup bread crumbs, onion and parsley, lemon juice, salt and pepper until well mixed.
Shape into 4 patties and coat with remaining bread crumbs.
These handle better if you refrigerate for at least 30 minutes before frying.

title: frozen strawberry daiquiri custard
directions: Beat egg yolks until fluffy.
Add 1 cup sugar gradually.
Beat until smooth.
Blend in lime and lemon juice, grated peel and salt. Stir over low heat until it thickens.
Soak gelatin in rum and stir into hot custard until it is dissolved.
Cool.
Beat egg whites until foamy; add 1 cup sugar gradually.
Beat until stiff.
Whip the cream until stiff.
Fold egg whites into custard, then fold in whipped cream.
Pour into pan and chill.
Can be served refrigerated or frozen.
Serve with strawberries.

title: bran muffins
directions: Pour milk over Bran Buds; let stand 5 minutes.
Mix sugar with Bisquick.
Add egg to Bran Buds, then add Bisquick mixture gradually.
Blend with fork.
Add raisins or nuts.
Bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Yield:
12 muffins.

title: egg noodles
directions: Add water
and
salt to egg and stir in enough flour to make stiff
dough.
Let
dough rest and roll on floured board. Cut thin and let dry 2 hours.

title: potato omelet
directions: Heat butter in a large skillet.
Add potatoes, a few at a time.
Cook until browned on both sides and tender.
Remove from skillet. Season with salt and pepper. Set aside.
Add onion to skillet and cook until tender.
Remove onion from skillet with slotted spoon.
Place in small bowl. Sprinkle with lemon juice. Return potatoes to skillet. Cover with tomatoes and onion. Cover skillet and cook over low heat 8 to 10 minutes.
Beat eggs and salt in a small bowl.
Pour over mixture in skillet. Cover and continue cooking until eggs are set. Cut into wedges to serve.

title: golden cheese and pepper rolls
directions: Grease a 13 x 9-inch pan.
In large bowl, combine flour mixture with yeast from foil packet.
Mix well.
In small saucepan, cook bell pepper in oil until tender.
Stir in corn and water.
Stir hot corn mixture and egg into flour mixture until dough pulls away from sides of bowl.
Turn dough on floured surface. Shape into a ball.
Knead 5 minutes, until smooth.
Cover dough in large bowl.
Let rise 5 minutes.
Divide into 24 pieces. Shape each piece of dough around 1 piece of cheese.
Cover and let rise for 30 minutes.
Bake at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes. Brush with butter.
Makes 24 rolls.

title: watergate salad
directions: Combine pudding mix, marshmallows and pineapple.
Mix well. Blend in whipped topping and chill for one hour before serving.

title: citrus fish steaks
directions: Combine all ingredients, except fish steaks.
Pour mixture over fish.
Cover and refrigerate at least 1 hour.
Remove fish; reserve marinade.
Cover and grill fish about 4-inches from heat, turning once and brushing 2 to 3 times with reserved marinade until fish flakes easily with fork.

title: ham-corn chowder
directions: Fry bacon crisp.
Add onion and celery and saute until golden brown.
Sprinkle with flour and stir.
Gradually stir in chicken broth and potatoes.
Simmer until potatoes are tender.
Add corn, milk and ham.
Simmer until chowder just starts to bubble; do not boil.
Season with salt and pepper and serve.

title: parmesan flounder fillets
directions: Arrange fillets in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan coated with vegetable cooking spray.
Combine remaining ingredients.
Spread mixture evenly over fillets.
Bake at 375° in oven for 12 to 15 minutes.
Yields 4 servings with about 161 calories per serving. You may used sliced lemons on your fish or with your fish.

title: 24 hour fruit salad
directions: Cook egg yolks, salt, vinegar, pineapple syrup, sugar and margarine in double boiler until thick.
Cool.
Fold in whipped cream, apricots, marshmallows, pineapple and oranges.
Chill 24 hours.
Serves 12.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Cream eggs and sugar.
Add remaining ingredients; mix well. Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours in a greased Bundt pan.

title: quick spanish rice
directions: Cook rice according to directions.
In medium saucepan, combine the first 7 ingredients.
Simmer for 10 minutes.
Stir cooked rice into tomato mixture.
May stir in chopped green onions.
Serves 4.

title: tuna mushroom canapes
directions: Drain tuna and flake.
Add soup, pimiento, green pepper and seasoning; blend.
Spread on bread.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Place on a baking sheet.
Broil 3 inches from heat for 5 minutes until cheese browns.
Makes 24 appetizers.

title: barbecued beef
directions: Brown onion, pepper and meat together.
Add remaining ingredients and cook slowly for 3/4 hour.

title: lemon-herb pot roast
directions: Combine lemon pepper, garlic and 1 teaspoon basil; press onto beef.

Heat oil in Dutch oven over medium until hot. Brown roast on all sides; drain well. Add 1 cup water to pan; bring to a boil. Reduce heat; cover tightly and simmer 2 hours. Add carrots, potatoes and onion. Continue cooking, covered, 30 to 45 minutes or until roast

and vegetables are fork-tender. Remove roast and veggies; keep warm. Skim fat from cooking liquid. Shake the cornstarch mixture and stir it into cooking liquid. Add the remaining basil. Cook and stir 1 minute or until thickened and bubbly. Carve roast. Serve with veggies and sauce.

title: brenna's cheesy spinach party loaf
directions: Cut slice from top of bread.
Remove center, leaving 1-inch of removed bread.
Brush inside with butter and bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Saute peppers, celery and onion.
Stir in rest of ingredients; heat, stirring constantly.
Pour into shell.
Serve.

title: chicken supreme
directions: Combine all ingredients except cheese.
Put in greased casserole dish, putting cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.
Serves 8.
This can be made and refrigerated overnight to be baked the next day.

title: italian casserole
directions: Brown hamburger, onions, celery and green peppers.
Drain and combine all ingredients, except cheese.
Pour into 9 x 11 dish and sprinkle with cheese and bake, uncovered, at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: scrambled eggs and green onion
directions: Saute onions in the butter in skillet, about 2 minutes.
Beat eggs slightly with fork and season with salt and pepper.
Add to onions and cook over low heat, stirring as egg sets.
When all is set, sprinkle with paprika.
Makes 4 servings.

title: sue's spanish chicken
directions: Put garlic and onion in blender and chop until fine.
Add a little oil.
Put water in pot.
Add garlic, onions, tomato sauce, garlic powder, onion powder and bouillon cube and bring all to a boil.
Add chicken.
When half done, add potatoes.
Cook until done.
Spoon over cooked rice.

title: pork chops and sauerkraut
directions: Brown pork chops in shortening in a large heavy skillet. Season with salt and pepper.
Remove chops from skillet; pour off the fat.
Add sauerkraut and apples; mix thoroughly.
Lay chops on top of kraut mixture.
Cover skillet and cook over low heat 1 hour, or until chops are tender.
Baste often with juices in pan.

title: apple pound cake
directions: Mix sugar and oil.
Add eggs and mix.
Combine flour, salt, soda and add with vanilla to the sugar mixture.
Add apples, walnuts and coconut.
Pour into a greased and floured tube pan. Bake at 375° for 1 hour and 20 minutes.

title: rice and steak casserole
directions: Cut steak bite size, roll in seasoned flour and brown.
Add celery and onions; brown lightly.
Place in 3-quart casserole. Stir in remaining ingredients.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: small town brownies
directions: Sift sugar, flour, salt and cinnamon into a bowl.
Bring oil, oleo, cocoa and water to boil.
Pour hot mixture over flour mixture and beat.
Dissolve soda in buttermilk and add to flour mixture along with eggs and vanilla.
Beat entire mixture.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugars together.
Add beaten eggs and cream together.
Mix dry ingredients.
Add vanilla, nuts and chips. Bake at 350°.

title: curried rice
directions: Rinse and dry rice.
Melt butter in skillet.
Add rice and cook, stirring, until lightly brown, about 10 minutes.
Add onion, celery and parsley and continue until vegetables are soft.
Add chicken broth, water and seasonings.
Cover and simmer over low heat about 20 minutes or until rice is tender.
Makes about 6 servings.

title: sugared nuts
directions: Combine sugar and sour cream in a large saucepan.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly until sugar is dissolved.
Cook without stirring to 234° on candy thermometer or until mixture forms a soft ball in cold water.
Remove from heat.
Add vanilla and nuts.
Stir gently until all nuts are coated.
Pour onto waxed paper.
Separate the nuts with a fork.
Let dry.
Store in an airtight container.
Yield: 4 cups.

title: bread bowl dip
directions: Cut top off bread and scoop out the inside of the bread.
Mix all the ingredients together and stuff inside the bread.
Put top back on bread bowl and cover with aluminum foil.

title: apple crumb pie
directions: Pare apples and cut up.
Arrange in 9-inch pie pan.
Sprinkle with 1/2 cup sugar mixed with cinnamon.
Sift remaining 1/2 cup sugar with flour.
Cut in butter until crumbly.
Sprinkle over apples.
Bake at 450° for 10 minutes, then reduce temperature to 350° and bake 40 minutes longer.

title: carrot cake
directions: Mix well and blend all ingredients except pineapple and eggs. Add the pineapple and eggs, two at a time, beating well. Bake at 350° for 40 minutes, then test.

title: congo squares 1
directions: Combine dry ingredients.
Add margarine and eggs.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan and bake at 350° until toothpick stuck in center comes out clean.

title: fried apples
directions: Slice the apples into 1/4-inch slices.
Melt the butter; add rings.
Sprinkle on brown sugar and cover for 5 to 7 minutes. Turn the rings over and repeat.
You can keep them warm in the oven.

title: chocolossal chip cookies
directions: Mix flour with baking powder and salt.
Beat butter until light and fluffy.
Gradually beat in sugars.
Mix in eggs and vanilla.
Stir in flour mixture until well blended.
Stir in chips and nuts.
Drop by rounded teaspoonfuls onto ungreased baking sheets.
Bake at 375° for 8 minutes or until lightly browned. Makes about 3 1/2 dozen cookies.

title: grandmother water's corn dodger cakes(160 years old)
directions: Scald cornmeal by adding small amounts of hot water at a time. Stir well after each addition.
Continue until all meal is scalded and is consistency of mush.
Drop by spoonful into deep hot grease.
Brown both sides.
Prefer bacon drippings.

title: spaghetti carbonara
directions: Cook bacon until crisp.

Drain; save 1 Tbsp. drippings. In blender, blend eggs, cream, parmesan, salt and pepper to taste. Cook pasta as directed, drain in colander.	On very low heat (in the same pot) melt butter and drippings; add cream, eggs and cheese mixture, stirring constantly, until thickened to a thin pudding consistency (coats the back of a spoon).
Toss in pasta and bacon bits.
Serve immediately with additional parmesan cheese.
I like to use garlic salt or better yet, mince garlic and add while butter is melting for a more robust flavor.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs.
Add oil, sugar, zucchini and vanilla.
Mix well. Add dry ingredients that have been sifted together.
Mix until well blended.
Pour into 2 regular loaf pans, which have been greased and floured.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: strawberry cake delight
directions: Bake the cake according to directions on the package, using two 8 or 9-inch round pans.
Remove from pans and cool. Clean, drain and mix fresh strawberries with the jar of strawberry glaze. Take one layer of cake and place it in a serving dish.
Put half of the fresh strawberries with glaze on top of it.
Place the second layer cake on top of it.
Put rest of berries on top of it. Frost the sides with Cool Whip, reserving a teaspoon of Cool Whip for the top of the cake.
Put a berry on top of the reserved Cool Whip for decoration.

title: easy veggie soup
directions: Brown and drain ground beef.
Add V-8 and Veg-All. Bring to a boil, then simmer until ready to eat.

title: depression chicken and noodles
directions: Combine all above ingredients (except noodles).
Place both pkg. of uncooked noodles in bottom of baking dish.
Pour all ingredients over the noodles, and bake at 350° until done, about 20 minutes.

title: sweet and spice pecans
directions: Preheat oven to 300 degrees.
Beat egg white and water until foamy.
Add sugar, spices and salt.
Let stand until sugar dissolves.
About 15 minutes.
Stir in nuts and mix well.
Spread on a large foil lined cookie sheet.
Bake 45 minutes stirring every 15 minutes.
Cool and break into pieces.

title: golden corn bread
directions: Sift dry ingredients into bowl.
Add egg, beaten until smooth, about 1 minute.
Do not overbeat.
Bake in greased 8-inch square pan or greased muffin pan.
Bake about 20 to 25 minutes at 350°.

title: pumpkin cake
directions: In a large bowl, sift flour.
Add cinnamon, soda, salt and baking powder.
In separate bowl, mix eggs, sugar, oil and pumpkin.
Mix well.
Add to dry ingredients.
Grease and flour a 9 x 13-inch pan and bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: chris' best carrot cake(an exceptional carrot cake!)
directions: Combine flour, soda, salt and cinnamon and set aside.
Combine eggs, oil, buttermilk, sugar and vanilla.
Beat until smooth. Stir in flour mixture, pineapple, carrots, coconut and chopped walnuts.
Pour batter into three greased and floured 9-inch round cake pans.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes or until a wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean.
Immediately spread Buttermilk Glaze evenly over layers.
Cool in pans 15 minutes. Remove from pans and let cool completely.
Frost with Cream Cheese Frosting:

title: beef jerky
directions: Marinate overnight.
Drain on paper towels.
Cook at 150° for 5 hours.
Leave oven door open a little.

title: mexican corn bread
directions: Mix in order given.
Beat eggs, grate cheese and crumble bacon.
Bake at 400° for 35 minutes.

title: texas sheet cake
directions: Mix oleo, water and cocoa.
Add sugar, flour and salt.
Then add the sour cream, soda and eggs.
Bake on cookie sheet (with sides), 12 x 18-inch, for 20 to 22 minutes at 375°.

title: turkey tetrazzini
directions: Cook spaghetti in broth. Add remaining ingredients and stir over low fire until cheese melts.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch pan and bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: chocolate chip cheese cake
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
Combine cookie crumbs, sugar and margarine.
Press firmly onto bottom of 9-inch pan.

title: strawberry fling (non-alcoholic drink)
directions: Beat ice cream until foamy thick in blender; pour into glasses.
Pour grenadine from spoon down inside each glass (forms bright crimson layer on bottom).
Garnish with strawberries. Makes 3 to 4 servings.

title: mulligan stew(serves 6)
directions: Heat oil in Dutch oven or kettle.
Add onions and saute until tender.
Slice fish in 1 to 2-inch pieces.
Add fish and remaining ingredients to onions.
Cover and simmer 25 minutes or until vegetables are tender.
Garnish with parsley and bacon (if used).

title: graham cracker cream pie
directions: After these are blended, press 2/3 of mixture in pie plate.

title: hot taco dip
directions: Fry sausage until done, drain and mash.
Add cheese, sauce and soup and heat until melted and heated through.
Serve in crock-pot to keep warm with corn chips.

title: good punch
directions: Mix water and sugar together and bring to a boil.
Add juices. Mix well and pour into jars or 1 gallon container (milk jugs) and freeze.
Set out 2 hours before serving.
Mix in punch bowl with Sprite.
Food coloring may be added.

title: mexican dip
directions: Layer on a dish in the order listed.
Top with a layer of grated cheese.
Chill approximately 1 1/2 hours.
Serve with chips and crackers.
This is an excellent party dip!

title: frosted hot dogs
directions: Cook bacon until crisp.
Crumble it into small pieces.
Add cheese and 1 tablespoon bacon drippings to mashed potatoes.
Split hot dogs lengthwise, not quite all the way through.
Fill with potato mixture.
Broil 4 to 5-inches from heat for about 5 minutes or until hot dogs are warm and potatoes are lightly browned.

title: little pecan sandwiches
directions: Spread the anchovy paste and cheese on the pecan half.
Top with another pecan half to make a tiny "sandwich."

title: baked acorn squash
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Pierce squash a few times and cook in microwave for 5 minutes on High (or until squash is slightly softened).
Remove and let cool until you can handle without burning hands.
Cut squash lengthwise in half and scrape out seeds.
Put 2 to 3 pats butter on each piece; drizzle well with honey and sprinkle with a little cinnamon and nutmeg.
Place both halves in shallow baking dish, skin side down.
Bake in 350° oven for 30 minutes.
Serves 2.

title: grandma's potato salad
directions: In the top of a double boiler over boiling water, heat water, butter and vinegar.
In a bowl, beat eggs.
Add sugar and cornstarch.
Add to butter mixture; cook and stir constantly until thick, about 5 to 7 minutes.
Remove from the heat; allow to cool. Stir in the salad dressing.
Fold in the whipped cream.
In a large bowl, toss potatoes, onions, salt and pepper.
Pour the dressing over and mix gently.
Chill.
Serve in a lettuce lined bowl, if desired.
Garnish with the hard-cooked eggs; sprinkle with paprika.
Yields 18 servings.

title: skillet salad
directions: Melt butter in skillet. Add all ingredients and cover.
Simmer 15 to 20 minutes or until tender.
Serve hot.

title: shepherd's pie
directions: Put meat in bottom
of baking dish.
Pour tomatoes over the meat.
Sprinkle with butter or margarine, salt and pepper. Then add enough cooked and
mashed potatoes to fill your dish. Sprinkle this with buttered
bread
crumbs,
salt
and pepper. (It improves the meat very much
if a small onion and a little green pepper are added.) Serves 5 or 6.

title: watergate cake
directions: Mix cake mix, 1 box pudding, oil, eggs, club soda and nuts. Grease and flour tube pan at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Cool. Beat Dream Whip until stiff peaks form.
Fold in other box of pudding.
Put on cake and refrigerate.

title: chicken taco
directions: Cook chicken; cool and debone.
Grease a 9 x 13-inch pan. Mix soups, onions, tomatoes and cheese.
Layer chicken, Doritos and soup mixture.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: spinach-cheese casserole
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Combine all ingredients and mix well.
Put into well greased loaf pan.
Bake 1 hour or until top is lightly browned.

title: joni's dad's baked beans
directions: Mix all ingredients together and put in 9 1/2 x 13 1/2-inch baking dish. Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: green beans with tomatoes
directions: Cook on top of stove until tender.

title: sweet-sour pork roast
directions: Sprinkle the pork roast with salt and pepper to taste; place in a baking pan.
Roast at 325° for 1 hour; pour off excess fat. Combine the tomato sauce, lemon juice, water, grated rind, 1/2 teaspoon salt, brown sugar and nutmeg in a saucepan.
Drain the pineapple chunks; pour over the roast.
Roast for about 2 hours, basting occasionally and adding water, if needed.
Makes 6 servings.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Mix well and pour into pie crust.
Place in freezer for several hours.
Top with Cool Whip and serve.

title: silver cake
directions: Cream butter; gradually add flour, then sugar and flavoring. Add egg whites last, that have been beaten stiff.
Frost with white frosting.
Bake at 350° until done.

title: shrimp fried rice
directions: In butter, saute onion, bell peppers, parsley flakes and green onions until clear. Season shrimp with Tony's and add to vegetables. Cook on medium heat until shrimp are pink. Pour beaten eggs into shrimp and vegetables. Add rice and stir until rice is coated with egg mixture. Cover and cook on low heat until eggs are cooked.

title: carrot bran muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Grease 12 muffin cups.
In large bowl, combine carrots, bran, honey, milk, oil, lemon juice, egg, dates or raisins and nuts, if desired.
Let mixture stand for 5 minutes. In a medium bowl mix together flour, sugar, baking soda, pumpkin pie spice and salt.
Combine dry ingredients into wet ingredients and stir just until moistened.
Bake for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: spicy garbanzo soup
directions: In a saucepan, over medium-high heat, heat tomato juice, tomato paste and hot pepper sauce, stirring to mix well.
Add garbanzos and chicken or turkey and bring to a low boil.
Reduce heat immediately.
Add oregano and simmer 5 minutes.
Stir in diced avocado and heat for 2 to 3 minutes.
Serve hot with parsley sprinkled on top.
Makes 4 (3/4-cup) servings.

title: eggs loraine
directions: Melt butter in 9 x 9-inch square pan.
Put 1/2 of cheese on bottom of pan.
Break eggs in pan; pierce yolks with fork and swirl.
Lay sausages over eggs.
Pour cream over all and sprinkle with other 1/2 of cheese.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes. Serves 6.

title: pineapple lime mold
directions: Bring 1 cup water to boil; stir in gelatin until dissolved. Add remaining 1/2 cup water and juice.
Gradually add gelatin to cream cheese, mixing until blended.
Chill until thickened, but not set.
Fold in pineapple, marshmallows and nuts.
Pour into 1-quart mold.
Chill until firm.
Unmold onto serving plate, surround with lettuce.
Serve with assorted fresh fruits and nuts, if desired.

title: microwave rocky road fudge
directions: Place milk chocolate chips in a large bowl.
Microwave, uncovered, on 50% power for 3 to 4 minutes, stirring once.
Stir in marshmallows and nuts.
Drop by teaspoons onto waxed paper and chill until firm, about 15 minutes.
Yield: about 24 pieces.

title: quick fruit cobbler
directions: Cream together the sugar and soft margarine.
Add milk, flour, baking powder and salt.
Mix until smooth.
Put 1/4 cup margarine in a 9 x 13-inch casserole dish and melt in oven.
Spread batter mixture over the melted margarine.
Put fruit on top.
If using fresh fruit, sprinkle with 3/4 cup of sugar (for fresh cherries, add slightly more sugar).

title: shrimp dip
directions: Cook shrimp. Rinse. Drain well. Mix all of the ingredients. Chill. Serve on crackers.

title: cheese pecan ball
directions: Chop onions and beef.
Mix everything together except pecans. Roll into a ball on wax paper. Cover with pecans.
Keep refrigerated until ready to serve. Allow time for flavors to mix.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients until dough is sticky and stands up.
More flour is needed on humid days.
Drop dough onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: hot jezebel sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients and serve with meat or spread over cream cheese with crackers for a canape.
Keeps indefinitely in the refrigerator.

title: lemon chess pie
directions: Mix sugar, corn meal and flour; add remaining ingredients. Mix well.
Pour in unbaked crust.
Bake at 350° on lower shelf of oven for 45 minutes.

title: strawberry bread
directions: Mix the
sugar, oil and eggs.
Add dry ingredients; mix well, then
add
strawberries and nuts.
Can be baked in well-greased loaf
pans	or
coffee cans filled half full.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes or until done.

title: strawberry shortcake
directions: In a mixing bowl, cream sugar and shortening.
Add eggs and vanilla; beat well.
Combine dry ingredients and add alternately with milk to the creamed mixture.
Spread in a greased 9-inch square pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Cool on wire rack.
Cut into 9 servings.
Split each serving horizontally and fill with whipped cream and strawberries.
Replace top of cake; garnish with berries and whipped cream.
Serve immediately.

title: almond cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Sift together the flour, cornstarch, baking powder and spices.
Blend into butter mixture.
Stir in chopped nuts.
Chill dough at least 2 hours.
Shape dough into rounds the size of melon balls.
Place on greased baking sheet; flatten slightly.
Combine egg yolk and water; brush onto cookies. Top each cookie with a nutmeat, pressing into cookie.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes until golden brown.
Yield:
3 dozen cookies.

title: lemon velvet cake
directions: Follow the directions on the cake mix box.
As soon as cake is removed from oven punch holes in cake with toothpick and pour icing over cake while hot.
Bake in oblong pan.

title: white sugar cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Mix in dry ingredients.
Chill dough.
Roll thin; cut out.
Bake at 425° for 8 minutes, until brown on edge.

title: macaroni pie
directions: Beat the eggs, milk, salt and pepper.
Put a layer of macaroni in baking dish; cover with grated cheese.
Repeat layers of macaroni and cheese. Pour the milk and egg mixture over the macaroni and cheese.
Dot with margarine.
Bake at 350° until browned.

title: low-fat rice pudding
directions: In large saucepan, bring to boil the rice and water.
Stir, cover and simmer until rice is tender and liquid is absorbed, about 14 minutes.
Turn into a round 1 1/2-quart casserole, sprayed with nonstick spray.
Stir in raisins; set aside.

title: a "child could make" blueberry cake
directions: Put berries in a 10 1/2 x 7 x 1-inch baking pan.
Cover with pineapple.
Pour on dry cake mix and scatter nuts over top. Drizzle melted butter over all.
Place in preheated moderate oven (350°) and bake for 1 hour.
Cool and cut in squares.

title: homemade vegetable soup
directions: Simmer soup bones in 2 quarts water with salt, pepper, juice from whole kernel corn and 1 onion, cut as directed, for 1 1/2 hours.
Add carrots and celery; cook until tender.

title: fruit bread, milan style
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Pour melted butter into large bowl of electric mixer.
Add the sugar and salt gradually, beating constantly.
Beating thoroughly after each addition, alternately add the 2 cups flour in thirds and lukewarm milk in halves to the butter mixture.
Add yeast and beat well.
Combine eggs and egg yolks and beat until thick and piled softly.
Add the beaten eggs all at one time to yeast mixture and beat well.
Beating thoroughly after each addition, gradually add the 3 1/2 cups flour.
Stir in raisins and citron.
Sift half of the remaining 1/2 cup flour over a pastry canvas or board.
Turn dough onto floured surface; cover and let rest 10 minutes.

title: one egg cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into a 9-inch greased and floured pan.
Bake at 375°.

title: five-minute fruit salad
directions: Arrange pineapple, oranges and kiwi on 4 lettuce lined plates. In a small bowl, stir together mayonnaise and milk. Spoon over fruit mixture. Sprinkle with nuts.

title: caramel dip
directions: With the exception of the nuts, mix all the ingredients together.
Blend with mixer.
Add nuts if desired.
Serve with apple or pear slices.

title: peanut butter pudding cake
directions: Thoroughly stir together flour, 3/4 cup of the brown sugar, the baking powder and salt.
Add milk, peanut butter, cooking oil and vanilla.
Spread in a greased 8 x 8 x 2-inch baking dish. Sprinkle with remaining brown sugar.
Carefully pour hot water over entire top.
Bake in a 350° oven for 45 minutes.
Serve warm with vanilla ice cream.

title: copper pennies
directions: Mix above ingredients and roll into two long rolls, about 50-cent size around.
Wrap in waxed paper.
(This will keep several days in the refrigerator.)
Slice 1/4 to 1/2-inch thick.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet, about 8 minutes in a 400° oven.
Good appetizers.

title: onion corn bread
directions: Mix together corn meal and flour.
Add buttermilk.
Beat egg, then add to mixture.
Add oil and mix well.
Add diced onions. Brush butter on bottom and sides of muffin pan (approximately 1/4 cup melted butter).
Spoon equal amounts of mixture in each pan. Preheat oven.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes or until golden brown.

title: coconut pound cake
directions: Sift together flour, salt and baking powder.
Cream Crisco, sugar and eggs together; beat well.
Add flour and milk alternately, ending with flour.
Add coconut flavoring.
Bake in tube pan or two loaf pans that have been greased and floured. Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until done.
Test with toothpick.

title: ma's salad
directions: Heat fruit to boiling.
Add cheese and jello in fruit.
Let partly cool.
Add milk.

title: pinwheel date cookies
directions: Mix shortening, brown sugar and 1 cup sugar; mix in eggs and cream well.
Sift flour with cinnamon, soda and salt; add to creamed mixture.
Roll out like jelly roll.
Cook dates, remaining sugar and water until smooth.
Add nuts.
Cool.
Spread date mixture on dough.
Roll up; wrap in waxed paper or foil. Refrigerate overnight.
Slice in 1/4-inch slices.
Bake at 375° for about 15 minutes.
Yield:
5 to 6 dozen cookies.

title: mexican cheese dip
directions: Melt butter.
Blend in flour and spices. Add milk and ketchup. Stir well. Add cheese and cook until cheese is melted. This recipe may also be cooked in your microwave.

title: squash pickles
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients and cover with water and ice for 3 hours.
Drain.
Bring to a boil and add remaining ingredients. Boil for 3 minutes and put in jars.

title: cherry streusel coffee cake
directions: *Can use blueberry pie filling or peach, except add 1/2 teaspoon cinnamon to the sugar before sprinkling over fruit.

title: cream cheese mints
directions: Combine softened (not melted) cheese and butter.
Beat well. Add sugar gradually; beat well.
Add flavoring and color.
Beat until nice and smooth.
Roll into small balls and flatten with palm of hand.
Place on wax paper and let dry for 4 hours or overnight, until mints are firm and the outside is dry, but inside is moist and creamy.
Yields 8 dozen.

title: deviled eggs
directions: Boil the eggs for about 45 minutes and then pour off the hot water and immediately cover them with cold water to stop the cooking of the eggs.
(Never boil an egg rapidly.)
Cut in half lengthwise.
Remove egg yolks and mash; blend with the relish, mayonnaise and salt.
Spoon into egg whites and chill.
If you like, add the carrots.

title: new orleans style creole chicken
directions: Season chicken breasts on both sides with salt and white pepper.
In a large electric skillet or regular skillet, heat vegetable oil (very hot).
Place chicken breasts in oil and let slightly brown, then turn and brown on other side (about 3 minutes each side).
Remove chicken from skillet and keep warm in a 250° oven.
Lower temperature in skillet and add onion, green onions, bell peppers, celery, bay leaf, garlic, thyme, cayenne pepper and gumbo file powder and saute until the onions are clear.
Then add water and tomatoes and simmer about 4 minutes.
Add chicken and simmer for an additional 10 minutes.
Adjust with salt and pepper to taste and serve over buttered rice.
Sprinkle chopped parsley over finished dish.
Serve with your favorite vegetable.
Serves 4.

title: zucchini quiche
directions: Combine all ingredients in a bowl.
Spread in a greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Preheat oven to 350° and bake 35 minutes until golden brown.

title: meatball stroganoff
directions: Mix thoroughly the beef, bread crumbs, onion, egg and seasoning.
Shape into 16 meatballs.
In skillet, brown meatballs; pour off fat.
Stir in soup, sour cream and water.
Cover; cook over low heat for 20 minutes, stirring now and then.
Serve with noodles.
Makes about 4 cups.

title: congo bars
directions: Melt shortening.
Add brown sugar and stir well.
Cool slightly.
Add the eggs, one at a time.
Beat well.
Add the dry ingredients and mix well.
Stir in the remaining ingredients and mix well.
Bake in a 9 x 13-inch greased pan at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: chocolate chip cake
directions: Grease and flour Bundt pan.
Beat together first 5 ingredients for 2 minutes.
Fold in chocolates.
Bake 50 to 60 minutes at 350°.
Cool 10 minutes.
Remove from pan.
Sprinkle with confectioners sugar.

title: nopalitos
directions: Boil cactus in salted water for 10 minutes and drain.
Saute ground meat in skillet and add remaining ingredients.
Simmer for 10 to 15 minutes.
Serve with black beans and tortillas.

title: cherry salad
directions: Mix cherries, pineapple and sugar.
Let sit overnight or for several hours.
When ready to serve, add pecans, marshmallows and bananas.
Mix and serve.

title: diet mandarin orange salad
directions: Mix whipped topping and cottage cheese.
Add mandarin oranges. Add jello dry to mixture.
Mix and refrigerate.
May use different fruits and other flavors of jello.

title: marinated pasta salad
directions: Cook macaroni 7 minutes.
Drain.
Rinse with cold water and drain again.
Put oil, sugar, vinegar, onion, salt and parsley into blender and mix until well blended.
Mix vegetables with macaroni.
Pour blended marinade over the vegetable mixture and let set overnight.
Stir once or twice while marinating.

title: marinated shrimp
directions: Mix oil, chili sauce, sugar, Worcestershire sauce, vinegar, bay leaves and hot sauce.
Pour sauce mixture over shrimp in large Ziploc bag.
Toss and marinate for at least 24 hours.
Drain most of the sauce mixture off and serve chilled.

title: $50 dollar cheese cake
directions: Mix all ingredients with an electric mixer until you have a smooth cake-like batter.
Pour into a baked and cooled graham cracker crumb crust in a spring form pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Leave oven on when you take out the cheesecake.
Cool for 10 minutes.
Then prepare the topping.

title: meat loaf
directions: Soak bread crumbs in milk for a few minutes.
Beat egg.
Mix all ingredients (except sauce ingredients) well.
Place in baking dish.

title: zucchini fruit bread
directions: Cream sugar, oil, egg and vanilla; mix well.
Grate zucchini. Combine with orange juice and peel; set aside.
Combine all dry ingredients and blend with creamed mixture.
Fold in zucchini mixture, nuts, dates and raisins.
Pour into Bundt pan that has been well-greased and floured.
Bake in preheated 325° oven for 1 hour and 15 minutes or until toothpick inserted near center comes out clean.
Wrap in foil, when cool, to keep moist.
This freezes well.

title: shepherd's pie
directions: Prepare your favorite meat loaf mixture.
Spread mixture in bottom of large cast-iron skillet or 9 x 13-inch baking pan. Cover meat loaf with mashed potatoes.
Prepare cornbread mix and pour batter over mashed potatoes.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: apricot punch
directions: Dissolve jello in hot water.
Add other ingredients and chill. Add 1 quart cold ginger ale at serving time.
Makes 1 gallon.

title: dutch fork slaw(shared by makay's georgia neighbors)
directions: *Can use 1 small can pimento as substitute.

title: grandma's good ol' okra
directions: Wash okra; drain.
Cut in small pieces.
Roll in cornmeal and salt.
Put oil in pan.
Add okra.
Cook in oven at 450° until done.
Stir occasionally.

title: poppy seed cake
directions: Cream shortening and sugar until light.
Add egg yolks, one at a time, beating well.
Add poppy seed filling.
Blend in yogurt and vanilla.
Sift flour, baking soda and salt; add gradually. Beat well.
Fold in stiffly beaten egg whites.
Pour into greased and floured Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes. Cool in pan 5 minutes.
Remove and cool on wire rack.
Sprinkle top with powdered sugar.

title: steak with herb dumplings
directions: Cut meat into serving sizes.
Trim and discard all fat.
Heat oil and brown meat on both sides; drain off oil.
Season meat highly with black pepper, paprika and Worcestershire sauce.
Add onions.
Pour soup mixture over all.
Cover and cook 1 hour or until tender.

title: steak and potato casserole
directions: Brown the steak in oil.
Slice potatoes and onions thin.
Line the casserole with a layer of potatoes and onions.
Place the steak on top, then pour the soup over the steak.
Repeat until all the potatoes, onions and steak are used.
Season to taste.
Bake in a 350° oven until meat and potatoes are done.

title: zesty crackers
directions: Pour oil into a large bowl.
Add dill weed, garlic salt and dressing.
Mix well.
Add oyster crackers and stir.
Seal the bowl and let stand for one hour, stirring every 15 minutes.
Serve.

title: irene's zucchini casserole
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Saute zucchini, mushrooms and onion in butter for about 10 minutes.
Stir in parsley and other seasonings.
In
a large bowl, blend eggs and cheese.
Add vegetable mixture.

title: easy english trifle("looks impressive, but is really easy.")
directions: Mix cake according to pkg directions and bake in 9 x 13 pan.
Cool completely and cut into 3 inch squares.
Layer once in bottom of a large trifle dish or large clear bowl.
Prepare pudding as directed.
Spread half of pudding on cake layer.
Spread half of strawberries over pudding.
Repeat all layers.
Refrigerate a couple of hours.
Just before serving, spread Cool Whip over top and garnish with fresh strawberries.

title: banana chocolate chip muffins
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
In large mixer bowl combine sugar and butter.
Beat at medium speed 1 to 2 minutes.
Add bananas, eggs and vanilla.
Continue beating until well mixed (1 to 2 minutes). By hand, stir in flour, baking soda and salt just until moistened. Fold in chocolate chips.
Spoon into greased 12-cup large muffin pan or 18-cup regular muffin pan.
Bake for 18 to 25 minutes or until light golden brown.
Remove from pan.

title: chocolate delight
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients until crumbly and pat into bottom of 8 x 12-inch pan.
Bake at 300° for 15 minutes.
Cool.
Combine powdered sugar and cream cheese, mix well.
Fold in 1 container of cool whip.
Spread over cooled crust.
Combine pudding and milk and pour over other 2 layers.
Spread remaining container of cool whip on top.
Keep refrigerated.

title: pico de gallo
directions: Combine vegetables. Add remaining ingredients.
Mix thoroughly.
Refrigerate several hours or overnight. Serve with corn or tortilla chips.

title: banana split ice cream
directions: Mix all the ingredients and our into ice cream freezer, adding enough milk to reach fill line in freezer can.

title: oatmeal chocolate chip cake
directions: Pour water over oatmeal in bowl.
Let it stand for 10 minutes. Add brown sugar, sugar and margarine.
Add eggs and mix well.
In another bowl, mix flour, baking soda, salt and cocoa, then add this to oatmeal mixture.
Now add 2/3 of the chocolate chips and the walnuts.
Pour into a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle with remaining chocolate chips.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: pizza sauce
directions: Put everything in a large pot and beat with wire whisk.
Makes 3 gallons.

title: southern stuffed bell peppers
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Crumble cornbread into large mixing bowl.
Add corn, tomatoes and peas.
Mix evenly until moist.
Add ham and mix.
Stuff mixture into bell peppers and place in large baking dish.
Spoon excess stuffing around peppers and place 1 strip bacon on top of each pepper.
Bake for 40 minutes.

title: easy chile
directions: Brown meat and drain well, salt and pepper.
Add onions, soup and garlic.
Stir well, add chili powder.
Simmer 15 to 30 minutes. Makes 4 servings.

title: graham cracker sandwiches
directions: Mix peanut butter and pudding mix in a medium bowl. Mix in milk. Let stand 5 minutes. (The mixture is a bit thicker than regular pudding.) Spread the pudding mixture on 8 graham crackers. Top with a second cracker. Place on a cookie sheet and freeze. Serve frozen.

title: persimmon cream pie
directions: Mix well.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake in 350° oven about 35 to 45 minutes.

title: chocolate finger paint
directions: Put
pudding
mix and milk in a medium size bowl.
Beat with an
electric
mixer at low speed for 2 minutes.
Let set until thick.
Finger
paint on white paper.
Let your picture dry for several hours.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Bring undiluted soup to a boil; add cream cheese until smooth and melted.
Add gelatine.
Put into the refrigerator until chilled.
Add celery, onion, mayonnaise and shrimp.
Pour into a mold and chill.
Take out of refrigerator 15 minutes before unmolding.
Serve with crackers.

title: rum goodies
directions: Mix all liquid ingredients in a large container. Place crushed ice in the glasses and garnish with the fruit. Pour punch into the glasses and serve.

title: sour cream hot potato salad
directions: Cut up potatoes in a large bowl. Saute onion in butter.
Mix with potatoes. Add both containers of sour cream.
Salt and pepper to taste. Sprinkle with parsley flakes.

title: seasoned salt
directions: Mix together all ingredients.
Store in airtight container. Use in soups, dressings, meats, vegetables, etc.
Experiment:
Add or subtract spices you personally like.
Example:
Lemon rind, parsley, cumin, etc.

title: chocolate covered cherries
directions: In a mixing bowl, cream the butter. Add

marshmallow creme, salt, extract and sugar; mix well. Knead into a large ball; chill for 1 hour. Roll into 1-inch balls and flatten into 2-inch circles. Wrap the circles around the cherries and carefully shape into balls. Place on a waxed paper-lined baking sheet. Cover loosely and refrigerate for 4 hours or overnight

title: rhubarb punch
directions: In a large saucepan, combine rhubarb, water and sugar.
Bring to a boil, reduce heat and simmer 5 to 10 minutes or until rhubarb is tender.
Cool slightly.
In a blender process half the mixture at a time until smooth.
Combine all ingredients.
In a large container, add enough water to make 1 gallon.
Serve on ice.

title: sweet monkey bread
directions: Add shortening to boiling water; cool to lukewarm.
Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Add sugar and egg to shortening.
Add yeast and mix.
Add flour.
Knead several minutes.
Turn into greased bowl.
Cover and let rise until double its size.

title: cream cheese bars
directions: Mix butter and brown sugar.
Add flour and save 1 cup as topping.
Use the rest as crust.
Put in a 13 x 9-inch pan and bake at 350° for 12 minutes.

title: zucchini bread
directions: In a large bowl beat eggs, sugar, oil, milk and vanilla.
In separate bowl, combine flour, baking powder, baking soda, salt and cinnamon.
Add dry ingredients to egg mixture and beat 2 minutes. Then add zucchini and nuts.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Makes 2 regular size loaf pans.
Grease and flour baking pans well.
Keep refrigerated.
Also freezes well.

title: don's shrimp etouffee
directions: Chop all vegetables as fine as possible.
Heat butter until it bubbles.
Add chopped vegetables.
Fry until golden brown; add drained tomatoes and half of the juice.
Let cook for 10 minutes. Add shrimp, seasoning and sherry.
Lower fire.
Cover and let steam 20 to 30 minutes.
Serve over fluffy rice.

title: marinated carrots
directions: Cook carrots until almost done; drain and cool.
Add onion and celery.
Combine remaining ingredients; mix well.
Refrigerate for at least 12 hours.

title: fruit cake cookies
directions: Mix all together and drop on cookie sheet.
Bake for 15 to 20 minutes at 300°.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix together. Form into small balls and cook at 400° on ungreased cookie sheet for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: grandmother's pudding
directions: Mix together and boil until thick.
(To do in microwave, reduce milk by 1/8 cup.)
Pour into 9-inch pie crust.
For chocolate, add 2 tablespoons cocoa, then cook.
For coconut, add 1/2 cup when mix almost done.

title: sugar free apple pie
directions: Need pastry for a double crust pie.
Cook together the apple juice, flour, tapioca, cinnamon and nutmeg until it begins to thicken.
Add the apples and cool slightly.
Fill the pastry shell and dot with butter.
Fit top crust and cut slits on top.
Bake at 415° for 15 to 20 minutes, then bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until golden brown.

title: "spinach dip"
directions: Blend well and chill overnight.
Serve dip in center of scooped out Hawaiian bread.

title: garlic biscuits(good with spaghetti or anything)
directions: Make Bisquick dough.
Add grated cheese.
Bake as ordered on Bisquick box.
Melt butter.
Add garlic powder.
Brush on biscuits.
Serve hot.

title: black and white brownies
directions: Grease 9 x 13 baking pan; set aside.
Prepare brownie mix according to directions.
Stir in half of white baking pieces, all of semi-sweet chocolate pieces and the 1/2 cup pecans.
Spread the batter in the prepared pan.
Bake at 350° about 30 minutes or until center is set.
Sprinkle remaining white baking pieces.
Bake 1 minute.
Cool in pan.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook chicken, skin and remove bones.
Cut in bite-size pieces. In a greased 9 x 13-inch casserole, cover the bottom with cooked chicken.
Mix soup, mayonnaise and poppy seed thoroughly and spread over chicken.
Crush enough Ritz crackers to spread over chicken and soup mixture to cover 1/4-inch depth.
Cook 1 hour at 325°.
If boned skinned chicken seems dry, sprinkle with chicken broth.
This can be prepared a day ahead.
Freezes good, too.

title: no sugar added peanut butter balls
directions: Cream butter and peanut butter together until well mixed. Add Equal spoonful 1/3 at a time mixing well after after addition. Mix in crushed rice krispies cereal until crumbly.
Make into balls size of walnuts and put on wax paper lined cookie sheets. Refrigerate until very firm.
Melt chocolate coating in double boiler with oil and dip balls to cover, set on wax paper to cool. Store in an airtight container.

title: lemon oil cake
directions: Combine ingredients in mixing bowl. Beat until well mixed, medium speed. Bake about 1
hour at 350°; test with straw. Heavy pan works best; be sure to oil and dust with flour. Let cake stand in pan a little while before turning on plate and then put on glaze.

title: green punch
directions: Mix until sugar is dissolved.
At last minute, add 1-quart 7-Up.
Serves 16.

title: grandma's rice pudding
directions: Cook rice until soft, approximately 1/2 hour.
Watch closely. Put all ingredients into a 1 1/2-quart baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: fresh apple cake(from harrisville cookbook)
directions: Chop peeled apples and set aside.
Measure salad oil into large mixing bowl.
Add sugar and eggs; beat until creamy.
Add dry ingredients.
Add nuts and apples.
Bake in 9 x 13-inch pan or 2 layers at 350° for 30 minutes or more, depending upon apples used.

title: crock-pot lasagna
directions: Cook onion, beef and garlic together in a skillet; drain. Add Ragu and mix well. Spread 1/4 of meat sauce in bottom of 5-quart slow cooker. Arrange 1/3 of noodles over sauce (may need to break noodles to fit). Combine the cheeses; spoon 1/3 of mixture over the noodles. Repeat layers twice. Top with remaining meat sauce. Cover and cook on low for 4 to 5 hours or until noodles are tender. Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: cheese grits
directions: Mix together salt, grits and water.
Cook for 5 minutes.
Add both kinds of cheese and the margarine, mixing well.
While still hot, place in casserole.
This much can be done a day ahead and refrigerated to bake the following day.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.

title: sour cream sugar cookies
directions: Cream margarine and sugar; add eggs and vanilla, mix well. Sift together dry ingredients; add alternately with sour cream, mixing well after each addition.
Dough will be stiff.
Drop dough by teaspoon on greased cookie sheet.
Dip bottom of a glass in water, then sugar.
Press each cookie to flatten.
Bake 8 minutes at 425°.
Makes 6 dozen.

title: skinny mary
directions: Pour tomato and sauerkraut juice over ice cubes in glass.
Add Worcestershire sauce and stir.
Serve at once.
Makes 1 serving.

title: crazy crust apple pie
directions: In a mixing bowl, combine flour, baking powder, salt, sugar, egg, shortening and water.
Blend well.
Beat 2 minutes on medium speed.
Pour batter into 9-inch pie pan.
Combine pie filling, lemon juice and spices; pour into center of batter.
Do not stir. Bake 45 to 50 minutes at 425°.

title: deviled pork chops
directions: Season pork chops with salt, black pepper and red pepper. Heat shortening in skillet; brown chops on both sides.
Add water. Add other ingredients (mixed together) over top of chops.
Cover and cook over slow heat until done.

title: easy cherry cobbler
directions: Pour fruit in casserole dish.
Add water and stir to mix. Sprinkle box of dry cake mix on top evenly.
Pat down.
Cut up margarine on top.
Bake at 350° until slightly brown and bubbly.

title: strawberry gelatin dessert
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in 2 cups boiling water.
Add strawberries, drained pineapple and bananas.
Pour 1/2 mixture into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Freeze 15 to 20 minutes.
Spread with sour cream.
Then pour remainder on top and refrigerate.

title: gram's skillet potatoes
directions: Lightly grease 10-inch skillet and heat on medium-high heat. Layer potatoes, onions and cheese in the skillet, ending with a layer of potatoes on top.
Reduce heat to low and cook for 15 to 20 minutes until done.
Immediately flip potatoes onto a serving plate and serve.
This recipe can be adjusted to fit serving needs.

title: sauerkraut salad
directions: Bring sugar and vinegars to a boil, then chill.
Wash kraut well and drain.
Combine with green pepper, onion, celery and pimento.
Add vinegar-sugar mixture and chill for a couple of hours or overnight.

title: frozen passion
directions: In electric ice cream freezer container, combine ingredients; mix well.
Freeze leftovers.

title: tv nuts and bolts
directions: Melt margarine and add spices.
Spoon over nuts and bolts, stirring from the bottom of pan.
Spread in shallow pan and heat oven to 250°.
Cook 30 to 40 minutes, stirring once or twice. Keeps forever in tins.

title: impossible pumpkin pie
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease pie plate.
Beat all ingredients until smooth (one minute in blender on high for 2 minutes).
Pour into pie plate.
Bake 50-55 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: lemon cheese bars
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients with a fork well.
Mixture will be kind of crumbly. Remove about 1 cup of mixture and set aside. Press the remaining into a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Bake at approximately 350° for 15 minutes.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Drain sweet potatoes.
Mix mashed sweet potatoes, 1 cup sugar, salt, 1/3 stick margarine, milk, butter and eggs (beaten) together. Pour into 1 1/2 to 2-quart casserole dish.
Sprinkle with topping made of brown sugar, flour, margarine and chopped pecans.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes or until topping turns light brown.

title: homemade applesauce
directions: Heat apples and water over medium heat to boiling. Reduce heat. Simmer 5 to 10 minutes or until tender, stirring occasionally. Stir in brown sugar, cinnamon and nutmeg. Heat to boiling 1 to 2 minutes, then mash. Makes 4 cups applesauce.

title: sloppy joes
directions: Brown meat, onion and pepper.
Add chili sauce, catsup and sugar.
Cook on low heat for 2 hours.

title: salsa dip
directions: Spread sour cream evenly on bottom of serving dish.
Spread salsa, then tomatoes, green peppers and cheese.
Serve with nacho chips.

title: chicken paillards with rosemary
directions: Flatten each chicken breast half into a paillard as follows: Carefully remove the tendon.
Put each breast half between two sheets of waxed paper and flatten with a meat pounder to a thickness of 1/8 inch or even less.
The paillards can be cooked right away or frozen.
To freeze, stack between sheets of waxed paper, then wrap in a plastic bag.

title: peach pie alaska
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water.
Add ice cream by spoonfuls. Stir until melted and smooth.
Blend in whipped topping and fruit.
Chill, if necessary, until mixture will mound.
Spoon into crust.
Chill about 3 hours or freeze until firm.
Garnish with peach slices.

title: crain's sunday pot roast
directions: Spray large roasting pan with Pam.
Place tri tip or roast in pan.
Top with sausage, cut in 4-inch pieces.
Pour barbecue sauce over all.
Cover tightly with lid or foil.
Bake at 275° or 300° for at least 4 hours or longer.

title: italian chicken
directions: Saute chicken in butter in skillet.
Reduce heat when fully cooked.
Sprinkle with Italian seasoning and garlic salt.
Add mushrooms, onion and diced tomato.
Simmer and top with cheese. Serve over rice (optional).

title: german apple cake
directions: Combine the first three ingredients and set aside. In a large mixing bowl beat eggs and sugar.
Combine oil and orange juice. Add alternating with dry ingredients to egg and sugar mixture. Mix until smooth.
Add vanilla and beat well.
Pour half of the batter into a greased and floured tube pan.
Arrange half of the apples over the batter.

title: souperior meat loaf
directions: Combine all ingredients, shape into loaf.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Microwave 25 minutes on High.
Let stand 5 minutes.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Combine sweet potatoes, sugar, eggs, vanilla, milk and 1/2 cup melted butter.
Beat with electric mixer until smooth and spoon into greased 2-quart shallow casserole.
Combine brown sugar, flour, 1/3 cup unmelted butter and pecans.
Sprinkle over top of casserole.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: spring salad
directions: Cook macaroni and drain.
Drain all vegetables.
(May also use cauliflower, broccoli, onions.)

title: fish chowder
directions: Cook bacon until crisp in 3-quart pot.
Remove and drain on paper towel.
Discard extra fat.
Put onions in pot; cook 4 or 5 minutes.
Stir in soup, milk and corn.
Bring to a simmer.
Stir in fish and thyme.
Simmer 3 to 4 minutes longer or until fish is translucent.
Sprinkle with bacon.

title: marinated carrots
directions: Use can carrots (or slice your own and cook). Drain and mix all ingredients. Add carrots. Refrigerate for 24 hours before eating. Will keep 2 weeks in refrigerator.

title: pineapple bake(goes great with baked ham)
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Beat in eggs.
Add bread, then add pineapple.
Bake in a 1-quart baking dish at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: texas yum yum cake
directions: Mix and press into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake until golden at 350°.

title: brownie cupcakes
directions: Melt together chocolate and butter.
Add flour, sugar, eggs, vanilla and nuts.
Pour into greased or paper-lined cupcake tins. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: greek salad
directions: Place lettuce, tomatoes, onion and cucumber in large serving bowl; toss to combine. Combine parsley and next 7 ingredients, stirring with a whisk. Add dressing, cheese, olives and peppers to lettuce mixture. Toss gently to coat. Serves 6 to 8.

title: broccoli and cauliflower salad
directions: Mix all ingredients and let set overnight.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Melt butter.
Mix butter with Veg-All, onion, mayonnaise and cheese.
Pour into casserole dish.
Crush stack of Ritz crackers and pour on top of casserole.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Place uncooked chicken breasts in a 9 x 13-inch pan. Place 1 slice of cheese over chicken. Mix the wine, soup and sour cream together. Spread over cheese. Melt butter and mix croutons. Sprinkle croutons over chicken. Bake for 325° for 1 hour. Serve over rice.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Mix all ingredients together and bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: potatoes for a crowd
directions: Combine ingredients and place in 9 x 14-inch pan.
Bake at 300° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: tom's blue cheese dip
directions: Mix first six ingredients together.
Crumble cheese into small pieces and add to mixture.
Good with hard pretzels, chips or raw vegetables.

title: lasagna
directions: Remove sausage from casing.
Chop the meat.
In large saucepan, saute sausage, beef, onion and garlic until brown.
Add sugar, 1 tablespoon salt, basil, fennel, pepper and half of parsley.
Mix well.
Add tomatoes, tomato paste and 1/2 cup water. Bring to a boil and simmer covered for 1 1/2 hours.

title: baked cabbage
directions: Layer half of cabbage in a 2-quart casserole.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Add remaining cabbage and salt and pepper.
Mix flour and cream and pour over cabbage.
Lay bacon over the top.
Cover and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Remove cover and bake 10 minutes more.

title: rice casserole
directions: In greased oblong baking dish, put rice, liquids and celery. Dot with margarine and sprinkle with paprika.
Cook at 350° for 1 hour.

title: sicilian meat roll
directions: Combine eggs, bread crumbs, tomato juice, parsley, oregano, salt and pepper; mix well.
Add beef; mix well.
On waxed paper or foil, pat meat to a 12 x 10-inch rectangle.
Arrange ham on top of meat leaving a small margin around edges.
Sprinkle shredded cheese over ham.
Starting from short end, carefully roll up meat using paper to lift.
Seal edges and ends.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/4 hours.

title: spinach lasagna
directions: Cook lasagna noodles according to package directions.
Mix together all remaining ingredients, except Parmesan cheese and spaghetti sauce and Mozzarella cheese.
Using 9 x 11-inch baking dish, pour a small amount of spaghetti sauce on bottom.
Layer with 1/2 lasagna noodles.
Next layer with 1/2 spinach mix.
Next layer with 1/2 package Mozzarella cheese.
Repeat.
End with sauce; sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 350° covered for 45 minutes.
Uncover and continue baking for 15 minutes.

title: lemon pie
directions: Mix undiluted lemonade and milk with a wire whip.
Add Cool Whip.
Pour into shell; garnish with grated lemon rind.
Cool 4 hours before serving.

title: italian ziti
directions: In a large pot pour in water, ziti and cooking oil.
Cook on a medium heat until ziti is soft.
In a frying pan spray cooking spray and put on a low heat.
Add to the ground beef, salt and pepper and place in frying pan.
Cook in pan until meat is brown. Drain meat and ziti once both are cooked.
Add meat to ziti.
Pour spaghetti sauce over meat and ziti.
Mix.
Serves 4 to 5 people.

title: rice salad
directions: Blend all ingredients and chill.

title: hello dollies
directions: Melt butter in a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Sprinkle graham cracker crumbs, then coconut, then chocolate bits, then walnuts over the butter.
Pour milk over it and bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes. Top will be brown.
Let cool and cut into squares.

title: chicken parmigiana
directions: Flatten chicken breasts.
Dip in egg and bread crumbs.
Brown on both sides.
Pour spaghetti sauce in baking dish.
Place chicken on sauce.
Top with Parmesan cheese and Mozzarella slices. Bake 15 minutes at 350° or until cheese is melted.

title: waldorf salad
directions: In small mixing bowl, sprinkle lemon juice over apples and toss lightly to combine.
Add celery, raisins and mayonnaise and mix until thoroughly coated.
Cover with plastic wrap and refrigerate until chilled, about 30 minutes.

title: rum cake
directions: Mix first 9 ingredients until velvety; stir in 1 cup nuts and 1/2 cup coconut.
Grease Bundt pan and dust with sugar.
In bottom of pan, scatter 2 tablespoons of pecans and 2 tablespoons of coconut.
Pour cake mix into pan.
Bake for 1 hour at 325°. Cool 5 minutes and turn out on plate and glaze.

title: soft no sugar cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Drop by teaspoon on cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: peanut butter chocolate pie
directions: Pour milk in large bowl; add pudding mix.
Beat until well blended, about 1 minute.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Fold in Cool Whip and candies.
Spoon into crust.
Freeze about 6 hours or overnight.
Let stand 10 minutes to soften before serving.
Keep in freezer.

title: boiling-water pastry
directions: Put shortening in bowl and gradually add water, creaming with fork until well mixed. Add flour and salt.
For one 2-crust 8-inch or 9-inch pie or two shells.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Combine soup, milk, soy sauce and pepper in a 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Stir in 1/2 can French fried onions.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes or until hot and bubbling.
Stir.
Top with remaining onions, then bake for 5 more minutes.

title: stir-fry
directions: Steam carrots.
Drain and save liquid.
Saute garlic and ginger in 1 tablespoon oil for 5 minutes.
Then discard garlic and ginger and retain oil.
Stir in mushrooms and water chestnuts and add tofu.
Saute for a few minutes.
Drain juice and save.
Simmer a few more minutes.
Put snow peas on top of tofu, followed by carrots and green onions.
Simmer until snow peas are done.
Boil sauce ingredients, last 5 on list, stirring constantly until done. Pour over vegetables and serve right away over rice.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Chill. Serve on crackers.

title: b. j.'s favorite rice
directions: Cook rice according to directions.
Mix in both cans of soup and serve with pork chops, meat loaf, etc.

title: mississippi mud cake
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients as any other cake.
Pour into a 13 x 9-inch pan and bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
When cake is done, cover top with marshmallows.
Pour icing over top.

title: strawberry cream pie
directions: Hull berries and set aside. Combine pie filling mix, sour cream, milk, rind and 2 cups of the whipped topping in bowl.

Beat with wire whisk until well blended, about 1 minute. Spoon half the filling into crust. Arrange berries stem down in filling and press down. Top with remaining filling. Freeze 1 hour or chill in refrigerator 3 hours before serving. Garnish with remaining whipped topping and additional strawberries, if desired.

title: fruit cobbler
directions: Mix pineapple and cherries in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle cake mix over fruit.
Scatter top with nuts.
Cut oleo into pieces and place on top.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: green bean casserole
directions: One large bunch:
Discard the long stems and hard pieces and any parts that are too old looking.
Wash 4 to 5 times or until they are free of grit and trash.
Last wash, lay them straight on each other, then roll up a handful and shred or cut them across the leaves.
This is the mustard and collards.
The turnip roots should be peeled and cut in quarters or half, depending on how large they are, then twist the tops to tear them.

title: lasagna roll-ups
directions: Cook noodles and then cut in half.
Prepare lasagna.
Drain. In medium bowl blend Ricotta cheese, eggs, Parmesan cheese, salt, pepper and garlic powder.
Stir in thawed and cooked spinach and 2 cups of Mozzarella cheese.
Spread Ricotta mixture evenly on lasagna strips.
Roll up each strip.

title: cheese potato casserole
directions: Let hash browns partially thaw out.
Place in greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix in other ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: mint brownies
directions: Cream margarine, sugar, eggs, vanilla and peppermint flavoring. Mix together flour, salt and cocoa.
Add flour, salt and cocoa to creamed mixture.
Bake in glass casserole dish for 30 minutes at 350° and let it cool before icing.

title: banana bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour a 9-inch angel food pan.
Beat together oil and sugar in a large bowl.
Add egg and vanilla and blend well.
Sift together flour, soda and salt.
Stir into batter.
Add nuts and bananas.
Bake in preheated oven at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: fruit cocktail cake
directions: Sift together flour, sugar, salt and soda.
Into this, blend eggs, fruit cocktail and vanilla.
Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: cherry cake
directions: Mix sugar, salt and shortening.
Beat in egg yolks, flour, vanilla, baking soda and milk.
Add stiffly beaten egg whites. Fold in cherries.
Grease and flour 2 cake pans (round).
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: crawfish salad
directions: Combine mayonnaise, French dressing, chili sauce, salt, pickles, celery seed, Worcestershire, horseradish, parsley, Tabasco and Paul Prudhomme seafood seasoning.
Mix well.
Add chopped eggs and crawfish tails.
Mix well.
Place lettuce on 4 to 6 salad plates.
Spoon crawfish mixture on top.
Garnish with tomato wedges and avocado slices.

title: chocolate oatmeal bars
directions: Cream butter and sugar; beat in egg yolks.
Add flour and oats.
Mix well.
Spread in greased and floured pan (13 x 9-inch).
Bake for 20 minutes at 350°.
Cool 10 minutes.
Melt chocolate chips and spread over bars.
Sprinkle with nuts.

title: lasagna
directions: Saute hamburg and garlic in oil.
Add next 5 items and simmer 20 minutes.
Cook noodles in boiling water for 7 minutes.
Drain. Beat Ricotta with eggs.
Fill 2 large buttered casserole dishes with alternating layers of noodles, Mozzarella, Ricotta mix, tomato meat sauce and Parmesan cheese.
End with top layer of meat sauce and Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes, covered.

title: swiss cheese egg bake
directions: Fold drained bread into eggs and cook until soft set.
Fold into greased 8 x 8-inch baking dish and sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Cover with Swiss cheese slices and sprinkle with bacon. Bake at 400° for 15 minutes.
Can be made the day before. Doubling the recipe fills 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: breakfast chocolate gravy
directions: Mix cocoa, flour and sugar.
Stir in liquid.
Cook until it boils.
Remove from stove.
Add butter; stir.

title: blueberry cream pie
directions: Whip cream cheese in one bowl. Whip whipping cream in another bowl.
Add sugar and vanilla to cream cheese and whip.
Fold cream into cheese mixture. Pour mixture into pie shell and pour pie filling on top.
Any flavor pie filling will work.
Chill and enjoy.

title: chicken with parsley sauce and broccoli with lemon butter
directions: Season chicken with salt and pepper.
Melt butter in broiler-proof baking dish large enough to hold chicken in single layer.
Turn chicken in butter to coat.
Arrange skin side down in baking dish; broil in preheated broiler about 6 inches from heat source for 5 minutes.
Remove from broiler and turn skin side up. Return to broiler about 5 minutes.
Mix remaining ingredients. Sprinkle evenly over chicken; baste well with butter.
Bake in 400° oven for 10 minutes or until tender.
Just before serving, reheat broiler.
Place chicken briefly under broiler to brown. Makes 4 servings.

title: walnut glory cake
directions: In a mixing bowl, beat egg yolks until slightly thickened. Gradually add 3/4 cup sugar, beating until thick and lemon colored. Beat in vanilla. Combine the flour, cinnamon and salt. Add to batter and beat until smooth. In another mixing bowl, beat egg whites on medium speed until soft peaks form. Add remaining sugar 1 tablespoon at a time, beating on high until stiff peaks form. Fold 1/4 of the egg whites into batter. Fold in remaining egg whites. Fold in nuts. Spoon into a greased 10-inch tube pan. Bake at 350° for 50 minutes or until cake
springs back. Cool. Run knife around cake. Remove from pan.

title: hamburger pilaf
directions: Brown the meat, then add the onion and garlic.
Cover and let steam 15 minutes.
Stir in chili sauce and powder.
Add the remaining ingredients; cover.
Let cook 20 minutes.
Red pepper flakes can be added to increase spiciness.

title: corn casserole
directions: Melt the first 3 ingredients in top of double boiler.
Add green chilies and corn.
Sprinkle top with grated cheese or bread crumbs.

title: sausage casserole
directions: Cook
sausage over medium heat until done, stirring and crumbling well.
Drain
on	paper towel and set aside.
Spread each slice	of bread with oleo. Cut bread into cubes and place in a 13
x
9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle with sausage and top with
cheese. Combine remaining ingredients and pour over mixture. Bake in preheated oven at 350° for 1 hour. Serve hot.

title: rhubarb crunch
directions: Arrange rhubarb in a 10-inch greased baking dish.
Mix other ingredients until crumbly and sprinkle this mixture over the rhubarb.
Bake about 40 minutes in a 375° oven.
Serve warm or cold.

title: lemonade pie
directions: Mix lemonade concentrate, Eagle Brand milk and Cool Whip together.
Pour into graham cracker crust.
Refrigerate overnight to blend flavors.
Refrigerate any leftovers.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Mix sugar, milk and butter in saucepan and bring to a rolling boil.
Boil for 5 minutes.
Remove from heat and add peanut butter and marshmallow.
Mix well.
Stir in flour, mixing well.
Pour into a well-greased 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: sausage bread
directions: Brown sausage and onion.
Do not drain.
Combine all other ingredients in large bowl.
Add sausage and onion.
Mix well. Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cook in 350° oven for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: holiday relish
directions: Stir can of cranberry sauce in a large bowl.
Peel orange and remove all white pith you can.
Cut orange into small sections. Add to cranberry sauce.
Add raisins and nuts to the mix.
Pour into a pretty bowl and chill at least one hour.
Keeps in the refrigerator 2 weeks to 1 month.
I freeze leftovers from holiday to holiday.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: pocket bread
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients and let stand 10 to 15 minutes. Add salt, flours and oil.
Mix 5 minutes.
Let rise.
Punch down; divide into 12 sections.
Roll each out.
Let rise 20 minutes. Place on wire mesh in oven and bake at 475° for 5 minutes.

title: sweet cucumber pickles
directions: Slice cucumbers.
Soak in lime water to cover for 12 hours, then wash in tap water.
Soak cucumbers for 4 hours in salt water, then wash in tap water.
Soak for 2 hours in tap water.
Mix alum in water and bring cucumbers to a boil, then wash well.
Put cucumbers in pot with vinegar, sugar and spices.
Put spices in a bag.
Heat until hot.
Put in hot sterile jars and seal.

title: grandma's salmon and rice
directions: Heat skillet on med-high heat until hot. Add bacon drippings and eggs. Mix well. Add salmon. Mix and separate salmon well. Add onion. Salt and pepper to taste. Turn heat down to med-low and simmer for about 15 minutes, stirring frequently to prevent scorching. Serve with, or over rice.

title: lazy day lasagna
directions: Mix Ricotta and Mozzarella cheeses with eggs, parsley, onion powder, basil and pepper.
Brown and drain chuck.
Cover bottom of 12 x 8 x 2-inch pan with thin layer of spaghetti sauce.
Layer half of noodles, then spread cheese mixture on top.
Combine remaining spaghetti sauce with ground beef.
Place remaining noodles on cheese mixture, then pour sauce with beef on top.
Pour water around edges.
Cover with foil and bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.
Let stand 15 minutes before serving.

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: Cut chicken breasts into bite-size pieces.
Saute in 1 tablespoon oil with onion, pepper and cilantro until tender.
Add beans.
Mix.
Mix enchilada and tomato sauces in small bowl. Cover bottom of 13 x 9-inch pan with small amount of sauce. Divide chicken mixture into 10 servings.
Place in tortillas and roll.
Place rolls in pan; cover with remaining sauce and cheese. Bake 25 to 30 minutes at 350°.
Serve with sour cream.

title: lo-cal gratin potatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Spray 10-inch gratin dish or pie plate with Pam.
Layer 1/3 of potatoes, overlapping slices (spiral). Over potatoes, sprinkle 1 tablespoon flour and top with sliced onion.
Dust with cayenne and 1/2 teaspoon paprika.
Layer another third potatoes.
Add remaining flour, black pepper and 1 tablespoon Parmesan.
Top with remaining potatoes.
Pour evaporated milk over gratin; add remaining cheeses and paprika. Cover with foil and bake for 45 minutes.
Remove foil; lower oven to 350° and bake 15 minutes more.
Set for 10 minutes; garnish with parsley.

title: silver dollar rolls
directions: Pour boiling water over sugar, shortening and salt in mixing bowl.
Cool to lukewarm and add yeast, softened in 1/4 cup water. Add beaten egg or egg yolks and mix well.
Add about half the flour and beat until smooth.
Add remaining flour and stir to mix thoroughly.
Cover and let rise in warm place until doubled, approximately 1 hour.
Stir down and fill greased muffin pans half full.
Cover and let rise until doubled, approximately 1/2 hour. Bake at 375° to 400° for 15 to 20 minutes.
When baked, brush tops with melted butter.

title: grandma's coconut custard pie
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Beat eggs until fluffy.
Add sugar, milk and vanilla.
Beat again until fluffy.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Sprinkle with nutmeg and 1 cup coconut.
Bake 10 minutes at 450°.
Reduce to 350°.
Bake 35 minutes more until knife inserted comes out clean.
Cool on rack.

title: cocoa krispies marshmallow treats
directions: Melt margarine in large saucepan over low heat.
Add marshmallows; stir until completely melted.

Remove from heat. Add Kellogg's Cocoa Krispies cereal; stir until well coated. Using buttered spatula or wax paper, press mixture evenly into a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan coated with cooking spray. Cut into squares when cool.
Yields 24 (2 x 2-inch) treats.

title: chicken tetrazzini
directions: Cook and drain spaghetti.
Melt the butter and then add mushrooms.
