Cook 5 minutes and season with nutmeg and salt.

title: orange salad
directions: Add
water
to
pudding and jello and cook until thick; cool. Add
oranges
to
cooled
tapioca
mixture.
Whip Dream Whip. Fold into tapioca mixture.
Pour into mold or cake pan. Serve topped with Dream Whip, if desired.

title: dirty cake
directions: Crumble cookies.
Make them into dirt.
Melt butter and put 3/4 cookie crumbs into pan.
Press it down.
Spread butter on top. Mix powdered sugar, cream cheese and 1 Cool Whip and pour on top of crumbs.
Mix pudding as directed and pour on top of cream cheese.
Spread other Cool Whip on top.
Take rest of crumbs and spread on top.

title: casserole
directions: Combine meat, salt, egg, 1/2 can tomato sauce, Italian seasoning and 1/2 can French fried onions.

title: fourteen day pickles
directions: 1st day - boil salt and water and pour over cucumbers.

title: perfect blueberry cake
directions: Cream together shortening and sugar.
Add egg yolks, vanilla and milk.
Add flour, baking powder and salt.
Fold in beaten egg whites. Lightly fold in blueberries that have been floured.
Bake in 8-inch square pan.
Sprinkle top with sugar before baking. Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: fruit dip
directions: Beat ingredients with electric mixer until well blended. Serve with assorted fruits.

title: ranch burgers
directions: Mix Hidden Valley dressing mix into ground beef.
Mix well. Form into patties and grill or broil until done.

title: broccoli chicken
directions: Boil chicken until it comes off bones easily.
Cool and debone.
Cook broccoli as directed on package, then drain.
Spread over bottom of large casserole dish.
Place chicken over broccoli and season with salt or pepper.

title: mike's famous pumpkin pie
directions: Mix pumpkin, eggs, brown sugar, salt, cinnamon, ginger, cloves and milk in this order.
Preheat oven to 425°.

title: russian tea
directions: Boil 1 cup of water.
Put in cloves.
Cover and remove from heat.
Let sit until other ingredients are assembled.

title: green bean salad
directions: Drain liquid off beans, peas and corn.
Mix all ingredients except oil, vinegar and sugar.
Mix sugar, vinegar and oil.
Heat to dissolve sugar.
When this has cooled, add Wesson oil and pour over mixture and other ingredients.
Place in refrigerator for 24 hours.
Drain off liquid and serve.

title: earthquake cake
directions: Grease 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle nuts and coconut in pan. Prepare cake mix as directed on box.
Pour over nuts and coconut. Melt butter, cream cheese and powdered sugar.
Pour over cake mix. Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: kentucky buttermilk cake
directions: You will need roses and baby's breath for garnish.

title: easy cheesecake
directions: Beat cream cheese until fluffy.
Gradually add sugar and vanilla.
Beat in eggs one at a time.
Stir in sour cream.
Pour into graham cracker crust.
Bake in preheated moderate (350°) oven for 60 to 70 minutes, or until halfway into the center is firm. Turn off oven.
Leave door slightly ajar; allow cheesecake to remain in the oven for 1 hour.
Cool.
Chill 4 hours or overnight. Top with cherry (or fruit of choice) pie filling.
This is very rich and a small piece is all that most people want!

title: chicken noodle soup
directions: Boil all ingredients with 8-10 cups water for 2 hours on low heat.
Strain.
Remove chicken breast and any other edible chicken pieces.
Chop the chicken.
In small saucepan, melt 2 tbsp butter. Add then chopped chicken and add pinch of garlic powder, onion, salt, black pepper, thyme and basil.
Saute until slightly browned.
Add 2 Tbsp. tomato sauce (and some more butter if needed).
Saute and add boiled macaroni noodle.
Saute another minute until macaroni is well coated with butter and tomato mixture.
Add to strained soup and slowly cook for 15 minutes.

title: dog biscuits
directions: Mix in separate bowl the eggs, molasses, oil, hot water and tomato sauce.
Mix all ingredients.
Roll out on floured surface with cookie cutters.
Bake in oven at 425° for 15 minutes.
Feed to dog.

title: pie crust
directions: Mix flour and salt and cut in Crisco as for pie dough.
Beat egg in cup; add enough water to make 1 cup of liquid, also add vinegar to cup.
Then add egg to flour mixture.
Dough will be soft and sticky.
Make 4 or 5 balls and put in freezer to use as needed or can be used immediately.
Chill for 20 to 25 minutes, then roll out and bake.

title: chocolate frosting
directions: Combine melted margarine, cocoa and salt, then add milk and vanilla.
Mix in sugar in 3 parts.

title: raw broccoli salad
directions: Wash broccoli and cut flowerets into bite size pieces.
Save the stalks and cook for another dish or soup.
Drain thoroughly. Place broccoli in a large bowl.
Add olives, eggs, onion, relish, lemon juice and enough mayonnaise to bind salad together.
Chill. The salad is better made the night before serving.
Yield:
8 servings.

title: tasty ovals
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Spread on bread slices.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes.

title: western beans
directions: Set electric skillet at 340°.
Cook and stir ground beef, onion, celery and green pepper until meat is brown and vegetables tender.
Drain off excess fat.
Dissolve bouillon cube in hot water.
Stir bouillon and remaining ingredients into meat mixture. Cover and simmer 15 minutes or until hot and bubbly.
Crumble bacon and sprinkle over beans.
Makes 6 servings.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream together shortening, sugars and eggs.
Add remaining ingredients one at a time, mixing well after each addition.
Add flour last and drop dough by tsp. on an ungreased cookie sheet.

title: baked pineapple
directions: Combine and bake at 350° about 1 hour.

title: perfect peppermint patties
directions: In a bowl, combine first four ingredients. Add milk and mix well. Roll into 1-inch balls and place on a waxed paper-lined cookie sheet. Chill for 20 minutes. In a double boiler or microwave-safe bowl, melt chocolate chips and shortening. Dip patties. Place on waxed paper to harden.

title: cherry salad
directions: Beat cream cheese until smooth.
Add sour cream, sugar and salt.
Mix well.
Fold in marshmallows and pecans.
Drain all the fruits.
Save a few for garnish.
Add the fruits to the cheese mixture.
Stir.
Chill 4 to 6 hours.
It can be frozen and slices. Serves 10.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: In a mixing bowl, beat the shortening and margarine or butter with an electric mixer on medium to high speed for 30 seconds. Add about half of the flour, the brown sugar, sugar, eggs, vanilla and baking soda.
Beat mixture until thoroughly combined.
Beat in the remaining flour.
Stir in chocolate pieces and, if desired, nuts.
Drop dough by rounded teaspoonfuls 2 inches apart onto an ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake in a 375° oven for 8 to 10 minutes or until edges are lightly browned.

title: barbecue pork chops
directions: Place pork chops in pan.
Pour over the chops the remaining ingredients (in the order given).
Cover the pan with aluminum foil tightly around the edges.
Cook in oven at 425° for 1 hour. Keep the chops turned over while cooking.

title: fancy chicken log
directions: Beat
together
softened
cream cheese, steak sauce and curry powder.
Blend
in
chicken,
celery
and 2 tablespoons parsley. Refrigerate remaining parsley.
Shape mixture into a 9-inch
log. Wrap
in plastic wrap and chill 4 hours or overnight.
Toss together remaining parsley and almonds; coat log. Serve with party crackers.
Makes about 3 cups.

title: delicious pound cake
directions: Mix in order listed.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour or until done. Grease pan and line with wax paper.

title: crock-pot roast beef
directions: Coat roast with flour.
Place in crock-pot.
Combine soup mix, gravy mix, ginger ale and remaining flour in bowl; mix well.
Add to crock-pot.
Cook on low for 8 to 10 hours or until roast is tender. Yield: 6 servings.

title: ham bake
directions: Combine cooked rice, ham, celery, peas and onions.
Dilute soup with milk; stir in ham mixture.
Pour in 9 x 13-inch baking dish. Mix cracker crumbs and melted butter and sprinkle on top.
Bake 40 minutes at 350°.
Let set 10 minutes before serving.

title: lib's chicken
directions: Mix chicken, boiled eggs, celery, onion, rice, soups, mayonnaise and lemon juice.
Mix all ingredients well.
In a saucepan melt one stick of margarine; add cracker crumbs and sliced almonds.
Set aside.
Put chicken mixture in 2 casserole dishes and top with cracker mixture.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: "easy and best dessert"
directions: Put pie filling in casserole baking dish.
Top with chopped pecans.
Top with cake mix.
Dice butter on top.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes, until brown.
Serve warm with vanilla ice cream.

title: crab bisque ii
directions: In medium saucepan, combine all ingredients; mix well.
Cook uncovered over medium heat for 5 to 10 minutes or until thoroughly heated and flavors are blended.
Remove bay leaf.

title: monkey bread
directions: Combine sugar and cinnamon.
Melt butter.
Roll each slightly thawed roll in butter, then in sugar and cinnamon mixture.
Place in well buttered Bundt pan and let rise overnight.
Brush tops with butter before baking as it will dry out slightly overnight. Bake for 20 minutes at 350°.

title: broccoli supreme
directions: Prepare broccoli and cut in small pieces.
Cook until crisp-tender.
Blend together soup and flour, then add sour cream, carrots, onion, salt and pepper.
Carefully stir in broccoli. Turn into 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Combine stuffing mix and melted butter.
Put on top of broccoli mixture.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes or until heated through.

title: taco pie
directions: Brown and drain beef.
Combine with remaining ingredients, except corn chips and cheese.
Spoon mixture over 2 cups of corn chips in casserole.
Crush remaining corn chips.
Sprinkle casserole with corn chips and cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: hamburger gravy
directions: Brown hamburger meat and drain. Add soup, water, salt and pepper. Cook on medium for about 5 minutes.

title: dukes mixture
directions: Fry ground beef, onion, salt and pepper.
Cook soup beans and 2 cups water.
When meat and onion are browned add to soup mixture and simmer about 15 minutes.

title: western baked beans
directions: Brown beef and add rest of ingredients.
Bake 45 minutes at 350° in covered casserole.

title: sweet and sour sauce(for chicken and pork tenderloins)
directions: Mix all ingredients together and heat, stirring occasionally until it thickens.
(You can add more chicken broth for a thinner sauce.)
I cook chicken and pork tenderloin in chicken broth with seasonings.
I let the meat sit out for 1/2 hour to cool before cutting.

title: lemon pie
directions: Mix 1/2 cup sugar and the flour together.
Add egg yolks, juice from lemon and grated rind.
Cook in double boiler until thick.
Beat egg whites real stiff; add remaining 1/2 cup sugar. Blend approximately 1/3 of the egg whites into yolk mixture.
Pour into baked pie shell; top with remainder of egg whites.
Brown in oven at 375°.

title: jalapeno cornbread with meat
directions: Combine cornmeal, milk, eggs, salt, soda, bacon grease and corn.
Mix well.
Brown meat until crumbly; drain well on a paper towel.
Pour half the corn meal batter into well greased skillet or baking dish.
Sprinkle with cheese, then cooked meat, diced onion and chopped jalapenos.
Top with remaining batter.
Bake for about 50 minutes in a preheated oven.

title: bean soup
directions: Cover beans with cold water and soak overnight.
Drain and recover with water.
Add the ham hock and simmer slowly for about 4 hours, until the beans are cooked tender.
Season with salt and pepper as desired.
Just before serving, bruise or mash beans with a large spoon to cloud the soup.

title: easy cobbler
directions: In a glass 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan, melt margarine in oven at 350°.
Combine milk, flour and sugar in bowl.
When margarine has melted, take out of oven.
Pour your mixture into glass pan.
Add your favorite fruit.
Bake for 45 minutes, or until brown.

title: aunt martha's casserole
directions: Cook and drain noodles.
Saute meat until brown; drain grease and add tomato sauce.
Remove from heat.
Mix together cottage and cream cheese, sour cream, onions and peppers.

title: champagne punch
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in water.
Add thawed lemonade.
Pour mixture in large punch bowl with ice block.
Slowly pour in ginger ale and champagne.

title: marjorie's sweet pickles
directions: Drain pickles well, cut in wedges and put back in original jars.
Mix next 3 ingredients.
Heat to boiling; pour over pickles.
Seal and turn upside down for a day or two.

title: frozen chocolate mint squares
directions: In 3-cup bowl combine wafers and margarine.
Press mixture firmly onto bottom of container.
In medium mixing bowl beat the marshmallow cream, mint extract and green food color with an electric mixer on medium speed until smooth.
Fold in 1/2 cup of the semi-sweet chocolate pieces.

title: dried sweet corn
directions: Mix all in a kettle; heat for about 30 minutes.
Keep stirring to prevent burning.
Put on a dryer, or it can be fried in the oven for several hours on a cookie sheet with oven on very lowest temperature until dry.

title: potatoes o'brien
directions: Combine ingredients.
Cover with foil and brown at 350° for 1 hour.

title: lemon custard or lemon dainty
directions: Combine margarine with salt, sugar and flour.
Mix well. Grate rind of lemon, squeeze lemon and separate eggs.
Combine egg yolks, milk, juice and rind of lemon.
Beat egg whites until stiff.
Combine egg yolk mixture with sugar, flour and margarine mixture. Fold in egg whites gently.
Pour into greased baking dish. Set in pan of hot water.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes. Serve warm.

title: apple pie
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Melt butter in an oblong baking dish.
In a pan, heat sugar and water until sugar melts.
Cut shortening into flour until fine.
Add milk and stir until soft dough forms. Pour on a floured surface and knead until smooth.
Roll out dough in a long shape, 1/4-inch thick.
Pour apples over dough and sprinkle with cinnamon.
Roll dough up like a jelly roll; dampen edges and seal.
Cut 16 slices in top.
Place dough in pan and pour sugar water over this.
Bake one hour.

title: new years soup number 10
directions: Cook 30 minutes; then add last 1 bag fresh spinach, chopped.

title: pistachio salad
directions: Fold into Cool Whip and let cool.

title: lemon bars
directions: Mix butter, flour, 1/2 cup plus 2 tablespoons sugar until crumbly.
Pat in cake pan.
Prick with fork.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until golden brown.
Beat eggs.
Add 2 cups sugar and lemon juice.
Pour over crust while still hot.
Bake 20 minutes more.
Sprinkle top with powdered sugar.

title: tater tots
directions: Pour melted butter in 9x13 baking dish.
Spread tater tots in dish.
Mix onions, sour cream and soup together and spread over tater tots.
Spread cheese over and top with the corn flakes.

title: dressing
directions: Toss breads in seasoning.
Saute celery and onion in margarine until tender.
Pour over bread.
Moisten with broth.
Put in casserole dish and bake at 325° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: chocolate chip pound cake
directions: Sift powdered sugar.
Mix cake mix and next 2 ingredients. Stir with a wire whisk to remove large lumps.
Add 3/4 cup of oil. Add water, eggs and sour cream.
Stir until smooth.
Stir in chocolate morsels.
Pour batter into a greased and floured pan. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Cool in pan on wire rack for 10 minutes. Remove from pan.
Sprinkle with sifted powdered sugar.

title: hot chocolate mix
directions: Mix together with wire whisk in a large bowl.
Put in 1/2 pint jars or any size jar.
Label jars:
1/3 cup mix to 1 cup water.
A warm treat for you!
Put a 6-inch cloth or paper circle on jar lid. Tie a ribbon or string around the jar for gift giving.
Enjoy!

title: raspberry applesauce salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water.
Add applesauce.
Stir and refrigerate until set.

title: no-bake disappearing bars
directions: Mix sugar, graham cracker crumbs, peanut butter and margarine in large bowl.
Knead into big ball.
Spread out evenly in 13 x 9-inch ungreased pan.
Spread melted chocolate over top of peanut butter mixture.
Dot with M&M's so when bars are cut each will have an M&M (approximately 35).
Refrigerate 2 hours.
Let sit at room temperature 1/2 hour before cutting.
Keep refrigerated.
Now watch them disappear.

title: lite dessert
directions: Pour strawberries into gelatin mold.
Line Lite Twinkies around mold on top of strawberries.
Place Cool Whip between and around Lite Twinkies.
Cover gelatin mold and place in freezer. Thirty minutes before serving, thaw out to serve.

title: coconut kisses
directions: Mix in order given; drop on greased
tin and bake in slow (325° to 350°) oven until done.

title: pineapple sour cream pound cake
directions: Mix pineapple with soda well.
Mix remaining ingredients and add pineapple mixture.
Beat 4 minutes.
Pour into greased and floured tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 55 minutes.
Cool 15 minutes before turning out of pan.

title: squash casserole
directions: In a 2-quart pan, boil water and bouillon cubes.
Add squash and cook until tender.
In bowl put sour cream, soup, carrots and onion.
Add squash.
Put in a 9 x 9-inch square greased pan.
Top with stuffing and margarine.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes at 350°.

title: 5 flavors cake
directions: Sift flour 3 times.
Cream butter, margarine, Crisco and sugar until fluffy.
Add a little flour; alternate adding milk and eggs until all flour, milk and eggs are used.
Add baking powder.
Add flour.
Grease and flour cake pan.
Cook between 275° and 350° (depending on how fast your oven bakes) until soaked.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Boil sweet potatoes in clear water until tender; peel while warm.
Put in large mixer bowl and on low speed, mash well.
Add butter while potatoes are warm.
Add sugar, eggs, milk and vanilla.
Pour into 9-inch deep pastry shell and bake at 350° until well set and lightly browned, about 45 minutes.

title: my pie shell
directions: Blend flour and Crisco; add water to desired consistency. Roll as thin as you can and be sure to prick the pie shell all over well.
Bake about 10 to 12 minutes, then cool completely.

title: peanut or pecan brittle
directions: Combine sugar, water and Karo. Bring to boil. Stir in nuts gradually so as not to lose boil. Keep at rolling boil until peanuts pop and turn a light brown. Remove from heat. Add soda and salt, stirring well. Pour into a well-greased pan or platter. Allow to spread on its own. Cool at room temperature and break into clumps.

title: cream pralines
directions: In 2 quart saucepan combine sugar, salt, milk and butter.
Stir over low heat until sugar melts.
Increase to medium heat and cook to soft ball stage (234°).
Remove from heat and stir in vanilla. Cool for 5 minutes.
After cooling, stir rapidly until mixture thickens and coats pecans lightly.
Drop quickly on foil from a tablespoon.
If mixture becomes too stiff, add a few drops hot water.
Let candy cool and set before removing from foil.

title: raspberry muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
In medium bowl, mix flour and other dry ingredients.
Stir in undrained raspberries, eggs and vanilla. Thoroughly mix in the oil and nuts.
Spoon into greased muffin cups (12).
They will be very full, but won't run over.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes; cool 5 minutes before removing from tins.

title: stuffed manicotti
directions: Cook manicotti according to package directions.
Drain and set aside.
Brown beef with garlic and salt.
Drain well.
Combine Mozzarella and cottage cheese, mayonnaise and ground beef.
Fill each manicotti shell with the cheese-meat mixture, then place in oblong baking dish.
Cover with spaghetti sauce and sprinkle with oregano and Parmesan cheese.
Cover with aluminum foil and bake 15 minutes at 350°.
Uncover and bake another 10 minutes, or until bubbly.

title: sweet and sour potato salad
directions: Boil potatoes in their jackets.
When tender, peel and slice. Add olives, celery, hard-cooked eggs, onion, pickle and parsley. Fry bacon until crisp and brown.
Beat eggs; add sugar, spices and diluted vinegar.
Mix well.
Pour egg mixture into hot bacon fat; cook, stirring constantly, until thickened.
Pour over potato mixture and mix lightly.
Serve hot.
Makes 6 servings.

title: glazed carrots
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Place carrots in a 9-inch pie pan.
In a small saucepan over moderate heat, melt butter; add onion and cook until lightly browned.
Remove from heat.
Stir in sugar and mustard; blend and spoon over carrots.
Bake, uncovered, 15 minutes or until lightly glazed.

title: blond brownies
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large bowl; mix well.
Spread mixture evenly in a greased 12 x 8-inch baking pan.
Bake in a preheated 350° oven for 25 minutes, or until golden brown.
Makes about 36 bars.

title: gingersnap stew(serves 100)
directions: Brown meat. Add enough water to cover completely. Add onions, bay leaves, salt and pepper, Worcestershire sauce and vinegar. Cook, covered, in oven until meat is tender.
Remove meat. Add vegetables. Cook until tender. Remove vegetables.
Use rolling pin to mash gingersnaps.
Add to juice. Cook on stovetop until thickened. Combine all ingredients. Heat!

title: blue ribbon mincemeat pie
directions: Cook
beef
thoroughly
but do not brown.
Put meat and apples through
food chopper using medium blade.
Combine all ingredients in large kettle.
Simmer for 30 minutes.
Cool and use as needed for pie.
Can freeze any extra for later.

title: hot salsa
directions: Peel and quarter a peck of small tomatoes, add sugar, salt, vinegar, lemon juice, Worcestershire sauce, dry mustard, garlic and basil leaves.
Simmer on stove 45 minutes.
Dice onions, sweet peppers and 8 to 10 hot red peppers.
Add to mixture and return to boil.
Pour into hot jars and seal.
Makes about 10 pints.
More hot peppers may be used if a hotter salsa is desired.

title: ham dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together very well.
Chill.
Take out of refrigerator about 30 minutes before serving.
Good with corn chips.
Makes 1 1/2 cups.

title: salmon cakes
directions: Drain salmon; flake.
Combine ingredients.
Mix well.
Form into 4 or 5 patties.
Pan-fry in a small amount of vegetable oil until lightly browned on both sides.

title: cajun marinade
directions: Mix all together and marinate in a large Ziploc bag.

title: teriyaki
directions: Combine all ingredients except the steak.
Marinate the steak in the mixture for at least 3 hours.
Cook on grill.

title: shrimp "scampi"
directions: Rinse the shrimp in cool water; pat dry.
Mix the olive oil, wine, parsley, garlic, salt and pepper to taste.
Pour over the shrimp in a shallow dish.
Cover and chill for 2 to 3 hours in refrigerator, turning the shrimp once or twice in the marinade.

title: oklahoma fried rice
directions: Cook rice.
Lightly grease a large frying pan.
Cook ham slowly.
In small frying pan, scramble egg until well done.
When eggs are cooked, mix them in with ham and chopped onions.
Mix rice in large frying pan with ham; stir for a few minutes and season with soy sauce to taste.
Whole meat or main dish.

title: belle falls vegetable casserole(heritage)
directions: Layer in a round casserole, peas and carrots.
Cover with mashed potatoes.
Be sure to have a little broth, enough to keep moist.
Good to use leftovers.

title: hot bean dip
directions: In 1 1/2-quart baking dish, layer cream cheese, beans and picante sauce.
Top with cheese.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°. Can be microwaved until thoroughly heated.
Serve with chips.

title: kenny's baked beans
directions: Fry bacon, crumble 4 of the slices and set aside.
Saute onion and green pepper in bacon drippings.
Add ground beef.
Brown and drain.
Combine all ingredients except whole slices of bacon.
Pour into greased shallow casserole dish.
Lay last 4 strips of bacon across bean mixture.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: pineapple casserole
directions: Cream butter and sugar. Add rest of ingredients and mix well. Put into 2-quart casserole dish. Bake at 350° for 1 hour, uncovered.

title: greek salad
directions: Wash romaine lettuce leaves, pat them dry with paper towels and tear into bite size pieces.
Place in a large bowl with cucumber, cheeses and mint; set aside while preparing the dressing.

title: blueberry nut cake
directions: Preheat
oven
Put all ingredients in a large bowl and
stir
until mixed.
Bake in an ungreased 9 x 9-inch pan for 45 to 55 minutes.
Cool and serve.

title: cheesy potato casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients in 9 x 13-inch pan (glass).
Bake 45 minutes in 350° oven.
Makes 10 servings.

title: two bean chili
directions: Cook ground turkey, green pepper, onion with chili powder and pepper until meat is browned and vegetables are tender.
Stirring to separate meat.
Add tomato puree, beans and bring to boil. Reduce heat and simmer for 30 minutes stirring occasionally.

title: hard candy
directions: Stir and cook until hard boil at 300°.
Remove from heat.
Add 2 tablespoons extract (desired flavor).
Add food coloring (as desired).

title: oatmeal crispies
directions: Cream the shortening and sugars.
Add egg and vanilla, then dry ingredients.
Mix well and drop from teaspoon onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake in a 350° oven for 10 minutes.

title: onion casserole
directions: Saute onions in butter until tender.
Line casserole dish with saltines.
Mix together soup, milk and eggs.
Pour onions and butter over saltines, then cover with soup mixture.
Top with grated cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: impossible pie
directions: Mix all ingredients in a bowl.
Pour in a well-buttered pie pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until browned (top and bottom).

title: barbecue beef sandwiches
directions: Cook roast in crock-pot 7 to 8 hours.
Do not add any seasonings to roast while cooking.
Chop roast.
Mix all ingredients for sauce and bring to a boil.
Simmer 15 to 20 minutes.
Add to chopped roast and heat thoroughly.
Serve with hamburger buns.
Makes 8 sandwiches.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix all together in large casserole dish.
Cook at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: whiskey sours
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Makes 1 gallon.

title: boil cookies
directions: Combine sugar, cocoa, butter and milk in saucepan and boil for 1 minute.
Remove from heat and add peanut butter, vanilla and oats.
Stir this mixture well and drop by spoonfuls on wax paper.

title: baked cabbage
directions: Cut cabbage in wedges 3/4-inch thick.
Cook in salt water for 10 minutes.
Drain and place cabbage in a greased casserole. Sprinkle with flour, salt and pepper.
Dot with butter.
Add hot milk and top with grated cheese.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: sweet potatoes supreme
directions: Whip potatoes until smooth.
Add other dry ingredients and mix well.
Beat eggs slightly and add to the mixture with vanilla. Pour into greased baking dish and bake at 300° until firm.
Remove from oven.
Sprinkle marshmallows over top.
Return to oven and bake until brown.

title: frank's mouth watering grilled spareribs
directions: Place ribs on grill over charcoal fire when coals have evenly turned grey.
Brush sauce lightly on ribs.
Cook for 1/2 hour, turning and brushing on sauce frequently.
Add additional sauce to ribs prior to serving.

title: sauerkraut salad
directions: Drain sauerkraut real well. Thoroughly mix all ingredients. Set overnight in refrigerator.
I keep this in a large Mason jar and have a salad available on a moment's notice.

title: easy meat loaf
directions: Mix ingredients except bacon.
Fry bacon lightly, drain and break up.
Cover beef mixture with bacon.
Pour 8 ounces tomato sauce to cover and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: oven glazed chicken
directions: Remove skim from chicken.
In a 2-quart dish, arrange chicken. Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.
Combine remaining ingredients; spoon over chicken.
Bake 30 minutes or until chicken is no longer pink.
Makes 4 servings.

title: appetizers
directions: Add cream to soften cream cheese.
Fill each lychee with cream cheese.
Add 1 almond in the center of each one.
Refrigerate and serve cold.

title: pizza dough
directions: Mix well and rise until double.
Bake at 450° for 15 minutes.

title: fast fruit fluff
directions: Mix Cool Whip and gelatin.
Stir in cottage cheese, nuts and fruit cocktail.
Chill at least 1 hour before serving.

title: 1-2-3-4 cake
directions: Mix sugar and butter until creamy. Add eggs, one at a time. Add flavoring. Add milk and flour alternately. Beat until well blended. Bake at 350°. Makes 3 (9-inch) layers.

title: oreo ice cream dessert
directions: Mix Oreos in blender.
Save half.
Mix half of crumbled Oreos and the oleo or butter (melted).
Put in a 9 x 13-inch dish or pan.
Layer the other ingredients: softened ice cream, fudge topping, peanuts (put in blender) and Cool Whip.
Then add the rest of Oreo mixture.
Freeze and remove from freezer before serving.
Let set out a few minutes to soften.

title: fried pheasant
directions: Mix ingredients in paper bag.
Heat in large heavy skillet over medium gas flame (325° to 350° dial setting on controlled burner), 1/4-inch melted shortening.
Shake in paper bag until each piece is well coated with flour (2 pheasants, cut in serving pieces and skin removed).
Add pheasants to hot fat and brown well on each side. Cover; reduce flame to simmer (200° to 225° dial setting on controlled burner) and cook until tender, about 40 minutes.
Remove cover and continue cooking 5 minutes.
Drain on absorbent paper. Serves 4.

title: turtle soup
directions: Place the turtle or terrapin meat in a large, heavy kettle. Add the scallions and 1 1/2 quarts water.
Simmer together gently for 2 hours.
Remove the meat from the broth and dice.
Return to the broth.
Add 1 quart water, the instant beef broth and salt; simmer for 2 hours longer or until the meat is tender.
Serve hot. The turtle meat was considered a "good medicine" among the Plains Tribes.

title: hominy casserole
directions: Saute pepper and onion in butter. Pour in casserole dish and sprinkle with bread crumbs and cayenne pepper. Bake in 350° oven for 45 minutes.

title: chocolate eclair cake
directions: In large bowl, mix pudding and 3 cups of milk until thickened, then fold in Cool Whip.
In 13 x 9-inch pan, layer first graham crackers (flat) and a layer of pudding, a layer of graham crackers, a layer of pudding and a layer of crackers.
Spread icing over the top.
Refrigerate overnight or at least 8 hours.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Heat applesauce and add soda.
Sift together flour, salt, cinnamon, cloves and allspice.
Mix eggs, shortening and sugar. Add dry ingredients and applesauce.
Add raisins and nuts; mix well.
Bake in a tube pan that has been greased and floured at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: three-in-one ice cream
directions: Pour all ingredients into container of ice cream freezer. Finish filling container with milk.
Makes 1 gallon.

title: sweet potato biscuits
directions: Mix all ingredients and knead a few times.
If possible, refrigerate dough for awhile.
Pat out on a floured surface.
Cut out about 3/4 to 1-inch thick.
Bake at 375° until golden brown, about 15 to 20 minutes.

title: classic lasagne
directions: In
a
large heavy pan, lightly brown beef and onion in oil. Add
tomatoes
(put
through blender or cut with edge of spoon), paste,
water,
parsley,
salt, sugar, garlic powder, pepper
and oregano; simmer, uncovered, stirring occasionally, about
30 minutes.
Meanwhile,
cook
lasagne
as
directed; drain.
Grate Mozzarella cheese.
In a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan,
spread about
cup
sauce.
Then
alternate layers of lasagne, sauce, cottage cheese, Mozzarella cheese and Parmesan cheese,
ending with
sauce,
Mozzarella
cheese and Parmesan cheese.
Bake
for
to 50 minutes, until lightly browned
and bubbling.
Allow to stand for 15 minutes; cut in squares to serve. Serves 8.

title: ham salad for sandwiches
directions: Boil the eggs while putting the other ingredients through a food grinder. Chop eggs and mix well.
Place in a refrigerator until needed.

title: squash pie
directions: Beat eggs; add milk and sugar.
Mash and strain cooked squash. Add salt and spices.
Combine the 2 mixtures and blend well. Fill deep pie shell.
Bake about 10 minutes in a hot 450° oven; reduce temperature to 350° and bake 30 minutes or until custard is set.

title: blueberry cake
directions: In bowl, cream butter until fluffy.
Add sugar gradually, beating until creamy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well.
Add flour, baking powder and salt.
Alternate with combined milk and grated orange rind and vanilla.
Pour into greased and floured 8-inch square pan.
Sprinkle blueberries over the top.
Bake at 350° for 60 minutes until cake begins to shrink from sides and is golden on top.
Cut in squares.

title: brownies
directions: Beat sugar and oil, add eggs and beat.
Add remaining ingredients.
Bake at 325° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: fruit punch
directions: Mix all ingredients thoroughly except fresh strawberries. Chill.
Stir in sliced fresh strawberries when ready to serve.

title: grandma evans' sugar cookies
directions: Beat well first six ingredients.
Fold in dry ingredients. Chill.
Roll into walnut sized balls.
Flatten with a glass.
Bake about 10 minutes or until lightly browned in a 350° oven.

title: russian tea
directions: Mix together and store in canister.
Use 1 to 2 teaspoons per cup of hot water.

title: orange salad
directions: Mix well and refrigerate until congealed.

title: coffee gelatin
directions: Sprinkle gelatin over 1/2 cup of coffee in small saucepan. Stir over low heat until gelatin dissolves.
Add remaining coffee and artificial sweetener.
Pour in bowl, cover and chill until firm.
Serves 4.

title: sour cream cornbread
directions: Melt margarine in 8-inch skillet in 350° oven.
Mix all ingredients until well blended.
Pour batter into hot pan and bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: dill oyster crackers
directions: In a bowl, combine Ranch dressing (original mix) with dill weed and oil.
Place crackers in oven-safe bowl or casserole dish. Pour dressing mixture over crackers. Bake 15 to 20 minutes at 250°.
Stir after 10 minutes.

title: royal mazurek(mazurek krolewski)
directions: Cream butter; sift and add sugar and salt.
Add alternately one egg yolk and a little of the flour mixture until all has been used.
Add almonds.
Bake in two (17 x 11-inch) pans for 20 to 25 minutes at 350°.
Cut when hot.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: microwave caramel corn(excellent)
directions: Combine brown sugar, corn syrup, oleo and salt in a 2-quart bowl.
Bring to a boil for 3 to 4 minutes, then cook 2 minutes on High.
Remove from microwave, then add soda.
Now, put popcorn in a brown grocery bag.
Pour syrup into popcorn.
Roll bag down and cook on High for 1 1/2 minutes.
Remove from microwave and shake it up, then put bag in for another 1 1/2 minutes on High.
Remove and shake again.
Spread on cookie sheet until cool.
Can add pecans, peanuts or walnuts in bag.

title: shepherd's pie
directions: Preheat broiler.
In large skillet, melt margarine.
Add onions and saute until translucent.
Add beef and cook until browned, breaking up meat with spoon.
Add vegetables and seasoning and cook, stirring, about 3 minutes.
Sprinkle flour over beef; cook 1 minute.
Add broth and Worcestershire; simmer 5 minutes.
Stir sour cream into potatoes.
Pour beef mixture into a 9 1/2-inch deep dish pie plate.
Top with potatoes.
Broil 5 to 10 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: breakfast crumb cake
directions: Mix sugar, shortening and 2 cups of the flour.
Take out 2 fistfuls for the crumbs.
Add milk, egg, 1 cup flour, baking powder and vanilla.
(Sift the flour with the baking powder prior to adding it.)
Pour batter into 2 round 8-inch pans or one deep square pan.

title: crawfish dip
directions: Place tomato ketchup in a container.
Then add 1 tablespoon of hot sauce.
Stir in 1/3 cup of vinegar.
Dash in a teaspoon of salt.
Dash in a tablespoon of pepper.
Stir all ingredients together.
Mix thoroughly.
Dip crawfish in as desired.

title: icing
directions: Blend together 1 cup 10x sugar and Crisco.
Add flour, milk and egg.
Gradually add sugar and vanilla.
Stir.

title: boursin cheese
directions: Cream all ingredients thoroughly.
Chill for at least 4 hours. Serve with crackers at room temperature.

title: hot fudge sundae cake(good with ice cream)
directions: Stir first 9 ingredients all together and pour in greased cake pan.
Sprinkle brown sugar over batter.
Mix cocoa, hot water, salt and vanilla.
Pour hot water mixture over brown sugar.
Bake at 350° until cake tests done.

title: honey walleye
directions: In a shallow bowl, beat egg; add honey.
In a plastic bag, combine crackers and salt.
Dip fish in egg mixture, then shake in bag until coated.
In a skillet, cook fillets in oil for 3 to 5 minutes per side or until golden and fish flakes easily with a fork.
Yields 4 to 6 servings.

title: sausage casserole
directions: Brown onion and sausage in a large skillet, stirring to crumble sausage; drain.
Add soup mix, rice, water and almonds. Mix well and simmer several minutes.
Spoon into a greased 2 1/2-quart casserole.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes.

title: lime congealed salad
directions: Drain fruit.
Fold together fruit, Cool Whip, Jell-O and nuts. Refrigerate overnight.

title: orange-banana frost
directions: Slice banana; mix with rest.
Pour into blender; mix until smooth.
Pour into tall glasses; top with scoop of sherbet. Garnish with mint leaf.

title: strawberry loaf cake
directions: Combine sugar, oil and eggs until mixed well.
Add soda, salt and cinnamon and continue mixing.
Now add flour, fruit and nuts. Pour in greased loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 60 minutes or until done.

title: bagels
directions: Combine 2 cups flour and yeast.
Add warm water, 3 tablespoons sugar and 1 teaspoon salt.
Beat at low speed with an electric mixer for 30 seconds.
Beat at high speed for 3 minutes.
Stir in as much of remaining flour as you can.
Turn out onto a floured surface; knead in enough flour to make dough stiff, elastic and smooth (6 to 8 minutes).
Cover; let rest for 10 minutes.
Divide dough into 12 portions.
Shape each portion into a ball; punch hole in the center and shape into a bagel.
Place on a greased baking sheet.
Cover; let rise for 20 minutes.
Broil bagels 3 to 4 minutes, turning once.
Drop bagels, 4 to 5 at a time into boiling water-sugar mixture.
Let simmer 7 minutes.
Drain on paper towels.
Place drained bagels on a well-greased baking sheet.
Bake in a 375° oven for 25 to 30 minutes, or until tops are golden brown.
Makes 12 servings.

title: grandma paylor's sourdough bread
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Let stand, covered with a cloth, until it is bubbly.
Take out 2 to 3 big mixing spoons and place in clean jar with loose fitting lid; store in refrigerator.
This is the starter and will be used in place of yeast.
Add 1/2 or 2/3 cup shortening or bacon grease; add flour until stiff.
Grease bowl and place dough in it and grease top of bread dough.
Cover with a clean cloth.
Let rise double in size.
Punch down and let rise again.
Form into loaves and let rise.
Makes 2 loaves.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
I like to divide the sponge after the starter is out and put an egg, milk, spices, raisins and make some sweet rolls as well as regular bread.

title: banana bread
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Put in a greased and floured loaf pan and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: pound cake
directions: Cream butter, Crisco and sugar together, then add 5 eggs, one at a time.
Add vanilla, then some flour alternately with milk. Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 30 minutes.

title: broccoli bread
directions: Mix all ingredients except Jiffy mix.
Add mix last.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch greased pan.
Bake 25 minutes at 400°.
Cut into squares and serve hot.

title: pecan sandies
directions: Cream butter and powdered sugar.
Add vanilla and water.
Add flour.
Mix well and add pecans.
Form small rolls 1 1/2 inches long.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet in slow oven (300°) for 20 minutes or until delicately brown.
While hot, roll in powdered sugar.
Makes 3 dozen.

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: Mix eggs, sugar and sour cream.
Add flour, soda and flavoring.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour or until toothpick comes out clean.

title: perfect rice
directions: Saute onion in butter.
Add chicken broth.
Add rice; bring to boil.
Cover and bake in a preheated 350° oven for 20 to 25 minutes.
Comes out perfect!

title: brownies
directions: Melt shortening and chocolate together in saucepan over very low heat.
Remove from heat.
Add sugars, eggs and vanilla; mix well.
Add blended dry ingredients and nuts to chocolate mixture, mixing well.
Spread in well-greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: old fashioned kansas yeast bread
directions: Sprinkle yeast over very warm water in a large bowl (very warm should feel comfortable when dropped on wrist).
Stir until yeast dissolves.
Heat milk-water mixture, sugar, butter and salt in a saucepan, stirring until sugar dissolves and butter melts.
Cool to lukewarm.
Add lukewarm milk mixture to yeast.
Stir in 4 cups of flour and beat until very smooth.
Mix in 3 more cups of the flour and then turn dough out on a floured board (use some of the remaining flour for flouring the board).
Work in enough of the remaining 1 cup of flour to make a soft dough.
Knead for 10 minutes until dough is satiny and elastic.
Place dough in a greased bowl, then turn greased side up.
Cover and let rise in a warm place until double in bulk, about 1 1/2 hours.
Punch dough down; divide in half.
Cover with dry cloth and let dough rest 10 minutes.
Roll each piece of dough into an 18 x 9-inch rectangle. Roll up from the short side, jelly roll fashion.
Press each end to seal, then tuck ends underneath loaves.
Place shaped loaves in two greased 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pans, seam sides down.
Cover with a dry cloth and let rise in a warm place until double in bulk, about 1 to 1 1/4 hours.
Bake in a hot oven (400°) for 25 to 30 minutes, until nicely browned and loaves sound hollow when tapped.
Remove from oven.
Ease loaves out of pans and cool upright on wire racks.

title: wine cake
directions: Spray pan with Pam. Line pan with 1/2 cup pecans. Heat oven to 350°. In large bowl, combine cake mix, pudding, eggs, water, oil and wine. Beat 4 minutes. Pour into pan. Bake 50 to 60 minutes.

title: pork chop and potato bake
directions: Slice and arrange potatoes in greased baking dish (large). Sprinkle with 1/2 envelope onion soup mix.
Heat mushroom soup and milk in saucepan.
(You can also add corn and green beans.) Arrange pork chops on top of potatoes.
Pour heated mixture on top of pork chops.
Top with other 1/2 of envelope of onion soup mix. Sprinkle with bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: pizza ricotta and spinach
directions: Cook spinach and drain completely.
Combine Ricotta, spinach, Mozzarella, eggs, oil, seasonings and vegetables.
Pour into oiled, deep pie plate.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Top with oil or butter.
Done when knife inserted comes out clean.

title: no-knead tupperware bread
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water in a 7 quart Tupperware container.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Add flour and next 4 ingredients, stirring until well blended.
Cover container with Tupperware lid and seal.
Let stand at room temperature 1 hour or until lid
"pops off".
Spoon the dough into 3 (9 x 5 inch) loaf pans coated with cooking spray.
Cover and let the dough rise in a warm place (85°) free from drafts, 30 minutes or until doubled in bulk.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes or until loaves sound hollow when tapped.
Experiment with various typed of flour and sugar mixtures.
Yield: 16 Servings per loaf, 3 loaves.

title: eston's vanilla ice cream
directions: Beat eggs and sugar together. Stir in vanilla, whipping cream and half and half. Add milk to the fill line. Freeze.

title: green tomato casserole
directions: Slice tomatoes and onions.
Cook in large skillet with butter until mushy.
Stir in curry powder, salt, peppers and water chestnuts, sliced.
Let mixture cool, then stir in sour cream and pimientos.
Pour into shallow casserole and top with a mixture of bread crumbs and cheese.
Bake about 30 minutes in 350° oven or until bubbly and crumbs are brown.
Serves 8.

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Beat in one egg at a time.
Add combined flour and salt alternately with sour cream and vanilla. Pour into a 10-inch tube pan or 3 loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for about 1 hour to 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: "old timey" jam cake
directions: Bake 3 layers of cake going by the directions on the box. Cool before stacking.
When layers are cool, spread jam or jelly between each layer and on top layer, then cover entire cake top and sides with Cool Whip.
Place in refrigerator.
Keep cool at all times.

title: easy baked beans
directions: Fry onions, bacon and green peppers over heat; drain off.
Put in beans and brown sugar.
Heat on low for 20 minutes.
